lusion (special action) Shadow Jump (special action)     \r\n\r\n    Character Gender \r\n     \r\n    There is usually very little difference between male and female as far as the rules are concerned.\r\n    For most races, the only technical difference is in height and weight calculations.\r\n    Still, there are a few races where the two genders are distinctly different with regards to ability adjustments and other traits.\r\n     \r\n     \r\n    In these rules (as in the original ones), the words โheโ, โhimโ, and โhisโ will often refer to both genders, in an attempt to make the text somewhat easier to read.\r\n     \r\n\r\n    Character Classes \r\n\r\n	\r\n	     \r\n     HP per Level:  The number of HP gained per level (including 1st) in this class.\r\n     SP per Level:  The number of SP gained per level (including 1st) in this class.\r\n     PP per Level:  The number of PP gained per level (including 1st) in this class.\r\n     Influence per Level:  The amount of influence gained per level (including 1st) in this class.\r\n     Skill Points per Level:  The amount of skill points gained per level in this class.\r\n     Key Ability Scores:  The key ability scores for this class. A character is recommended to choose classes that match his best ability scores.\r\n     Favored Alignment:  This is a typical and/or recommended moral alignment for the class.\r\n     Spell Knowledge:  Specifies how the class learns spells and other supernatural powers.\r\n     Role-Playing Notes:  Additional notes related to role-playing characters of this class.\r\n     Roles:  Some typical roles and professions that can be seen as varieties of this class.\r\n     Ranks:  Ranks and titles that were often used for this class in an earlier version of D&amp;D.\r\n     Class Configurations:  These are typical roles for each class together with their suggested skill selections.\r\n     \r\n	    \r\n	    \r\n	     \r\n	     Class: \r\n	   	 Bard (Brd) \r\n	   	  \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 HP/Level: \r\n	   	 6 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 SP/Level: \r\n	   	 6 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 PP/Level: \r\n	   	 8 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Infl/Level: \r\n	   	 5 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Skill Pts/Level: \r\n	   	 18 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Key Ability Scores: \r\n	   	 Cha, Dex, Int \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Favored Alignment: \r\n	   	 Non-Lawful \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Spell Knowledge: \r\n	   	 Bards typically learn new spells from a teacher, an arcane spellbook, personal development, etc. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Role-Playing Notes: \r\n	   	 Most bards learn their trade as apprentices to a master bard or by attending a bardic college. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Roles: \r\n	   	 Entertainer, performer, actor, teacher, advisor, diplomat, spy. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Ranks: \r\n	   	  \r\n	   	 \r\n	     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Bard Configuration: \r\n		   	 Bard \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Acrob, Athle, Percp, Perfm, Steal, WpFnc, FSTri, ArcIl, BAff, BdKno, BdMus \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Know, Lingu, Psych, SCtrl, Thiev, WpGen, WpBow, WpBaM, ArmLt, ArcDi, ArcEn, ArcIm, DivLi, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Bard Configuration: \r\n		   	 Diplomat Bard \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Know, Lingu, Perfm, Psych, WpBaM, ArcDi, ArcEn, ArcIm, ArcIl, BAff, BdKno, BdMus, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Percp, SCtrl, WpGen, ArmLt, FSTri, ArcAb, ArcCo, ArcTr, DivIn, DivLi \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Bard Configuration: \r\n		   	 Spy Bard \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Athle, Lingu, Percp, Perfm, Psych, Steal, Thiev, WpLtB, FSTri, ArcEn, ArcIl, BdKno \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Acrob, Know, SCtrl, WpBaM, WpBow, WpGen, ArmLt, FSMob, ArcDi, DivLi, BAff, BdMus \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n	    \r\n	    \r\n	     \r\n	     Class: \r\n	   	 Cleric (Clr) \r\n	   	  \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 HP/Level: \r\n	   	 8 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 SP/Level: \r\n	   	 4 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 PP/Level: \r\n	   	 8 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Infl/Level: \r\n	   	 5 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Skill Pts/Level: \r\n	   	 18 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Key Ability Scores: \r\n	   	 Wis, Con, Cha \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Favored Alignment: \r\n	   	 Any (same as deity) \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Spell Knowledge: \r\n	   	 A cleric\'s church will teach him most of the spells that he has sufficient divine skills to cast.More unusual spells can be learned from a teacher, divine writings, personal prayers, etc. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Role-Playing Notes: \r\n	   	 Most clerics are part of an ecclesiastical hierarchy, with obligations as well as benefits. Some, however, devote themselves to their deity or philosophy without joining the official church.Clerics are common among nearly all races. Adventuring and crusading clerics are mostly seen among humans and dwarves, however.Unless the current situation prevents it, a cleric should pray regularly and observe all of the religion\'s rituals and special holy days.A cleric who violates his deity or philosophy will lose the ability to channel divine energy (cast divine spells, turn undead, etc.) until he atones. He can still gain levels in the class and improve his divine skills, but they will be mostly useless until atonement. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Roles: \r\n	   	 Priest, advisor, healer, diplomat, judge, warrior-priest. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Ranks: \r\n	   	 Acolyte, Adept, Priest, Curate, Prefect, Canon, Lama, Patriarch, High Priest \r\n	   	 \r\n	     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Cleric Configuration: \r\n		   	 Cleric of Destruction \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 WpGen, WpFll, WpCrs, WpAre, WpShd, ArmHv, DivBl, DivDe, DivLi, DivPr, DivRe, CAChs, CADes \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Heal, Percp, Ride, CmbIn, FSPow, DivEl, DivIn, DvSmi, EncIt, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Cleric Configuration: \r\n		   	 Cleric of Knowledge \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Heal, Know, Psych, WpShd, ArmMd, DivBl, DivCh, DivIn, DivLi, DivPr, DivSu, CAKno, EncIt, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Percp, CmbIn, WpGen, WpBaM, DivEl, DivRe, BdKno, CALaw \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Cleric Configuration: \r\n		   	 Cleric of Life \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Heal, Psych, WpBaM, WpShd, ArmMd, DivBl, DivCh, DivIn, DivLi, DivPr, DivRe, DivSu, CAHea, EncIt, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Percp, CmbIn, WpGen, DivEl, DivNa, DvPro \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Cleric Configuration: \r\n		   	 Cleric of War \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 WpGen, WpFll, WpCrs, WpAre, WpShd, ArmHv, Warfr, DivBl, DivDe, DivPr, DivRe, CAWar \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Heal, Percp, CmbIn, WpBaM, DivCh, DivEl, DivIn, DivLi, DivNa, DivSu, DvSmi, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n	    \r\n	    \r\n	     \r\n	     Class: \r\n	   	 Druid (Drd) \r\n	   	  \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 HP/Level: \r\n	   	 6 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 SP/Level: \r\n	   	 6 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 PP/Level: \r\n	   	 8 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Infl/Level: \r\n	   	 5 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Skill Pts/Level: \r\n	   	 18 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Key Ability Scores: \r\n	   	 Wis, Dex \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Favored Alignment: \r\n	   	 Neutral \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Spell Knowledge: \r\n	   	 A druid\'s society will teach him most of the spells that he has sufficient divine skills to cast.More unusual spells can be learned from a teacher, divine writings, personal prayers, etc. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Role-Playing Notes: \r\n	   	 Druids revere nature and abhor unnatural creatures. They shun items of a technological or mechanical nature, and they take an oath to not wear metallic armor.Nearly all druids, even the most solitary and isolated ones, are part of a global society. When the protection of nature requires it, a number of society members may cooperate, but at other times, they may compete with or even prey on each other. The society has a distinct hierarchy, but low-ranking members have few obligations towards their superiors.Most druids are elves, gnomes, humans, or half-elves.A druid who violates his deity, philosophy, or oaths of conduct will lose the ability to channel natural energy (cast divine spells, change shape, etc.) until he atones. He can still gain levels in the class and improve his druidic skills, but many of them will be mostly useless until atonement. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Roles: \r\n	   	 Protector of nature. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Ranks: \r\n	   	 Aspirant, Ovate, Initiate of the 1st Circle - Initiate of the 9th Circle, Druid, Archdruid, The Great Druid \r\n	   	 \r\n	     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Druid Configuration: \r\n		   	 Druid \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 AnEmp, WpGen, DivAn, DivEl, DivIn, DivLi, DivNa, DivPl, DivPr, DAff, AniCm, WldSh \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Athle, Heal, Know, Percp, SCtrl, Surv, WpNat, WpAre, WpBaM, WpBrl, ArmLt, SplCr \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n	    \r\n	    \r\n	     \r\n	     Class: \r\n	   	 Fighter (Ftr) \r\n	   	  \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 HP/Level: \r\n	   	 10 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 SP/Level: \r\n	   	 8 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 PP/Level: \r\n	   	 2 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Infl/Level: \r\n	   	 5 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Skill Pts/Level: \r\n	   	 18 \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Key Ability Scores: \r\n	   	 Str, Con, Dex \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Favored Alignment: \r\n	   	 Any \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Spell Knowledge: \r\n	   	  \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Role-Playing Notes: \r\n	   	 Most fighters, as compared to warriors, have had some sort of formal training, usually in an army, an academy, a gladiator school, or at least a militia.Fighters are common among all of the civilized and semi-civilized races. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Roles: \r\n	   	 Mercenary, officer, soldier, guard, bodyguard, martial trainer, champion, hunter. \r\n	   	 \r\n	   	\r\n	   	 Ranks: \r\n	   	 Veteran, Warrior, Swordsman, Hero, Swashbuckler, Myrmidon, Champion, Superhero, Lord \r\n	   	 \r\n	     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Fighter Configuration: \r\n		   	 Archer \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Athle, WpLtB, WpBow, WpCrs, ArmLt, ArmMd \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Craft, Percp, Ride, WGen, WpHvB, WpFir, WpShd, CmbIn, DmRed, DaSns, FSMob, Warfr \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Fighter Configuration: \r\n		   	 Axe Fighter \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Athle, WpGen, WpAxe, WpPlA, WpLtB, WpCrs, WpBrl, WpShd, ArmMd, ArmHv, CmbIn, DmRed, FSPow \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Craft, Ride, Percp, Surv, WpNat, WpHvB, WpExo, DaSns, FSTri, Warfr \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Fighter Configuration: \r\n		   	 Barbarian Fighter \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Athle, Surv, WpNat, WpAxe, WpBow, WpExo, WpBrl, ArmMd, Bersk, CmbIn, DmRed, FSMob, FSPow \r\n		   	 \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Secondary Skills: \r\n		   	 Acrob, Craft, Percp, Ride, Steal, WpGen, WpShd, DaSns, FSPre, FSTri \r\n		   	 \r\n		     \r\n		    \r\n		    \r\n		     \r\n		     Fighter Configuration: \r\n		   	 Duelist Fighter \r\n		   	  \r\n		   	\r\n		   	 Primary Skills: \r\n		   	 Athle, WpFnc, 