 smaller. However, this does provoke attacks of opportunity. \r\n         Flying and incorporeal creatures are not affected by obstructions on the ground. \r\n         For creatures that occupy multiple squares, the worst conditions apply. \r\n         Creatures can squeeze through areas half as wide as their normal space (or half as high as their height), but this costs double movement. While squeezing, you suffer a -4 circumstance penalty to attack rolls, DeC, and Ref. Spaces that are both narrow and low quadruple the AP cost and cause double the penalty. \r\n         If you accidentally end your movement in an illegal square, you instead end up in the previously occupied square. If this square is also illegal, you fall prone in that square. \r\n     \r\n     \r\n    Obstructed/difficult terrain includes the following features:\r\n     \r\n     \r\n         Rubble or uneven ground \r\n         Undergrowth \r\n         Steep slopes (uphill generally worse than downhill) \r\n         Slippery ground \r\n         Stairs \r\n         Ladders \r\n         Shallow pools \r\n         Low walls \r\n         Broken pillars, statues, etc. \r\n         Darkness \r\n         Dense fog \r\n     \r\n     \r\n    If multiple conditions apply, the DM is free to increase the movement cost to ร3 or ร4.\r\n     \r\n\r\n     Overland Movement \r\n     \r\n    The speed of overland movement is described above, specified as the number of km covered per day.\r\n    The speed should be modified for the terrain and the quality of the road, as shown below:\r\n     \r\n\r\n	\r\n	    	\r\n    \r\n   	Overland Movement \r\n     \r\n     Terrain \r\n    Highway Speed Mult. \r\n    Road Speed Mult. \r\n    Trackless Speed Mult. \r\n     Encounter Distance (sq) \r\n    Getting Lost Mod \r\n    Find Sustenance Mod \r\n   	  \r\n Barren or badlands &times;1 &times;1 &times;0.75  6d6x4 -3 +2   Cleared or farmland &times;1 &times;1 &times;0.75  6d6x8 -5 0   Desert, rocky &times;1 &times;1 &times;0