les the amount of clearing a character can do.\r\n     \r\n\r\n     Dungeons and Buildings \r\n     \r\n    See DMG 4E p67+ for unusual terrain features. Try to make some of them more generic, possibly looking at effects of certain extraplanar environments.\r\n     \r\n\r\n     Traps \r\n     \r\n    Traps come in many different varieties, but they can be roughly categorized as either mechanical or magic.\r\n    Traps are also defined by other parameters, such as their trigger, their attack bonus and type, their damage, etc.\r\n     \r\n     \r\n    Detecting and defeating, or maybe just surviving, a trap can be as challenging as slaying monsters,\r\n    so adventurers are awarded experience points for the traps they encounter.\r\n    The table below shows how to calculate the EL of a trap, and as usual, each EL equals 300 XP.\r\n     \r\n\r\n	\r\n	    \r\n   	Traps and Trap Modifiers \r\n     \r\n     Trap Feature \r\n    EL \r\n    Cost \r\n   	 Details \r\n   	  \r\n Pit trap 1 per 4 sq depth 100 gp per 4 sq depth  Search DC 20; Sabotage DC 20. Base attack +10 vs Ref. Damage according to falling rules.   Pit trap, spiked +1 +50 gp  As pit trap, but victims also suffer 1d4 spike attacks (+10 vs DeC; d6+2 HP P damage each).   Ranged weapon trap 1 per 7 HP 100 gp per 7 HP  Search DC 20; Sabotage DC 20. Base attack +10 vs DeC. Damage based on projectile, thrown, or falling weapon (with optional Str mod).   Melee weapon trap 1 per 7 HP 100 gp per 7 HP  Search DC 20; Sabotage DC 20. Base attack +10 vs DeC.   Poison trap Per poison Per poison  Can be an inhaled, injected, or contact poison.   Magic device trap 1 per 7 HP Enchant Item  Search DC 25; Sabotage DC 25. Base attack +10.   Magic spell trap (PP cost)/2 Varies  Varies   Easy to find -1 -50 gp  -5 Search DC   Hard to find +1 +100 gp  +5 Search DC   Very hard to find +2 +200 gp  +10 Search DC   Easy to disable -1 -50 gp  -5 Sabotage DC   Hard to disable +1 +100 gp  +5 Sabotage DC   Very hard to disable +2 +200 gp 