  Administration \r\n         Other \r\n         \r\n             Analysis  \r\n             RolCalc Examples  \r\n         \r\n      \r\n		    \r\n			\r\n    Rules of Culture \r\n     \r\n     \r\n\r\n    Social Class \r\n     \r\n     \r\n\r\n    Wealth Class \r\n     \r\n     \r\n\r\n    Reputation \r\n     \r\n    An individualโs \r\n    reputation  \r\n    will affect other peopleโs attitudes and may give bonuses or penalties to certain action checks\r\n    (Psychology skill checks in particular). Note that a reputation will only have an effect on people who know and believe in the reputation.\r\n    It is up to the DM to decide whether a reputation should apply to an action check, and also whether it should be a bonus or penalty.\r\n    In general, a reputation should be a benefit more often than a hindrance.\r\n     \r\n     \r\n    When you apply a reputation to an action check, you should generally use the full value.\r\n    When multiple reputations apply to the same check, start with the highest of them and then add half of the remaining ones.\r\n    It is also possible for one reputation to counteract or lessen another one.\r\n     \r\n\r\n    Influence \r\n     \r\n    Influence  \r\n    is a measure of your power over another individual or an organization. This power can be used to request favors,\r\n    mobilize military forces, gather economic resources, etc.\r\n     \r\n     \r\n    In many ways, an influence check can be used to achieve effects similar to those you achieve with Psychology-based skill checks.\r\n    However, while the Psychology checks try to improve the targetโs attitude towards you,\r\n    an influence check instead tries to force the target to help you (for reasons of duty or debt).\r\n     \r\n     \r\n    Influence can also be used to determine the effects and results of power struggles within an organization.\r\n    Assume, for example, that a lieutenant in a thievesโ guild assassinates his boss.\r\n    If there are no other members with a higher or similar level of influence, he can then easily take over the guild.\r\n    On the other hand, if several members have similar levels of influence, internal warfare is likely to ensue.\r\n     \r\n\r\n     Family and Clan \r\n\r\n     Contacts, Friends, and Enemies \r\n\r\n    Henchmen, Minions, and Followers \r\n\r\n	\r\n	    \r\n   	Animal Companion Improvements \r\n     \r\n    CL \r\n    Str \r\n    Dex \r\n    HP \r\n    DR \r\n    Att \r\n    Def \r\n    AP \r\n     Traits \r\n   	  \r\n+2 +1 +1 +10 +2 +1 +1 +2  +4 enh modifier on Acrobatics skill   +5 +2 +2 +20 +4 +2 +2 +4  +4 enh modifier to Will   +8 +3 +3 +30 +6 +3 +3 +6    +11 +4 +4 +40 +8 +4 +4 +8    +14 +5 +5 +50 +10 +5 +5 +10  +10 enh modifier on Acrobatics skill   +17 +6 +6 +60 +12 +6 +6 +12         \r\n\r\n	\r\n    \r\n   	Divine Mount Improvements \r\n     \r\n    CL \r\n    Str \r\n    Int \r\n    HP \r\n    DR \r\n    Att \r\n    Def \r\n    AP \r\n     Traits \r\n   	  \r\n+2 +1 +3 +10 +4 +1 +1 +2  +10 enh modifier on Acrobatics skill   +5 +2 +4 +20 +6 +2 +2 +4  +2 enh modifier to base speed   +8 +3 +5 +30 +8 +3 +3 +6  Command Similar Creatures (special action)   +12 +4 +6 +40 +10 +4 +4 +8  +lvl+5 enh modifier to MR        \r\n\r\n	\r\n    \r\n   	Familiar Improvements \r\n     \r\n    CL \r\n    Int \r\n    HP \r\n    DR \r\n    Att \r\n    Def \r\n    AP \r\n     Traits \r\n   	  \r\n0 +2 +4 +1 +1 +1 +1  +10 enh modifier on Acrobatics skill   +2 +3 +8 +2 +2 +2 +2  Deliver Touch (special action)   +4 +4 +12 +3 +3 +3 +3  Speech, with master   +6 +5 +16 +4 +4 +4 +4  Speech, with similar creatures   +8 +6 +20 +5 +5 +5 +5    +10 +7 +24 +6 +6 +6 +6  +lvl+5 enh modifier to MR   +12 +8 +28 +7 +7 +7 +7    +14 +9 +32 +8 +8 +8 +8    +16 +10 +36 +9 +9 +9 +9    +18 +11 +40 +10 +10 +10 +10         \r\n\r\n	\r\n    \r\n   	Psicrystal Improvements \r\n     \r\n    CL \r\n    Int \r\n    HP \r\n    DR \r\n    AP \r\n     Traits \r\n   	  \r\n0 +6 +12 +8 +11  Self-propulsion Ground