ation of the action.\r\n     Results:  Description of the effects of success and failure, respectively. If certain levels of success or failure have special effects, they will also be described here.\r\n     Difficulties:  If the action has different difficulty or target numbers, they are listed here. Modifiers to the DC are also listed here.\r\n     Modifiers:  A list of the modifiers that can apply to the action check (not to the DC).\r\n     \r\n Brawling Attack Actions      \r\n    Brawling actions are close combat attacks made with the whole body.\r\n     \r\n     \r\n         Grappling: Wrestling. \r\n         Crushing: Crush an opponent under your own body. \r\n         Bull Rush: Push an opponent back. \r\n         Overrun: Bowl your opponent over. \r\n     \r\n  Action:  Break Barrier - [Untrained]    Action Check:  d20 + Weapons - Brawling skill + Str mod + grapple size mod + PAM + AB vs. DC   Action Time:  8 + size mod AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Tch   Duration:  Instantaneous   Target(s)/Area:  Door, wall, barrier, etc.   Description:  You try to break down a door or similar barrier.   Results:  S - You destroy the barrier.F - You fail to break down the barrier. You can try again.   Difficulties:  Break down barrier: Barrier\'s DC     Action:  Bull Rush - [Untrained, AoO]    Action Check:  d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. opposed d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + DeB   Action Time:  8 + size mod AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Tch   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  You first move into your target\'s square (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move). You then try to push the target out of the square with an opposed Strength check.You can only Bull Rush opponents that are within one size category of yourself.   Results:  S - The target is pushed back one square. For every 5 levels of success, you can push back the opponent one more square, but you have to move with him and pay 1 additional AP per square moved. Both you and the target provoke attacks of opportunity for this move.F - You are pushed back into the last square you occupied before the attack.   Modifiers:  Target has more than two legs: -4Bull rush with charge: +2     Action:  Crush - [Untrained, AoO]    Action Check:  d20 + Str mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. Ref   Action Time:  8 + size mod AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Tch   Target(s)/Area:  Your spacing   Description:  You first move or jump into the targeted area (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move) and fall prone. By doing this, you try to pin and crush the target(s) under your own body.You can only Crush opponents that are two or more size categories smaller than yourself, since larger creatures can push you out of their square.   Results:  S - You crush the target under your body, causing blunt damage according to your size (Tiny 1d4 B, Small 1d6 B, Medium 1d8 B, Large 2d6 B, Huge 3d6 B, Gargantuan 4d6 B, Colossal 5d6 B; add Str mod to the damage).Affected targets are considered grappled until they escape, you move, or you stand up from prone.F - The target moves out of your way (for free) into any adjacent square.   Modifiers:  Crush with charge: +2     Action:  Grapple Attack - [Untrained]    Action Check:  d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. opposed grapple attack check   Action Time:  6 + size mod AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Tch   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  Grapple attacks can only be made after a grapple has been initiated, but they can be made by anyone involved in the grappling.   Results:  S - The grapple attack inflicts the same damage as an unarmed attack made by the attacker. To be more specific, this attack can involve an elbow to the face, a claw attack, bending the opponent\'s joints, crushing him with a bear hug, etc. Use the damage modifier either from Weapons - Generic, Weapons - Brawling or Weapons - Natural, whichever is higher.Alternatively, a successful check can be used to achieve one of the following results:- Draw a light weapon or other accessible item.- Make a melee attack with a light weapon against another grappler.- Escape from the grapple and move into an adjacent space. Your check has to beat all opposing grapplers for it to be successful.- Move all grapplers (including yourself) one or two squares. Your check has to beat all opposing grapplers for it to be successful.- Pin another grappler. You can only pin one opponent at a time.- Break another grappler\'s pin.- Knock another grappler prone.- Use a light weapon held by another grappler to attack him or another grappler. This first requires a successful grapple check and then a melee attack roll with a -4 attack penalty.Once you have an opponent pinned, a successful check can also be used to achieve these results:- Throw the pinned opponent into an adjacent square (if no other grappler is also grappling the same opponent). For every 5 levels of success, you can throw the opponent one square further away, causing damage as if the opponent had fallen the same distance. The thrown opponent is no longer pinned or grappled.- Try to incapacitate the pinned opponent, causing twice the normal grappling damage in SP.- Prevent the pinned opponent from speaking (and using verbal components) until the pin is broken.- The pinned opponent can be used as an improvised weapon or shield against non-grappling opponents until the pin is broken.- If you have a mouth and are four or more size categories larger than the pinned opponent (or have an improved swallow ability), you can swallow the opponent. This automatically causes bite damage. The opponent is considered grappled even after being swallowed, but the swallower is no longer grappled.F - You inflict no damage.   Modifiers:  More free primary natural attacks than opponent: +4Using a single primary attack form: -20 (the attacker is not considered grappled)     Action:  Initiate Grapple - [Untrained, AoO]    Action Check:  d20 + Dex mod + size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. DeC   Action Time:  8 + size mod AP   Implements:  C, primary attack(s)   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Tch   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  To start a grapple, first make the indicated action check against your opponent. If the attack of opportunity causes damage, the grapple automatically fails. If the target is already grappling with someone else, this check is automatically successful.If you successfully initiate a grapple with a target two or more size categories larger than you, you are holding onto the target, but the target is not considered grappled (unless it chooses to be).   Results:  S - You are now grabbing (but not grappling) the target. Next, make a free grapple attack (see Grapple Attack action). If this attack succeeds, you deal normal grapple damage to the target, move into the target\'s square, and are now grappling with the target. This move provokes attacks of opportunity from opponents other than the target.As an alternative to dealing damage, the attacker can choose among the other effects listed under the grapple attack action (except pin).F - You lose the grab and fail to initiate the grapple.   Modifiers:  More free primary natural attacks than opponent: +4Using a single primary attack form: -20 (the attacker is not considered grappled; this also means that the attacker can move normally, carrying along all grapplers)     Action:  Overrun - [Untrained, AoO]    Action Check:  d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. opposed d20 + Str or Dex mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + DeB   Action Time:  8 + size mod AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Tch   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  You first move into your target\'s square (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move).Your opponent can simply choose to avoid you, and in that case, you continue your move out of the square (and action time is reduced by 4 AP).If your opponent tries to block, you make the opposed check shown above.   Results:  S - The defender is knocked prone, and you can choose to continue your movement.If the target is smaller than you, you can make a free leg attack against it.F - You are pushed back into the previous square.EF - You are pushed back into the previous square and knocked prone.   Modifiers:  Target has more than two legs: -4Overrun with charge: +2    Defense Actions   Action:  Assume Defensive Stance    Action Check:  d20 + Defensive Stance skill + Wis mod + PAM vs. DC   Action Time:  4 AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  4 SP/r   Range:  Personal   Duration:  Until ended   Target(s)/Area:  You   Description:  You assume a defensive stance, temporarily gaining a +2 morale bonus to Str, +2 to Con, and +2 to all defenses (Fort, Ref, Will, and DeC).While in defensive stance, you cannot use any [Move]-related action without losing the bonuses.Skill level 8: You can now use 1 MP per round for movement actions without losing defensive stance.Skill level 9: The cost of defensive stance decreases to 3 SP per round.Skill level 11: The bonuses while in defensive stance increase to +4 Str, +4 Con, and +4 defenses.Skill level 15: You can now use 2 MP per round for movement actions without losing defensive stance.Skill level 17: The cost of defensive stance decreases to 2 SP per round.Skill level 21: The bonuses while in defensive stance increase to +6 Str, +6 Con, and +6 defenses.Skill level 22: You can now use 3 MP per round for movement actions without losing defensive stance.Skill level 25: The cost of defensive stance decreases to 1 SP per round.Skill level 29: You can now use 4 MP per round for movement actions without losing defensive stance.   Results:  S - You assume a defensive stance and gain the indicated bonuses.F - You fail to assume the correct stance. You can try again next round.   Difficulties:  Assume defensive stance: 10     Action:  Cloaking Dance    Action Check:  d20 + Stealth skill + Dex mod + PAM vs. base DC 25   Action Time:  5 AP   Implements:  C   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Personal   Duration:  1 r   Target(s)/Area:  You   Description:  You whirl your cloak in a distracting way or use some other optical trick and movement to conceal your position.   Results:  S - You gain concealment against creatures relying on vision.ES - You gain good concealment against creatures relying on vision.F - You gain no benefit.     Action:  Defensive Roll    Action Check:  d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. 10 + damage dealt   Action Time:  Reaction   Implements:  C   Cost:  2 SP   Range:  Personal   Duration:  Instantaneous   Target(s)/Area:  You   Description:  When you are struck by a weapon attack that would reduce you to 0 HP or less, you can attempt to reduce the damage by rolling with the blow.   Results:  S - Halve the damage you would otherwise have taken from the attack.CS - You avoid the attack completely.F - You take normal damage from the attack.     Action:  Deflect Projectile    Action Check:  d20 + Danger Sense skill + Dex mod + PAM + DeB vs. ranged attack roll   Action Time:  Reaction   Implements:  Weapon   Range:  Personal   Duration:  Instantaneous   Target(s)/Area:  One projectile   Description:  You can attempt to deflect projectiles or thrown weapons that would otherwise strike you. Siege weapon projectiles and most magical attacks cannot be deflected.   Results:  S - You deflect the projectile and take no damage from it.CS - If you have a free hand, you can choose to catch the projectile instead of deflecting it.F - You fail to deflect the projectile and take normal damage.   Modifiers:  Ki - Defense synergy: +1 per 5 lvls     Action:  Dodging - [Untrained, Move]    Action Check:  d20 + Fighting Style - Mobility skill + Dex mod +