 or other object. \r\n         Melee Trip: Use your weapon to trip an opponent. \r\n     \r\n  Action:  Entangling Attack    Action Check:  (Weapon attack vs. DeC) + (d20 + Fighting Style - Trickery / 2 + Int mod + PAM + AB vs. Ref)   Action Time:  As per attack + 3 AP   Implements:  C, weapon   Cost:  As per attack   Range:  As per attack   Duration:  Spcl   Target(s)/Area:  1 creature   Description:  You use your weapon to slow an opponent down or even prevent him from moving.   Results:  If the weapon attack hits and deals damage, the secondary attack has the following effects:S - Your opponent\'s adjusted speed is halved for 1 round.ES - Your opponent\'s adjusted speed is halved for the rest of the encounter.CS - Your opponent is entangled (and immobilized) for the rest of the encounter.F - No effect other than the attack\'s regular damage.     Action:  Melee Attack - [Untrained]    Action Check:  d20 + Str or Dex mod + size mod + skill mod + PAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC   Action Time:  8 + weapon\'s size mod AP   Implements:  C, melee weapon   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Reach   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  You make a normal attack with a melee weapon against an opponent within reach.If the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.   Results:  S - You deal normal damage.ES - Halve DR against this attack.CS - You deal additional damage according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier.F - You miss.EF - You deal normal damage to your weapon (no effect for natural weapons).CF - The defender can try to deflect your attack back on you or against another target adjacent to you both. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon with a -4 penalty.     Action:  Melee Coup de Grace - [Untrained, AoO]    Action Check:  Melee attack roll + 20 vs. DeC   Action Time:  12 + weapon\'s size mod AP   Implements:  C, weapon   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  1 sq   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  You use a melee weapon to deliver a coup de grace against a helpless defender.   Results:  As per attack. If the attack results in a critical hit, the attacker can make a secondary attack of (d20 + damage dealt) vs. Fort defense (S - defender takes an additional 100 HP of damage).     Action:  Melee Disarm - [Untrained]    Action Check:  Melee attack roll vs. DeC + target weapon\'s size mod   Action Time:  8 + your weapon\'s size mod AP   Implements:  C, melee weapon   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Reach   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  You try to knock your opponent\'s weapon, shield, wand, or other exposed item out of his hands.If the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender. If this attack of opportunity causes damage, the disarm automatically fails.   Results:  S - You hit the weapon, and the defender has to make a Str or Dex check against (5 + damage). If this check fails, the weapon or item is dropped (for every 5 levels of failure, it lands 1 sq further away). If you are doing the disarm with a hand (or other natural weapon with a grip), you can instead choose to grab the weapon or item for yourself.F - The disarm fails.EF - The defender manages to disarm you instead.   Modifiers:  Attacking weapon is larger than target item: +4 per size categoryAttacking weapon is smaller than target item: -4 per size categoryTarget item is exposed but not a melee weapon: +4Target item is semi-exposed (e.g. necklace, helmet, weapon in scabbard): -4Target item is held in locked gauntlet or hard to reach or grab (e.g. ring): -10Defender is pinned by attacker: +4     Action:  Melee Sunder - [Untrained]    Action Check:  Melee attack roll vs. DeC + target item\'s size mod   Action Time:  8 + your weapon\'s size mod AP   Implements:  C, melee weapon   Cost:  1 SP   Range:  Reach   Target(s)/Area:  1 target   Description:  You try to damage or destroy an opponent\'s weapon, shield, or other object.