e spellโs effect (and the PP cost modifier in parenthesis).\r\n     Target/Area:  The focus, target, or area of the spellโs effect (and the PP cost modifier in parenthesis).\r\n     Description:  General description and explanation of the spell.\r\n     Options:  Description of additional spell options that can be learned and used.\r\n     Results:  Description of the effects of success and failure, respectively. If certain levels of success or failure have special effects, it will also be described here.\r\n     Modifiers:  A list of the modifiers that can apply to the spellcasting check or attack check.\r\n     \r\n  Spell:  Affliction - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - NecromancyDivine - NatureDivine - Retribution   Attack/Action Check:  Ranged: d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. FortTch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  0 PP+1 PP for deafness+1 PP for blindness+3 PP for disease+3 PP for poison   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)Medium (+6)   Duration:  1 r (+0)Encounter (D; +2)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +6)1 month (D; +8)1 year (D; +10)Permanent (D; +12)Instantaneous (+16)   Target/Area:  1 living creature (+0)2 living creatures (+2)3-4 living creatures (+4)5-8 living creatures (+6)9-16 living creatures (+8)   Description:  You afflict the targets with deafness, blindness, and/or a debilitating disease.   Options:  Disease option: Caster can choose one of the following diseases: Blinding sickness, Cackle fever, Filth fever, Mindfire, Red ache, Shakes, and Slimy doom. The disease strikes immediately, with no incubation period.Poison option [Poison]: You inflict the target with a horrible poison (see Affliction Poison).   Results:  S - The target suffers the chosen effects.CS - The effect\'s duration increases by one step for free.F - The target avoids the effect.     Spell:  Air Walk - [Su, MR, AoO, Air]    Skill(s):  Divine - Elements   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)F (divine implement)   Cost:  7 PP+6 PP for wind walk   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)Medium (+6)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)2 creatures (+2)3-4 creatures (+4)5-8 creatures (+6)9-16 creatures (+8)   Description:  The targets can tread on air as if it was solid ground. They can walk up or down at a maximum angle of 45 degrees.A mount of animal intelligence has to be trained before it can walk on air successfully.   Options:  Wind walk option: The targets can also turn into gaseous form and back at will (5 r transformation time). When gaseous, a target can choose a base speed of 2 (perfect maneuverability) or 60 (poor maneuverability).     Spell:  Analyze Dweomer - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Divination and OuranomancyPsi - Clairsentience (+2 PP cost)   Attack/Action Check:  (d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will)   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)F (500+ sp gem)   Cost:  1 PP   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)Medium (+6)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)Concentration (+4)   Target/Area:  Objects or creatures (+0)   Description:  You discern all active spells and magical properties of an object or creature. If you choose the \"concentration\" duration, you can redirect the spell and analyze multiple targets.For magical items, you learn of all functions, how to activate them, and how many PP it has. For active spells, you learn of the skill, the spell, and the power level.   Results:  S - You discern all active spells and magical properties of the target.F - You fail to analyze the target.     Spell:  Animal Shapes - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Wild Shape   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  11 PP   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  1 day (D; +0)   Target/Area:  1 willing creat. (+0)2 willing creat. (+2)3-4 willing creat. (+4)5-8 willing creat. (+6)9-16 willing creat. (+8)   Description:  You change the shape of all targets into the same kind of animal. This is a grade II shapechange.Each target can terminate the effect on itself at will.     Spell:  Animate Objects - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - TransmutationDivine - LifePsi - Psychokinesis   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+2 PP for full mobility   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  1 small object (+0)2 small objects (+2)3-4 small objects (+4)5-8 small objects (+6)9-16 small objects (+8)   Description:  The basic spell allows you to give simple commands to inanimate and unattended objects (but within their inherent limitations). For example, a rope can be commanded to \"coil\", \"knot\" itself, \"loop\", \"uncoil\", \"entangle\" (a creature in the same square), etc. An unlocked chest can be commanded to \"open\" or \"close\".Larger objects than small can also be animated. One medium object counts as two small, one large as four small, one huge as eight small, and one gargantuan as sixteen small.   Options:  Full mobility option: The objects gain full mobility and attack ability (see the creature chapter).     Spell:  Animate Plants - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - Plants   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+2 PP for spike growth+10 PP for liveoak+12 PP full mobility+12 PP for changestaff+12 PP for shambler   Range:  Medium (+0)Long (+3)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  Plants in spherical spread; 8 sq radius (+0)   Description:  The basic spell animates all normal plants in the area of effect and causes them to entangle all creatures that enter the area.   Options:  Spike growth option: Instead of animating the plants in the area, you turn them into a mass of hard and sharp spikes. Their appearance does not change, but they cause 1d4 HP of damage for every square that a creature moves on foot through the area. Furthermore, if a +10 attack roll succeeds against a creature injured by the spikes, its movement is halved for 24 h (as per caltrop wounds).Full mobility option: You give full mobility and attack ability to a maximum of eight large plants in the area. A huge plant counts as two large, a gargantuan plant as four large, and a colossal plant as eight large. See animated objects in the creature chapter for details.Liveoak option: You transform any Huge tree in the area into a treant-like creature (see the creature chapter) that defends you and obeys your spoken commands.Changestaff option: Same as the liveoak option, but this instead transforms any wooden staff (or small tree).Shambler option: You transform some of the undergrowth into 1d4+2 shambling mounds that defend you and obey your spoken commands.     Spell:  Antilife Shell - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - Protection   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)F (divine implement)   Cost:  5 PP for anti-plant+2 PP for anti-vermin+4 PP for anti-animal+6 PP for anti-life   Range:  0 (+0)   Duration:  1 h (D; +0)   Target/Area:  Spherical emanation; 2 sq radius (+0)   Description:  The basic spell creates an invisible and mobile barrier that keeps out plant creatures and animated plants.Forcing the barrier against an affected creature disrupts the field.   Options:  Anti-vermin option: The barrier also keeps out vermin (small mammals, insects, arachnids, etc).Anti-animal option: Like anti-vermin, but the barrier also keeps out animals, monstrous animals, and vermin.Anti-life option: Like anti-animal, but the barrier also keeps out aberrations, dragons, humanoids, and monstrous humanoids (but not outsiders, elementals, constructs, and undead).     Spell:  Antimagic - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Ouranomancy and AbjurationDivine - ProtectionPsi - Psychokinesis and Telepathy   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)Reaction (+10)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for +1 resistance+3 PP per additional +1+4 PP for specific MR+8 PP for generic MR+6 PP for backlash+8 PP for spell turning+8 PP for spell leeching   Range:  Personal (+0)Tch (+3)Close (+6)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)2 creatures (+2)3-4 creatures (+4)5-8 creatures (+6)9-16 creatures (+8)Spherical emanation; 2 sq radius (+0), 4 sq rad (+4), 6 sq rad (+8)   Description:  The basic spell grants a resistance bonus to defenses against spells and other supernatural effects.If you select an emanation as the area of effect and one of the MR options, you effectively create an area of anti-magic of the specified strength.   Options:  Specific MR option: You grant the targets magic resistance equal to your skill level against all spells belonging to a single arcane, divine, or psi skill.Generic MR option: You grant the targets generic magic resistance equal to your skill level.Backlash option: Anyone who casts a spell or uses a power that can be affected by the Antimagic power suffers a backlash that inflicts a loss of 2 PP.Spell turning option: You add spell turning to the protection. Casters who cast rays and targeted spells (but not area effects) against the resistance and fail will themselves become a target.Spell leeching option: Same as spell turning option, but instead of turning a spell against its caster, you absorb some of the spell\'s power. If you are the target of a ray or targeted spell, and the spell fails, you gain half of the spell\'s (total PP cost + PP boost) as temporary PP.     Spell:  Antipathy/Sympathy - [Su, MR, AoO, Mind]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Enchantment   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  1 h (+0)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)M (gem worth 100+ gp)   Cost:  15 PP   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  1 day (D; +0)1 month (D; +4)1 year (D; +6)Permanent (D; +8)   Target/Area:  Location or object; Up to 8 cubes per level   Description:  With the Antipathy effect you cause an object or location to repel creatures of a specific race or alignment.With the Sympathy spell you cause an object or location to attract creatures of a specific race or alignment.   Results:  S - The spell works as intended.Antipathy: Affected creatures are unable to enter or approach.Sympathy: Affected creatures feel an overpowering urge to stay in the area or touch the object.F - The spell fails to attract or repel the target.Antipathy: Intended creatures feel uncomfortable (shaken) within the area of effect.     Spell:  Arcane Mark - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Illusion   Attack/Action Check:  (d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC)   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+1 PP for invisible mark+2 PP for location+8 PP for secret chest+14 PP for summoning   Range:  Tch (+0)   Duration:  Permanent (+0)   Target/Area:  One personal mark   Description:  You mark any object or surface with your personal rune or mark (up to six separate characters). The mark can be no larger than 30x30 cm. On a living creature, the mark disappears after roughly one month.   Options:  Invisible option: The mark is invisible, but can be seen by anyone able to detect magic or invisibility.Location option (req Arcane - Divination): As long as you are in the same plane, you can sense the approximate direction and distance to the mark.Secret chest option (req Arcane - Conjuration and Ouranomancy; [Dimension]): You mark a special chest (constructed of expensive materials and worth at least 500 gp) that you can repeatedly hide on the Ethereal Plane and summon to your present location at will (5 AP cost). Regardless of the chest\'s actual size, it can contain 30 litres per skill level.Summoning option (req Arcane - Conjuration; [Teleport]): If the mark is placed on an object weighing no more than 5 kg, you can summon it to your current location at any time (5 AP cost). If the object is held or carried by another creature, you have to make a spellcasting check against that creature\'s Will.     Spell:  Arcane Ward - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Abjuration and Divination   Action Time:  10 min (+0)1 min (+2)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)F (tiny bell)   Cost:  1 PP+4 PP keeps out animals+4 PP trigger on ethereal+6 PP for protection   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  1 day (D; +0)1 month (D; +4)1 year (D; +6)Permanent (D; +8)   Target/Area:  Spherical emanation; 4 sq radius (+0), 8 sq radius (+4)   Description:  You create a ward that triggers a mental or audible alarm every time a creature of tiny or larger size enters without saying the password.Mental alarm: If you are within 1 km, you hear a mental \"ping\". It wakes you up from normal sleep but does not interrupt your concentration.Audible alarm: A bell-like sound is heard for 1 round within the warded area and up to 12 squares outside.   Options:  Animal option: Normal animals will not willingly enter the area.Ethereal option: The alarm will also trigger on incorporeal and extradimensional creatures.Protection option [Illusion]: When the ward triggers, a number of protective effects take place. The area fills with dense fog (as in Fog Cloud spell), all doors become magically held (as in Hold Object spell), stairways are filled with strong entangling webs, up to ten doors can be hidden behind illusory walls, and the fog can be made nauseating in two separate positions. All of these effects have a duratio