 defenses.Despair option: Same as sadness, but with a -4 penalty (instead of -2).Hope option: You instill hope, giving the targets a +2 morale bonus on all action checks, weapon damage rolls, and defenses.Heroism option: Same as hope, but with a +4 bonus (instead of +2).Mirth option: The target laughs uncontrollably, falling prone and rendered unable to take actions. This effect does not work against creatures of Int 2 or lower.Discord option: The target becomes very irritated and aggressive. Each round there is a 50% chance that it attacks the nearest conscious creature with its most effective attack.Death wish option: The target gets a suicidal urge and spends its actions trying to harm itself in the most efficient manner. This can include attacking itself, provoking opportunity attacks, jumping into a fire, etc.Dancing option: The target gets an uncontrollable urge to dance and can perform no other actions. The dancing imposes a -4 penalty to DeC, -10 penalty to Ref defense, and negates any parry bonus to DeC.   Results:  S - You successfully affect the emotions of the target.CS - The effect\'s duration increases by one step for free.F - You fail to affect the target.   Modifiers:  You or your allies are attacking the targets: -5 for calm emotions     Spell:  Control Fire - [Su, AoO, Fire]    Skill(s):  Arcane - PyromancyDivine - ElementsPsi - Psychokinesis   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for control (sz F, +2 PP per increased size)3 PP for pyrotechnics3 PP for smoke cloud5 PP for quench   Range:  Medium (+0)Long (+3)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  1 fire source (+0)   Description:  The basic spell lets you control an existing fire of up to the specified size. You can increase or decrease the size by one step or you can move the fire up to 6 squares.The pyrotechnics effect consumes a nonmagical fire source (up to a 4ร4ร4 squares volume) by turning it into a momentary pyrotech