s (+0)   Description:  The basic spell gradually heats or chills stone and metal objects. The maximum amount of affected material is 10 kg per skill level, and a creature must wear metal armor or carry metal and stone objects weighing at least one-fifth of its own weight to suffer the effects listed below.Round 1: Cold/Warm, No damageRound 2: Icy/Hot, 1d4 HP of cold/fireRound 3+: Freezing/Searing, 2d4 HP of cold/fire   Results:  S - You successfully heat or chill the targeted objects.F - You fail to affect the objects.     Spell:  Control Undead - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - NecromancyDivine - Death   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+2 PP for charm+4 PP for hold+6 PP for compulsion   Range:  Close (+0)Medium (+3)   Duration:  Concentration (+0)Encounter (D; +2)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +6)1 month (D; +8)1 year (D; +10)Permanent (D; +12)   Target/Area:  1 undead (+0)2 undead (+2)3-4 undead (+4)5-8 undead (+6)9-16 undead (+8)   Description:  The basic spell makes you and your companions effectively invisible to the targeted undead, causing them to ignore you completely (as long as you don\'t touch or attack them).   Options:  Charm option: You change the target\'s attitude to friendly. You will still need additional skill checks to convince the creature to do things it would not ordinarily do, and suicidal orders will not be obeyed. If you attack the target, you automatically break the spell.Hold option: You render the target immobile and helpless.Compulsion option: You can actually control the undead creatures (compelled condition) with simple mental commands as long as they remain within range.   Results:  S - You successfully affect the target.CS - The effect\'s duration increases by one step for free.F - You fail to affect the target.   Modifiers:  You or your allies are attacking the targets: -5     Spell:  Control Vegetation - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - PlantsCleric Affinity - Plant Domain   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  5 PP   Range:  Long (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  Special (see below)   Description:  This spell can have one of the following effects:Overgrowth: You cause normal vegetation to become extra thick and overgrown (see heavy undergrowth in Environment chapter). Multiply all movement costs in the area by 4. The area can be a 20 square radius circle, a 30 square radius semicircle, or a 40 square radius quarter-circle.Prune growth: You cause normal vegetation to shrink to one-third its normal size, becoming less tangled and bushy. The vegetation appears to have been carefully pruned and trimmed. The area can be a 20 square radius circle, a 30 square radius semicircle, or a 40 square radius quarter-circle.Greenshield: You cause an area of abundant foliage to shape itself into 6 sq diameter hemispherical \"chamber\". Creatures inside have full concealment towards the outside, and good concealment the other way. The area looks relatively natural and can only be detected with a DC 15 Spot check.Enrichment: You increase the potential growth and productivity of normal vegetation by one-third for one year. The area is a circle of 1 km radius.Stunt growth: You reduce the potential growth and productivity of normal vegetation by one-third for one year. The area is a circle of 1 km radius.     Spell:  Control Water - [Su, AoO, Water]    Skill(s):  Arcane - HydromancyDivine - ElementsCleric Affinity - Ocean Domain   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  9 PP   Range:  Long (+0)   Duration:  1 h (D; +0)   Target/Area:  Circular surface of water; 20 sq rad (+0), 30 sq rad (+4), 40 sq rad (+8)+4 for shapeable   Description:  You raise or lower a surface of water by up to 0.5 m per skill level. Boats at the edge of the altered surface will slide down to the lower level.     Spell:  Control Weather - [Su, AoO, Air, Water]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Aeromancy and HydromancyDivine - Elements and Nature   Action Time:  10 min (+0)1 min (+4)9 AP (+10)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for winds+6 PP for weather+10 PP for extreme weather+10 PP for vengeance+12 PP for cyclone+12 PP for waterspout+14 PP for maelstrom   Range:  Medium (+0)Long (+3)   Duration:  Concentration (+0)1 h (+4)1 day (+8)1 month (+12)Permanent (+16)   Target/Area:  Cylindrical volume; up to 8 x level sq rad, 8 sq high (+0); 3 km rad, 3 km high (+4); 6 km rad, 3 km high (+8)   Description:  You alter the winds and/or weather in the local area. The wind effects are noticed as soon as the casting is completed, but other weather effects take approximately 10 minutes to manifest.For wind, you can alter its direction and strength, and you can optionally create a calm eye around you of up to 8 square radius. Other than a normal wind blowing in a single direction, you can create a downdraft from the center outward, an updraft from the edges towards the center, or a clockwise or counterclockwise rotation. For every skill level, you can increase or decrease the wind speed by 3 m/s.   Options:  Weather option: In addition to controlling the winds, you can also increase or decrease precipitation, fog, and temperature. However, you can only create weather conditions that are appropriate for the climate and season.Extreme weather option: Same as weather option, but you can also create weather conditions that are not typical or appropriate for the climate and season.Vengeance option (req Divine - Retribution): You summon a fierce storm, including black clouds, lightning, and thunder. If you concentrate on the storm for a minimum number of rounds, you can trigger specific effects in the area; after 2 or more rounds, acid rain causing 1d6 HP of damage; 3 or more rounds, six bolts of lightning strike one square each (+20 attack against Ref; S - 10d6 HP of electricity damage; F - half damage); 4 or more rounds, hailstones dealing 5d6 HP of blunt damage. Even when you don\'t concentrate on the storm, it reduces visibility to 1 square, effectively deafens all creatures in the area, quadruples movement costs, and makes ranged attacks impossible.Cyclone option: As part of the wind alteration, you create a small cyclone that lasts for up to one round per skill level. The cyclone has a 2 sq diameter at the base, 6 sq diameter at the top, and is 6 sq tall. It can move 12 squares per round, and you can specify its path at the time of casting or control it each round by spending 6 AP. Creatures of Large size or smaller take 3d6 HP per round in contact with the cyclone. If a +10 attack beats the Ref of a victim of Medium size or smaller, it is bodily picked up by the cyclone and carried along, automatically taking 1d6 HP and 1d6 SP of damage per round.Waterspout option: You cause a waterspout to rise up from a body of water at least 2 squares wide and 4 squares deep. The spout has a 1 sq radius and is 16 sq tall, and you can move it 6 squares per round (but it must remain over water). Creatures and objects in contact with the spout suffer a +8 attack against Ref each round. A successful attack causes 4d6 SP of damage. Creatures and objects of medium size or smaller are sucked into the spout and take 2d6 SP per round for 1d3 rounds (after which they are expelled).Maelstrom option: You create a deadly vortex in a body of water. The vortex has a 12 square radius and is 12 squares deep, and the body of water must be at least this size. Any creature or craft of large size or smaller suffers a +10 attack against Ref each round. If the attack succeeds, the target is sucked into the vortex. Once sucked inside, a target is battered for 4d6 SP per round for 2d4 rounds (after which it is expelled).     Spell:  Courage - [Su, MR, AoO, Mind]    Skill(s):  Divine - Charm   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+4 PP for immunity   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)2 creatures (+2)3-4 creatures (+4)5-8 creatures (+6)9-16 creatures (+8)   Description:  You instill courage in the target creatures, giving them a +4 morale bonus against fear effects. Fear effects that are active at the time of casting are suppressed for the spell\'s duration.   Options:  Immunity option: The target creatures become completely immune to fear effects and morale penalties.     Spell:  Create Object - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Conjuration and TransmutationDivine - SummoningPsi - Metacreativity   Action Time:  10 min (+0)1 min (+4)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  1 object of vegetable matter (+0)1 stone object (+2)1 metal object (+4)1 crystal object (+6)   Description:  You create a non-magical, non-living object of the chosen material. The object can also include parts of simpler, cheaper materials. Complicated items require a Crafting check to be successfully created.The finished object is limited to a mass of 20 kg per skill level.     Spell:  Create Portal - [Su, AoO, Teleport]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Ouranomancy   Attack/Action Check:  Spellcasting check vs. base DC 20   Action Time:  10 min (+0)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)M (100 gp of amber)   Cost:  13 PP for destination at long range+2 PP for unlimited+6 PP for extraplanar+2 PP for two-way+4 PP for keyed   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  1 r (+0)Encounter (D; +2)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +6)1 month (D; +8)1 year (D; +10)Permanent (D; +12)Instantaneous (+16)   Target/Area:  Circular portal; 1 to 4 sq diameter (+0)   Description:  You create an interdimensional connection between a location near you and another location within long range. Anything (including creatures, objects, spells and powers, air, water, light, and sound) that passes through the portal from the front side is shunted from the origin to the destination. From the back side, a portal is inert and invisible.   Options:  Unlimited option: The destination can be any location in the same plane.Extraplanar option: The destination can be any location on any plane.Two-way option: The portal is two-way and clearly visible at both the origin and destination locations.Keyed option: The portal is keyed to a trigger of some sort. Here are some example triggers: active when exposed to sunlight, active at the autumn equinox, active for one minute after password is spoken, active only for creatures carrying a certain medallion, etc.   Results:  S - You create a portal to the correct destination.F - You create a portal, but you miss the destination by 1d4ร10%.OF - You fail to open the portal.   Modifiers:  Very familiar destination: +0Studied destination carefully: -2Seen destination casually: -4Viewed destination once: -6     Spell:  Create Sustenance - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - Life and Summoning   Action Time:  10 min (+0)1 min (+2)1 r (+4)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for water or purification+4 PP for food+10 PP for feast   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  Sustenance (see below)   Description:  The basic spell creates up to 10 l of water per skill level. Alternatively, it can be used to purify spoiled, rotten, or poisoned food and drink, making it suitable for eating and drinking. The latter use is limited to an amount suitable for 10 M-sized creatures per skill level (daily intake).   Options:  Food option: In addition to the water, you create simple but nourishing fare for up to 3 M-sized creatures per skill level (daily intake). The food stays fresh for approximately 24 hours.Feast option: You bring forth a great feast suitable for up to one M-sized creature per skill level. In addition to the food and drink, you call forth tables, chairs, and services that remain for 1 hour. Those that partake of the feast\'s beverage are cured of natural diseases and nausea, become immune to poison for 12 h, and receive temporary HP equal to your skill level (also for up to 12 h). Those that partake of the food become immune to fear and receive a +1 morale bonus to attack rolls and Will defense for 12 h. At least 1 hour must be spent drinking and eating in order to receive the benefits.     Spell:  Create Undead - [Su, AoO, Necrotic]    Skill(s):  Arcane - NecromancyDivine - Death   Action Time:  1 h (+0)1 min (+4)9 AP (+8)6 AP (+14)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)M (gems)   Cost:  1 PP for zombies and skeletons+6 PP for ghouls+7 PP for ghasts+10 PP for mummies+11 PP for shadows+12 PP for wraiths+13 PP for mohrgs+14 PP for spectres+15 PP for devourers   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  1 corpse (+0)2 corpses (+2)3-4 corpses (+4)5-8 corpses (+6)9-16 corpses (+8)   Description:  The basic spell can infuse relatively intact bodies and skeletons with necrotic energy and animate them into zombies and undead skeletons, respectively. The created undead will obey your spoken commands.If you spend additional PP, you can create more powerful undead.See the creature chapter for details about each type of undead, but note that the maximum total level of each undead created is equal to your skill level. Also note that the total level of controlled undead can never exceed four times your skill level. If you exceed this limit, you lose control over the undead you created first.The created undead remain animated until they are destroyed. Once destroyed, they cannot be animated again.The gems consumed during the process have to be worth a minimum of 50 sp per TL of undead created.     Spell:  Create Wall - [Su, AoO, Earth]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Conjuration and LithomancyDivine - Elements and Summoning   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)M (5 gp of gold dust)   Cost:  9 PP for stone wall11 PP for iron wall   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  1 x level squares (S; +0)   Description:  You create a vertical wall of stone or iron that automatically merges into adjoining surfaces. The wall can be up to 1 cm thick per skill level. The wall must be unbroken and cannot be created in the same space as a creature or object.You can also create a non-vertical wall, to use as a bridge or ramp, for instance. Such a wall must be buttressed and supported on at least two sides (halving the available area).You can add crenellations and battlements to the wall, but this halves the available area.     Spell:  Create Web - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Conjuration   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Dex mod + Area Attack skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Ref   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  3 PP   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  4 sq radius spread (+0)   Description:  You create a mass of sticky web-like strands, entangling creatures in the area. The strands must be anchored on at least two sides.One square of web counts as cover, while four squares count as total cover.The webs are flammable; a torch \"attack\" destroys one square, and magical fire destroys everything in the area. Creatures caught in a burning web take 2d4 HP of fire damage.   Results:  S - Affected target is entangled.CS - The target is entangled and unable to leave its square.F - The target is not entangled, but the area is still considered difficult terrain.     Spell:  Crystal Shard - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Psi - Metacreativity   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Dex mod + weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC/Ref   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for 3d6 HP of damage+2 PP per additional d6 HP   Range:  Close (+0)Medium (+3)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  Ray (+0)Conical spread, 3 sq long (+2); starting at casterSpherical spread, 4 sq radius (+4)   Description:  You create and fire a razor-sharp crystal (or crystals) at a target, dealing the specified amount of piercing damage.   Results:  S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.ES - Target\'s DR is halved against this damage.CS - The target takes double damage.F - You miss the target.     Spell:  Cure Affliction - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - LifePsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+2 PP for anti-paralysis+2 PP for lesser restoration+2 PP for delay poison+4 PP for neutralize poison+4 PP for cure blindness+4 PP for cure deafness+4 PP for cure disease+4 PP for cure insanity+4 PP for medium restoration+8 PP for greater restoration+10 PP for life force   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)Also see below   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)2 creatures (+2)3-4 creatures (+4)5-8 creatures (+6)9-16 creatures (+8)   Description:  The basic spell removes minor adverse conditions (dazed, dazzled, nauseated, sickened, and stunned). It also provides the caster with a +5 circumstance bonus when using the Heal skill to diagnose or treat the target creature(s).   Options:  Anti-paralysis option: You remove the effects of any paralysis from the creature(s).Lesser restoration option: You restore 1d4 points of ability damage to one ability score.Delay poison option: Suppresses the effects of any poison for 1 day, regardless of whether the target already has poison in its system or is exposed to poison during the day.Neutralize poison option: Instead of temporarily suppressing the effects of poison, it removes all poison from the target\'s system and also makes it immune to poison for 1 day.Cure blindness option: You cure blindness, whether it is natural or magical. Lost eyes are not restored.Cure deafness option: You cure deafness, whether it is natural or magical. Lost ears are not restored.Cure disease option: Cures all diseases (and kills all parasites) that the target is suffering from. Certain magical diseases may require you to beat the DC of the disease with your spellcasting check.Cure insanity option: Cures any insanity, natural or magical, that the target is suffering from.Medium restoration option: Restores all ability damage. Also restores ability drain to one ability score.Greater restoration option: Restores all ability damage and ability drain.Life force option: Restores any levels and/or AP drained recently (up to 1 day per skill level).     Spell:  Cure Fatigue - [Su, MR, AoO, Radiant]    Skill(s):  Divine - LifePsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)   Action Time:  6 AP (+0)3 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP per 5 SP   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+4)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)2 creatures (+2)3-4 creatures (+4)5-8 creatures (+6)9-16 creatures (+8)   Description:  You channel radiant energy into the target creature(s), using it to cure their fatigue. The base cost is 1 PP per 5 SP (same amount for each target).     Spell:  Curse - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - Retribution   Attack/Action Check:  Ranged: d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. WillTch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)F (divine implement)   Cost:  0 PP+1 PP per -1 action penalty+1 PP per -1 defense penalty+1 PP per -1 ability score decrease (to minimum 1)+2 PP for mark+3 PP for silence+4 P