pell envelops the target\'s body in a force field that provides an armor bonus to DR (without hindering movement at all).     Spell:  Force Field - [Su, MR, AoO, Force]    Skill(s):  Arcane - KinetomancyPsi - Metacreativity and Psychokinesis   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)M (100 sp of diamond dust per PP spent)   Cost:  1 PP for floating disk7 PP for force field+8 PP for telekinetic   Range:  Close (+0)Medium (+3)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  Disk, 1 sq diam (+0)Sphere, 1 sq rad (+0)Vertical wall, 4 x level squares (S; +2)Barred cage (cube; 4 sq side; +4)Closed cage (cube; 2 sq side; +4)   Description:  Floating disk: This version creates a floating, slightly concave disk of force that follows the caster at a height of 1 m and a distance of 1 square. It moves at a maximum speed of 12 squares per round. The disk can carry a maximum weight of 50 kg per skill level.Force field: This version creates a force field of the chosen shape. Unless otherwise specified, the field is immobile and invisible. No amount of physical force or damage can affect the field, but it can be bypassed with teleportation effects or dispelled.The force field can be created so that it intersects with solid, non-living matter, but it cannot be created within living creatures or be used to injure them.The barred cage consists of 1-cm wide bands and 1-cm wide gaps. Attacks through such a cage are only possible if they can pass through gaps of that size.   Options:  Telekinetic option: If the creatures and objects enclosed in the force field weigh 2500 kg or less, you can concentrate to move the field and its contents up to 6 squares per round (in any direction but only within the chosen range). If you cease concentrating when the field is unsupported, it falls at a slow rate of 12 squares per round.     Spell:  Force Missile - [Su, MR, AoO, Force]    Skill(s):  Arcane - KinetomancyPsi - PsychokinesisCleric Affinity - War Domain   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Dex mod + Ray Attack skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC (one attack per missile)   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for 1 missile+2 PP per add. missile   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  1+ missiles of force (+0)   Description:  You shoot one or more missiles of pure force at targets within range. Each missile that hits deals 2d4 HP of piercing or 2d4 SP of blunt damage (your choice).   Results:  S - The missile strikes the target and deals damage.ES - Halve target\'s DR against this attack.CS - The missile causes double damage.F - The missile misses and disappears.     Spell:  Forceful Hand - [Su, MR, AoO, Force]    Skill(s):  Arcane - KinetomancyCleric Affinity - Strength Domain   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  7 PP+2 PP for bull rush+4 PP for grappling+6 PP for striking fist+8 PP for crushing fist   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Concentration (+0)Encounter (D; +2)   Target/Area:  Hand of force (+0)   Description:  Creates a magical hand of force (Sz L; HP 3 per skill level; DeC 9; Fort, Ref, and Will same as caster; DR 10; never provokes AoO).In the basic spell, the hand automatically interposes itself between the caster and one designated opponent. It provides cover between those two individuals, and it halves the opponent\'s speed, if the opponent moves towards the caster and weighs below 1000 kg.Designating a new opponent is a redirection action.   Options:  Bull rush option: Once per round, the hand can make a bull rush attack (+15 vs. DeC) against the target.Grappling option: Once per round, the hand can initiate a grapple (+22 vs. DeC) or make a grapple attack (+27 attack; no damage).Striking fist option: Once per round, the hand can strike the opponent with a melee attack (+28 vs. DeC; 1d8 + 11 HP blunt damage; +20 attack vs. Fort to stun for 1 round).Crushing fist option: Once per round, the hand can initiate a grapple (+32 vs. DeC) or make a grapple attack (+37 attack; 2d6 + 12 HP blunt damage).     Spell:  Foresight - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - DivinationDivine - InsightPsi - Clairsentience   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  5 PP per offensive +15 PP per defensive +111 PP per reroll+4 PP for danger sense+8 PP for improved danger sense   Range:  Personal or Tch (+0)Close (+3)   Duration:  1 r (+0)Encounter (+2)1 h (+4)1 day (+6)1 month (+8)1 year (+10)Permanent (+12)   Target/Area:  You (+0)1 creature (+2)2 creatures (+4)3-4 creatures (+6)5-8 creatures (+8)9-16 creatures (+10)   Description:  This spell gives the target a rudimentary sixth sense or precognitive ability. This precognition means that you gain an insight bonus to attack rolls (offensive choice) and/or to DeC and Ref defenses (defensive choice). The reroll option means that one check (typically one that you fail or one that an enemy succeeds with) can be rerolled; note that any single check may only be rerolled once.   Options:  Danger sense option: The target gains 6 bonus skill levels in the Danger Sense skill.Improved danger sense option: The target cannot be surprised or flat-footed, and the bonus skill levels in Danger Sense increase from 6 to 12.     Spell:  Freedom - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - AbjurationDivine - ProtectionPsi - Psychometabolism and PsychoportationKi - Study of Water   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  3 PP+12 PP for greater freedom   Range:  Personal or Tch (+0)Close (+3)   Duration:  Instantaneous (existing effects only; +0)Encounter (+2)1 h (+4)1 day (+6)1 month (+8)1 year (+10)Permanent (+12)   Target/Area:  You (+0)1 creature (+2)2 creatures (+4)3-4 creatures (+6)5-8 creatures (+8)9-16 creatures (+10)   Description:  You make the target resistant to mundane or magical effects that restrict and slow. The target can move with full speed and freedom through water, mud, undergrowth, webs, and similar obstacles. It also gains a +10 bonus on any defense against grappling and entangling attacks, spells that slow movement or cause paralysis, and similar effects.Existing and active effects that slow or entangle are also terminated, if the effect\'s PL is beaten.   Options:  Greater freedom option: The target gains immunity (rather than a +10 bonus) against slowing and restricting effects. The immunity also extends to binding spells, petrification, stunning, and similar effects.     Spell:  Fusion - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Psi - Psychometabolism   Action Time:  1 r (+0)9 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  15 PP   Range:  Tch (+0)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)   Target/Area:  You and one willing creature (+0)   Description:  You physically join your body with that of another willing creature. This creature must be of the same size category and creature type as yourself. At the time of casting, you decide whether you or the other creature has control of your fused body. You also decide which equipment is worn and carried by the fused body (all other equipment is temporarily absorbed into the body).The fused body looks like a mix of you and the other creature. It has the sum of both creatures\' health points (HP, FP, and PP; current as well as maximum). Its ability scores, speed, attack forms, skill ranks, and levels will be the best from each creature.When the spell ends (or the body dies), the fused being separates, leaving the two bodies in adjacent squares. Damage to health points and ability scores are divided equally between the two bodies.     Spell:  Geas - [Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Lang, Charm]    Skill(s):  Arcane - EnchantmentDivine - Charm   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  10 min (+0)1 min (+4)1 r (+10)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  3 PP+8 PP for greater geas   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  Up to 1 week (D; +0)   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)   Description:  You place a magical command on the target creature, typically to carry out some service or refrain from some action. If the command is suicidal or nearly so, or if the creature\'s TL exceeds your skill level, the spell fails.If the target is prevented from carrying out the command or tries to avoid carrying it out, it takes 2 points of persistent ability damage per day to each ability score (to a minimum of 1). This damage disappears 24 hours after the creature resumes its task.   Options:  Greater geas option: In addition to the ability damage for disobeying the geas, the creature also takes 3d6 HP and 3d6 SP of damage per day and is constantly sickened.   Results:  S - The target creature is placed under a magical command.F - The target resists your geas.     Spell:  Genesis - [Su, AoO, Dimension]    Skill(s):  Arcane - Conjuration, Ouranomancy, and TransmutationDivine - Elements and SummoningPsi - Metacreativity and Psychoportation   Action Time:  1 week (33%; +0)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)1000 XP   Cost:  17 PP   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  Demiplane (+0)   Description:  This powerful spell creates a demiplane of finite size. If you cast the spell on one of the inner planes, you create a demiplane within the Ethereal Plane, and if you use it on an outer plane, the demiplane will take shape within the Astral Plane.When the spell is completed, the plane is very small (1 m diameter), but it starts to grow spontaneously, increasing 0.3 m in radius per day for 180 days. After that the rate of growth decreases to 0.3 m per week (approximately 15 m per year).You determine the plane\'s environment and characteristics as you cast the spell. For an ethereal demiplane this includes atmosphere, water, temperature, terrain features, etc, but it does not include precious materials nor buildings and other constructions. An astral demiplane is typically more dreamlike and spiritual in nature, and your decisions determine primarily how the plane is perceived by visitors.     Spell:  Ghost Sound - [Su, AoO, Illusion]    Skill(s):  Arcane - IllusionPsi - PsychokinesisBardic Music   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Int mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+2 PP for silence+2 PP for sound sculpting   Range:  Close (+0)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +8)1 month (D; +12)1 year (D; +14)Permanent (D; +16)   Target/Area:  Illusory sound within a 3 sq radius sphere (+0)Illusory sound in a 1 sq radius emanation centered on creature (+0)   Description:  You create the illusion of a sound, roughly limited in volume to four talking humans per skill level. For example, you can create the sound of talking, singing, shouting, walking, marching, running, roaring, squeaking, etc. Some variation in volume and basic character can be programmed at the time of casting.   Options:  Silence option: You deaden sounds in the area of effect, providing a -10 penalty on listen checks. Sonic attacks are not affected, but creatures in the area receive a +4 bonus against language-dependent attacks. Action checks with a verbal component suffer a -4 penalty.Sound sculpting option: You change a certain type of sound into a different sound. For example, you can change the sound of the wind into singing, or you can change all voices in the area into barking. If this affects someone\'s voice, action checks with a verbal component suffer a -4 penalty.   Results:  S - Target does not realize that the sound is an illusion.F - Target realizes that the sound is an illusion.     Spell:  Glyph of Warding - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - AbjurationDivine - Protection and Retribution   Action Time:  10 min (+0)1 min (+4)1 r (+8)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)M (5 gp of diamond dust per PP spent)   Cost:  3 PP+2 PP for concealment+6 PP for greater glyph+6 PP for pain glyph+6 PP for sleep glyph+8 PP for fear glyph+8 PP for persuasion glyph+10 PP for stun glyph+10 PP for weakness glyph+12 PP for death glyph+12 PP for insanity glyph   Range:  Tch (+0)   Duration:  Triggered (D; +0)Permanent (D; +8)   Target/Area:  1 glyph (+0)   Description:  You trace a clearly visible glyph on an object or surface. When a creature not designated by you at the time of casting interacts with the object (e.g. touches, reads, opens, walks over, etc), the glyph triggers. Optionally, you can designate a password that lets any creature interact with the trapped object without triggering the trap.Hiding or being invisible does not fool a glyph, but it will not be triggered by creatures on another plane. Also note that a glyph cannot be used offensively, by throwing a trapped object at an opponent, for instance.If the duration is permanent, the glyph can be triggered repeatedly (but requires 1 hour to recharge).Acid glyph (req Arcane - Hydromancy or Divine - Elements; [Acid]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of acid damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.Cold glyph (req Arcane - Hydromancy or Divine - Elements; [Cold]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of cold damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.Fire glyph (req Arcane - Pyromancy or Divine - Elements; [Fire]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of fire damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.Force glyph (req Arcane - Kinetomancy or Divine - Elements; [Force]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of blunt damage in a 2 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes full damage.Lightning glyph (req Arcane - Aeromancy or Divine - Elements; [Electric]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of electricity damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.Paralysis glyph (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm): +5 attack against Ref (S - the target is enclosed in a shimmering stasis field for up to 10 days (or until released by you)). A captured target is not aware, does not age, and needs no air, food, or drink, but it can still be injured by outside weapons and forces.Sonic glyph (req Arcane - Aeromancy or Divine - Elements; [Sonic]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of sonic damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.   Options:  Concealment option: The glyph is nearly invisible and hard to find by Perception (DC 15 + PL) or detection spells (opposed spellcasting check).Greater glyph option: The glyph makes a +10 attack and deals 12d6 HP of damage (instead of +5 and 6d6).Pain glyph option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Retribution): If a +10 attack against Fort succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst suffer wracking pains for 1 hour. This imposes a -4 penalty on all action checks.Sleep glyph option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm; [Mind, Sleep]): If a +10 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst fall into a catatonic slumber for 3d6ร10 minutes.Fear glyph option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm; [Mind, Fear]): If a +10 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst become panicked for 1 round per skill level.Persuasion glyph option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm; [Mind, Charm]): If a +10 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst become charmed by the caster for 1 hour per skill level.Stun glyph option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm): If a +12 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst become stunned for 1d6 rounds.Weakness glyph option (req Arcane - Necromancy or Divine - Death; [Necrotic]): If a +12 attack against Fort succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst suffer 3d6 points of Strength damage.Death glyph option (req Arcane - Necromancy or Divine - Death; [Necrotic]): If a +12 attack against Fort succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius die.Insanity glyph option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm; [Mind]): If a +12 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius become permanently insane.     Spell:  Heal Wounds - [Su, MR, AoO, Radiant]    Skill(s):  Divine - LifePsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)   Attack/Action Check:  (Ranged: d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. WillTch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC)   Action Time:  6 AP (+0)3 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP per 5 HP+6 PP for revivify+14 PP for regeneration   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  1 creature (+0)2 creatures (+2)3-4 creatures (+4)5-8 creatures (+6)9-16 creatures (+8)   Description:  You channel radiant energy into the target creature(s), using it to heal their wounds. The base cost is 1 PP per 5 HP of healing (same amount for each target).   Options:  Revivify option: If the target died due to HP damage during the previous two rounds, the healing still takes effect (potentially saving the target\'s life).Regeneration option: You restore missing body parts (limbs, eyes, ears, etc), destroyed organs, and crushed bones. This regeneration takes 2d10 rounds after completion of the spell.     Spell:  History Reading - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Psi - Clairsentience   Action Time:  1 h (+0)10 min (+4)1 min (+8)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP+2 PP for detection   Range:  Tch (+0)Close (+3)   Duration:  Concentration (+0)   Target/Area:  1 object (+0)Spherical spread, 6 sq rad (+2)   Description:  You try to sense psychic impressions from the target. This lets you learn about the significant events in the target object or area\'s history. The maximum temporal extent is 100 years per skill level, and for every 10 minutes you concentrate, you receive one vision from the target\'s past. The visions are shadowy and dreamlike, but they are generally detailed enough to reveal a creature\'s race, gender, and approximate age.   Options:  Detection option: This option lets active detection powers be used within your visions.     Spell:  Hold Creature - [Su, MR, AoO, Mind]    Skill(s):  Arcane - EnchantmentDivine - CharmPsi - Telepathy   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  3 PP   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Concentration (+0)Encounter (D; +2)1 h (D; +4)1 day (D; +6)1 month (D; +8)1 year (D; +10)Permanent (D; +12)   Target/Area:  1 person (+0)1 creature (+4)2 creatures (+6)3-4 creatures (+8)5-8 creatures (+10)9-16 creatures (+12)   Description:  You paralyze the target creature. It is still aware and able to breathe, but it cannot move, perform actions, or even speak. It is considered helpless.   Results:  S - The target is paralyzed.CS - The effect\'s duration increases by one step for free.F - The target is dazed for 1 round.OF - The target is unaffected.     Spell:  Hold Object - [Su, AoO]    Skill(s):  Arcane - KinetomancyPsi - Psychokinesis   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  1 PP for DC 15+1 PP for DC 20+2 PP for DC 25   Range:  Close (+0)Medium (+3)   Duration:  Encounter (D; +0)1 h (D; +2)1 day (D; +4)1 month (D; +6)1 year (D; +7)Permanent (D; +8)   Target/Area:  1 object (+0)   Description:  You immobilize any unattended object (including doors and gates) of up to huge size. Anyone other than you who tries to move or open the object has to make a Str check against the specified DC.     Spell:  Holy Smite - [Su, MR, AoO, Radiant/Necrotic]    Skill(s):  Divine - Retribution   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0), Silent (+2)S (+0), Still (+2)   Cost:  3 PP for 4d4 HP+2 PP per additional 1d4 HP   Range:  Medium (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  Spherical burst; 4 sq rad (+0), 6 sq rad (+4)   Description:  You punish your enemies with a blast of radiant or necrotic energy (depending on your patron deity\'s alignment). The blast deals +1 HP per die of damage against creatures opposed to your deity\'s alignment.   Results:  S - The blast deals the indicated amount of damage and blinds the target for 1 r.CS - The target takes double damage and is blinded for 1d4 r.F - The target takes only half damage (and is not blinded).CF - The target takes no damage.     Spell:  Holy Word - [Su, MR, AoO]    Skill(s):  Divine - Retribution   Attack/Action Check:  d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will   Action Time:  9 AP (+0)6 AP (+6)   Implements:  V (+0)   Cost:  13 PP+4 PP for banishment   Range:  0 (+0)   Duration:  Instantaneous (+0)   Target/Area:  8 sq radius spread (+0)   Description:  You utter a word of divine power. This has a detrimental effect on creatures whose alignment differs greatly from your deity\'s. Creatures within one step along both alignment axes suffer no ill effects. Other creatures suffer the following (cumulative) effects, depending on their TL:TL ','2013-01-26',512.11,'82c8af6a0f4aa9a05461238ff041c0e3',0,2),(83,2,'http://localhost/rold20/hb12a_equipment.php','RoL d20 - List of Equipment (Mundane Items)','','\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n	\r\n\r\n		\r\n	            \r\n	             \r\n	            \r\n	                 \r\n	                    RoL d20 Role-Playing System\r\n	                 \r\n	             \r\n			  \r\n		\r\n        \r\n			\r\n		 Handbook