 elemental is a being composed of one (or several) of the four classical elements: air, earth, fire, or water.  Immunity (racial) to critical hits Immunity (racial) to paralysis Immunity (racial) to poison Immunity (racial) to sleep attacks Immunity (racial) to drowning and suffocation    Humanoids  A humanoid usually has two arms, two legs, and one head, or at least a humanlike torso, arms, and a head. Humanoids have few or no supernatural or extraordinary abilities, but most can speak and usually have well-developed societies. They usually are of Small or Medium size.     Humanoids, Monstrous  A monstrous humanoid is a humanoid with supernatural or extraordinary abilities, or at least one of extraordinary size.     Outsiders  An outsider is at least partially composed of the essence (but not necessarily the material) of some plane other than the Material Plane. Some creatures start out as some other type and become outsiders when they attain a higher (or lower) state of spiritual existence.     Plants & Fungi  This type comprises vegetable creatures. Note that regular plants, such as those growing in gardens and fields, lack Wisdom and Charisma scores and are considered objects rather than creatures, even though they are classified as alive.  Life sense (6 sq) Blind (immune to illusions and gaze attacks) Immunity (racial) to critical hits Immunity (racial) to mind attacks Immunity (racial) to paralysis Immunity (racial) to poison Immunity (racial) to polymorph    Undead  Undead are once-living creatures animated by spiritual or supernatural forces.  Life sense (12 sq) Immunity (racial) to necrotic Immunity (racial) to ability damage Immunity (racial) to critical hits Immunity (racial) to disease Immunity (racial) to mind attacks Immunity (racial) to paralysis Immunity (racial) to poison Immunity (racial) to drowning and suffocation        \r\n\r\n     \r\n     Living creatures:  All creatures except constructs and undead.\r\n     Persons:  Bipedal creatures belong