INSERT INTO `actions` VALUES (1,'Move',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'1 MP (x2 for obstructed terrain, x2 for moving defensively - no AoO)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Move 1 sq.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(2,'Crawl',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'2 MP (x2 for obstructed terrain)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Crawl 1 sq.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(3,'Walk',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'Full round',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can walk a number of squares equal to your adjusted speed.\\nObstructed squares count double.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(4,'Jog',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'Full round',NULL,NULL,'1 SP',NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can jog a number of squares equal to 2 times your adjusted speed.\\nObstructed squares count double.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(5,'Run',2,'[Untrained, Move]',NULL,'Full round',NULL,'C','2 SP',NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can run a number of squares equal to 3 times your adjusted speed.\\nReduce your normal maneuverability by one step.\\nYou cannot run through obstructed squares, and while running, you can only use passive DeC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(6,'Sprint',2,'[Untrained, Move]',NULL,'Full round',NULL,'C','4 SP',NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can sprint a number of squares equal to 4 times your adjusted speed.\\nReduce your normal maneuverability by two steps.\\nYou cannot sprint through obstructed squares, and while sprinting, you can only use passive DeC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(7,'Stand Up',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'4 MP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You stand up from prone.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(8,'Drop Prone',2,'[Untrained, Move]',NULL,'1 MP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You lie down on the ground.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(9,'Melee Attack',3,'[Untrained]','d20! + Str or Dex mod + size mod + weapon skill + skill mod + PAM + other mods vs. DeC','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, melee weapon','1 SP','Weapon\'s reach',NULL,'1 target','You make a normal attack with a melee weapon against an opponent within reach.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.','S - You deal normal damage.\\nES - Halve DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier.\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon (no effect for natural weapons).\\nCF - The defender can try to deflect your attack back on you or against another target adjacent to you both. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon with a -4 penalty.',NULL,NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(10,'Melee Disarm',3,'[Untrained]','Melee attack roll vs. DeC + target weapon\'s size mod','8 + your weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, melee weapon','1 SP','Weapon\'s reach',NULL,'1 target','You try to knock your opponent\'s weapon, shield, wand, or other exposed item out of his hands.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender. If this attack of opportunity causes damage, the disarm automatically fails.','S - You hit the weapon, and the defender has to make a Str or Dex check against (5 + damage). If this check fails, the weapon or item is dropped (for every 5 levels of failure, it lands 1 sq further away). If you are doing the disarm with a hand (or other natural weapon with a grip), you can instead choose to grab the weapon or item for yourself.\\nF - The disarm fails.\\nEF - The defender manages to disarm you instead.',NULL,'Attacking weapon is larger than target item: +4 per size category\\nAttacking weapon is smaller than target item: -4 per size category\\nTarget item is exposed but not a melee weapon: +4\\nTarget item is semi-exposed (e.g. necklace, helmet, weapon in scabbard): -4\\nTarget item is held in locked gauntlet or hard to reach or grab (e.g. ring): -10\\nDefender is pinned by attacker: +4','+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(11,'Melee Sunder',3,'[Untrained]','Melee attack roll vs. DeC + target item\'s size mod','8 + your weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, melee weapon','1 SP','Weapon\'s reach',NULL,'1 target','You try to damage or destroy an opponent\'s weapon, shield, or other object. This action does not work against worn armor.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.\\nAlthough there are usually no special effects caused by striking specific body parts, it is possible to do so with this action.','S - You deal normal damage against the object.\\nES - Halve the item\'s DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage to the object according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier. Note, however, that most objects are resistant or immune to critical hits. Also, you deal normal (non-critical) damage to the object\'s wielder.\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon (no effect for natural weapons).\\nCF - The defender can try to deflect your attack back on you or against another target adjacent to you both. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon.',NULL,'Attacking weapon is larger than target item: +4 per size category\\nAttacking weapon is smaller than target item: -4 per size category','+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(12,'Melee Trip',3,'[Untrained]','Melee attack roll vs. DeC\\nThen d20! + Str mod vs. d20! + Str or Dex mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, melee weapon','1 SP','Weapon\'s reach',NULL,'1 target','You can attempt to trip an opponent with a natural weapon or with certain melee weapons.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.\\nIf the attack roll succeeds, you make a Strength check opposed by the target\'s Strength or Dexterity check.\\nTrip will only work against creatures within one size category of the attacker.\\nIf a flying creature is tripped, it starts falling (as if unable to maintain minimum forward speed).\\nTrip can also be used to unhorse a mounted opponent. A Ride check can be made in place of the defender\'s Str/Dex check.','If the weapon attack hits, the secondary attack has the following effects:\\nS - The target is knocked prone. For every 5 levels of success, you can choose to move (or actually throw) the opponent one square away, causing damage as if the opponent had fallen the same distance.\\nF - You fail.\\nEF - The target manages to trip you instead.',NULL,'The following modifiers do not apply to the melee attack but to the Str check:\\nTarget is smaller than you: +4\\nTarget is larger than you: -4\\nTarget has more than two legs: -4\\nTarget has Acrobatics skill: -1 syn per 5 lvls','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(13,'Ranged Attack',4,'[Untrained]','d20! + Dex mod + size mod + range mod + weapon skill + skill mod + PAM + other mods vs. DeC','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You make a normal attack with a ranged weapon against an opponent within range.','S - You deal normal damage.\\nES - Halve DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier.\\nF - You miss. To find out where the weapon lands, roll 1d8 to determine a direction away from the target square, and determine distance by multiplying the weapon\'s base range by d% percent.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon.\\nCF - The defender can try to deflect your attack against another target adjacent to himself and within your line of effect. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon with a -8 penalty.',NULL,'Target is adjacent to ally: -4','+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(14,'Ranged Disarm',4,'[Untrained]','Ranged attack roll vs. DeC + weapon\'s size mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You try to knock your opponent\'s weapon, shield, wand, or other exposed item out of his hands.','S - You hit the weapon, and the defender has to make a Str or Dex check against (5 + damage). If this check fails, the weapon or item is dropped (for every 5 levels of failure, it lands 1 sq further away).\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon.',NULL,'The following modifiers do not apply to the melee attack but to the defender\'s Str check:\\nTarget item is larger than Medium: +4 per size category\\nTarget item is smaller than Medium: -4 per size category\\nTarget item is exposed but not a melee weapon: -4\\nTarget item is semi-exposed (e.g. necklace, helmet, weapon in scabbard): +4\\nTarget item is held in locked gauntlet or hard to reach or grab (e.g. ring): +10','+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(15,'Ranged Sunder',4,'[Untrained]','Ranged attack roll vs. DeC + item\'s size mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You try to damage or destroy an opponent\'s weapon, shield, or other object. This action does not work against worn armor.','S - You deal normal damage against the object.\\nES - Halve the item\'s DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage to the object according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier. Note, however, that most objects are resistant or immune to critical hits. Also, you deal normal (non-critical) damage to the object\'s wielder.\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon.',NULL,'Target item is larger than Medium: -4 per size category\\nTarget item is smaller than Medium: +4 per size category','+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(16,'Ranged Trip',4,'[Untrained]','Ranged attack roll vs. DeC\\nThen d20! + Str mod vs. d20! + Str or Dex mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You can attempt to trip an opponent with certain ranged weapons, such as bolas and lariats.\\nIf the attack roll succeeds, you make a Strength check opposed by the target\'s Strength or Dexterity check.\\nTrip will only work against creatures within one size category of the attacker.\\nIf a flying creature is tripped, it starts falling (as if unable to maintain minimum forward speed).\\nTrip can also be used to unhorse a mounted opponent. A Ride check can be made in place of the defender\'s Str/Dex check.','If the weapon attack hits, the secondary attack has the following effects:\\nS - The target is knocked prone.\\nF - You fail to trip the opponent.',NULL,'The following modifiers do not apply to the ranged attack but to the Str check:\\nTarget is smaller than you: +4\\nTarget is larger than you: -4\\nTarget has more than two legs: -4\\nTarget has Acrobatics skill: -1 syn per 5 lvls','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(17,'Splash Attack',4,'[Untrained]','d20! + Dex mod + size mod + range mod + (Weapons - Area Attacks skill) + PAM + other mods vs. DeC','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, ranged splash weapon','1 SP','Per weapon (default 2)',NULL,'Per weapon (default 1 sq radius sphere)','You throw a splash weapon at a creature or a square.','S - You deal normal damage to the target.\\nF - You miss. To find out where the weapon lands, roll 1d8 to determine a direction away from the target square, and determine distance by multiplying the weapon\'s base range by d% percent.\\nRegardless of success, roll separate attack rolls (according to the weapon; default +4) against the Ref of creatures in the splash area.',NULL,'Primary target is adjacent to ally: -4','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(18,'Spray Attack',4,'[Untrained]','d20! + Dex mod + size mod + (Weapons - Area Attacks skill) + PAM + other mods vs. Ref','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, spray weapon','1 SP','0',NULL,'Per weapon (default 1 sq conical burst)','You use a spray weapon against one or more opponents within range. Even throwing sand or flour can be considered a spray attack.','S - You deal normal damage.\\nF - You typically deal half normal damage (depending on the weapon).\\nCF - You deal normal damage to yourself.',NULL,'Target is adjacent to ally: -4','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(19,'Bull Rush',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20! + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM vs. opposed d20! + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C','1 SP','Rch',NULL,'1 or more targets','You try to rush an opponent and push him back.\\nYou first move into your target\'s square (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move). You then try to push the target out of the square with an opposed Strength check.\\nYou can only Bull Rush opponents that are within two size categories of yourself.','S - The target is pushed back one square (away from your direction of movement). For every 5 levels of success, you can push back the opponent one more square, but you have to move with him and pay 1 additional AP per square moved. Both you and the target provoke attacks of opportunity for this move.\\nF - You are pushed back into the last square you occupied before the attack.','','Target has more than two legs: -4\\nBull rush with charge: +2\\nEach additional target after the first: -4 (cumulative)','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(20,'Crush',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20! + Str mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM vs. Ref','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C','1 SP','Rch',NULL,'Your spacing','You try to crush opponents under your own body.\\nYou first move or jump into the targeted area (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move) and fall prone. By doing this, you try to pin and crush the target(s) under your own body.\\nYou can only Crush opponents that are two or more size categories smaller than yourself, since larger creatures can push you out of their square.','S - You crush the target under your body, causing blunt damage according to your size (Tiny 1d4 B, Small 1d6 B, Medium 1d8 B, Large 2d6 B, Huge 3d6 B, Gargantuan 4d6 B, Colossal 5d6 B; add Str mod to the damage).\\nAffected targets are considered grappled until they escape, you move, or you stand up from prone.\\nF - The target moves out of your way (for free) into any adjacent square.',NULL,'Crush with charge: +2','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(21,'Overrun',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20! + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM vs. opposed d20! + Str or Dex mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C','1 SP','Rch',NULL,'1 or more targets','You try to rush your opponent and knock him prone.\\nYou first move into your target\'s square (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move).\\nYour opponent can simply choose to avoid you, and in that case, you continue your move out of the square (and action time is reduced by 4 AP).\\nIf your opponent tries to block, you make the opposed check shown above.\\nIf your spacing would allow you to overrun multiple targets, you can compare your action check against each potential target\'s opposed check (with the appropriate modifiers).','S - The defender is knocked prone, and you can choose to continue your movement.\\nIf the target is smaller than you, you can make a free leg attack against it.\\nF - You are pushed back into the previous square.\\nEF - You are pushed back into the previous square and knocked prone.',NULL,'Target has more than two legs: -4\\nOverrun with charge: +2\\nEach additional target after the first: -4 (cumulative)','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(22,'Initiate Grapple',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20! + Dex mod + size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM vs. DeC','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C, primary attack(s)','1 SP','Rch',NULL,'1 target','To start a grapple, first make the indicated action check against your opponent. If the attack of opportunity causes damage, the grapple automatically fails. If the target is already grappling with someone else, this check is automatically successful.\\nIf you successfully initiate a grapple with a target two or more size categories larger than you, you are holding onto the target, but the target is not considered grappled (unless it chooses to be).','S - You are now grabbing (but not grappling) the target. Next, make a free grapple attack (see Grapple Attack action). If this attack succeeds, you deal normal grapple damage to the target, move into the target\'s square, and are now grappling with the target. This move provokes attacks of opportunity from opponents other than the target.\\nAs an alternative to dealing damage, the attacker can choose among the other effects listed under the grapple attack action (except pin).\\nIf the free grapple attack fails, the grapple is not successfully initiated.\\nF - You lose the grab and fail to initiate the grapple.',NULL,'More free primary natural attacks than opponent: +4\\nUsing a single primary attack form: -20 (the attacker is not considered grappled; this also means that the attacker can move normally, carrying along all grapplers)','+1 attack bonus per AP',1),(23,'Grapple Attack',5,'[Untrained]','d20! + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill) + PAM vs. opposed grapple attack check','6 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)',NULL,'C','1 SP','Rch',NULL,'1 grappling target','While grappling, you can use grapple attacks to inflict damage or control your opponent in different ways.\\nGrapple attacks can only be made after a grapple has been initiated, but they can be made by anyone involved in the grappling.','S - The grapple attack inflicts the same damage as an unarmed attack made by the attacker. To be more specific, this attack can involve an elbow to the face, a claw attack, bending the opponent\'s joints, crushing him with a bear hug, etc. Use the damage modifier either from Weapons - Generic, Weapons - Brawling, or Weapons - Natural, whichever is higher.\\nAlternatively, a successful check can be used to achieve one of the following results:\\n- Draw a light weapon, material component, or other accessible item.\\n- Use a light weapon (already drawn) to deal damage to another grappler as if using a melee attack.\\n- Escape from the grapple and move into an adjacent space. Your check has to beat all opposing grapplers for it to be successful.\\n- Move all grapplers (including yourself) one or two squares. Your check has to beat all opposing grapplers for it to be successful.\\n- Pin another grappler for 1 round. You can only pin one opponent at a time.\\n- Break another grappler\'s pin.\\n- Knock another grappler prone.\\n- Use a light weapon held by another grappler to attack him or another grappler. This first requires a successful grapple check and then a melee attack roll with a -4 attack penalty.\\n\\nOnce you have an opponent pinned, further successful checks can also be used to achieve these results:\\n- Throw the pinned opponent into an adjacent square (if no other grappler is also grappling the same opponent). For every 5 levels of success, you can throw the opponent one square further away, causing damage as if the opponent had fallen the same distance. The thrown opponent is no longer pinned or grappled.\\n- Try to incapacitate the pinned opponent, causing twice the normal grappling damage in SP.\\n- Prevent the pinned opponent from speaking (and using verbal components) until the pin ends.\\n- The pinned opponent can be used as an improvised weapon or shield against non-grappling opponents until the pin ends.\\n- If you have a mouth and are four or more size categories larger than the pinned opponent (or have an improved swallow ability), you can swallow the opponent. This automatically causes bite damage. The opponent is considered grappled even after being swallowed, but the swallower is no longer grappled.\\n- If you have a rope readily available, two consecutive successful checks allow you to tie up two of the pinned opponent\'s limbs (as a free Use Rope action).\\n\\nF - You inflict no damage.',NULL,'More free primary natural attacks than opponent: +4\\nUsing a single primary attack form: -20 (the attacker is not considered grappled)','+1 attack bonus per AP\\n+1 damage bonus per AP',1),(24,'Charge Attack',6,'[Untrained, AoO]','As per attack','As per attack + 1 MP per sq moved',NULL,'C, as per attack','2 SP','As per attack',NULL,'1 target','You move two or more squares directly towards an opponent in line of sight and then make a melee attack with a +2 damage bonus or a brawling attack with a +2 attack bonus. A charge with a melee attack can also be a melee disarm, melee sunder, melee trip, or even an akimbo attack.\\nThe movement provokes attacks of opportunity normally, but the attack itself does not.\\nYou must have a clear path across easy terrain for your movement, but please note that Maintain Balance and Jumping actions can be used to allow charging over some types of difficult terrain. The attack must be aimed in the same direction as the move (+/-45 degrees).\\nThe attack must be made with primary attack forms (or with weapons held in primary attack forms).\\nDuring and after a charge, you suffer a -2 DeC penalty (per charge, if multiple charge attacks are made in the same round) until the start of your next turn.\\nSome weapons deal double damage when used in a charge attack and your adjusted speed is 10 or better.\\nSome weapons deal double damage when readied against a charge.\\nCharging can be done with any mode of movement that allows running or sprinting. A flying charge is usually performed as a dive.\\nThe Jump and Dodging actions can also be used as part of a charge attack.','As per attack.',NULL,NULL,'As per attack.',1),(25,'Akimbo Attack',6,'[Untrained]','Two or more separate weapon attack checks','Var',NULL,'C, as per attacks','1 SP','As per attacks',NULL,'1 or more targets','You make two or more attacks simultaneously. The maximum number of simultaneous attacks is equal to the number of attack forms or weapons you have. The maximum number of attacks is also limited by your skill levels in the appropriate Weapons skill(s). Each attack carries an attack penalty, but this penalty can be reduced with skill levels in Fighting Style - Akimbo.\\nThe total AP cost is the sum of the AP cost of each attack, but with a reduction based on the number of attacks.\\nThe AP reduction and base modifier is...\\nDouble attack: -2 / -6\\nTriple attack: -4 / -8\\nQuadruple attack: -6 / -10\\nQuintuple attack: -9 / -12\\nSextuple attack: -12 / -14\\nSeptuple attack: -16 / -16','As per attacks.',NULL,'Attack with natural weapon: Penalty for that attack reduced by 4\\nAttack with light weapon: Penalty reduced by 2\\nAttack with two-handed weapon: Penalty increased by 4\\nAll attacks against the same opponent: Penalty for all attacks reduced by 2\\nNote that the reduced penalties can never turn the penalty into a bonus.','As per attacks.',1),(26,'Melee Coup de Grace',3,'[Untrained, AoO]','Melee attack roll + 20 vs. DeC','12 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 9 AP)',NULL,'C, weapon','1 SP','1 sq',NULL,'1 helpless target','You use a melee weapon to deliver a coup de grace against a helpless defender.','As per attack. If the attack results in a critical hit, the attacker can make a secondary attack of (d20! + damage dealt) vs. Fort defense (S - defender takes an additional 100 HP of damage).',NULL,NULL,'As per attack.',1),(27,'Ranged Coup de Grace',4,'[Untrained, AoO]','Ranged attack roll + 20 vs. DeC','12 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 9 AP)',NULL,'C, weapon','1 SP','1 sq',NULL,'1 helpless target','You use a projectile weapon to deliver a coup de grace against a helpless defender.','As per attack. If the attack results in a critical hit, the attacker can make a secondary attack of (d20! + damage dealt) vs. Fort defense (S - defender takes an additional 100 HP of damage).',NULL,NULL,'As per attack.',1),(28,'Cast Spell',7,'[Su, AoO, Boost, T10]','(d20! + Arcane/Divine/Psi skill + ability mod - total PP cost + MAM)','Var',NULL,'C + var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','+1 casting check bonus and PL per AP\\n-1 casting check penalty and PL per AP\\nFor single-target damage spell: +1 damage bonus per AP',1),(29,'Counterspell',7,'[Su, AoO, T10]','d20! + Arcane/Divine/Psi skill + ability mod + MAM + PP spent vs. spellcasting check','Reaction or 6 AP','You see a spellcaster start to cast a spell or concentrating on an ongoing spell.','C, V, S','0+ PP','Long (LoS; see modifiers)','Instantaneous','1 spellcasting target','You try to interrupt the target\'s spellcasting by using the same skill.\\nYou use this action by first spending a reaction on a Spellcraft action to identify the spell being cast. If you successfully identify the spell, and you know the same spell or are trained in the same skill that the caster is using to cast the spell, you can spend another reaction to make a simple opposed skill check against the caster spellcasting check. You may spend any amount of PP (up to your skill level) and add them to your check.\\nA different kind of counterspelling can be used to co-opt an existing spell that someone else is maintaining through concentration. Note that this is an active action and not a reaction. First, you perform an active Spellcraft (Identify Supernatural Effect) action, with a concentrating spellcaster as the target. If you successfully identify the spell, and you know the same spell or are trained in the same skill that the caster used to cast the spell, you can make a simple opposed skill check against the caster\'s spellcasting check. You may spend any amount of PP (up to your skill level) and add them to your check. If you win the opposed check, you co-opt the spell and can control it for as long as you maintain concentration.','S - You interrupt the target\'s spellcasting.\\nCS - You can redirect the spell against a new target (including the caster).\\nF - Your counterspelling fails.',NULL,'Short range: +0\\nMedium range: -4\\nLong range: -8\\nCounterspelling with the right skill but without knowing the spell: -2\\nSpellcraft synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls','+1 action check bonus per AP',1),(30,'Draw Weapon',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'2 AP',NULL,'Hand(s)',NULL,'Tch',NULL,NULL,'You can draw a maximum of one weapon per available hand. The same action is used to draw other items that are kept easily accessible, such as wands, potions, etc.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(31,'Sheathe Weapon',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'2 AP',NULL,'Hand(s)',NULL,'Tch',NULL,NULL,'You can sheathe a maximum of one weapon per available hand. The same action can be used to sheathe other items, such as wands, potions, etc.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(32,'Ready Shield',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'4 AP',NULL,'Hand(s)',NULL,'Tch',NULL,NULL,'You either grasp and ready a shield or loosen and stow it.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(33,'Stow Equipment',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'Half round',NULL,'Hand(s)',NULL,'Tch',NULL,NULL,'You either retrieve an item from a backpack or other worn container or store an item in such a container.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(34,'Pick up Item',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'4 AP',NULL,'Hand(s)',NULL,'Tch',NULL,NULL,'You pick up an item from the ground.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(35,'Drop Item',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'0 AP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You drop an item.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(36,'Learn Spell',7,'[T10/20]','d20! + Arcane/Divine/Psi skill + ability mod vs. 20 + (spell\'s or variation\'s minimum PP cost)','1 day (50% time)',NULL,'C',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'One spell/power/variation','You try to learn a new spell, power, or spell/power variation.\\nYour skill level in all the mandatory skills must be at least equal to the spell\'s or variation\'s minimum PP cost. You use your highest mandatory skill level as a bonus on the learning check.','S - You learn the spell (with