,'1 week (50% time)',NULL,'C, (tools)','Special','Personal',NULL,'You','You use your skill to craft and then sell items.','If you are in a location where you can perform your skill and sell the products created, you earn half the check result in silver pieces.',NULL,'Untrained use: -5 circ\\nImprovised tools: -2 circ\\nMasterwork tools: +2 circ',NULL,NULL),(56,'Forge Document',10,'[Untrained, Secret]','d20! + Crafting (Calligraphy) skill + Int mod vs. opposing Perception','1d4 min per page',NULL,'C, writing materials',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'One document','You try to forge a document.','S - You make a forgery that fools the reader.\\nF - The reader recognizes your document as a forgery.',NULL,'Generic documents: +8\\nForging a signature: +4\\nThe reader gets the following modifiers...\\nType of document unknown: -2\\nType of document well known: +2\\nHandwriting not known: -2\\nHandwriting well known: +2\\nCasual review: -2',NULL,NULL),(57,'Repair Item',1,'[Untrained, T10/20]','d20! + Crafting skill + Int mod vs. DC','Var',NULL,'C, tools','1/3 of listed price','Tch','Instantaneous','One or more objects','You use this skill to repair one or more (non-magical) objects.','Every day you make a successful skill check, you produce a number of \"virtual\" sp equal to your skill check. When the sum reaches half the object\'s listed price, the repair is finished.\\nIf you fail a check by 5 or more, 10% of the raw materials have been destroyed, increasing the cost accordingly.','Very simple item (<1 sp): 5\\nCommon item (1-10 sp): 10\\nHigh-quality item (11-100 sp): 15\\nComplex item (101-1000 sp): 20\\nVery complex item (1000+ sp): 25','Untrained use: -5 circ\\nImprovised tools: -2 circ\\nMasterwork tools: +2 circ',NULL,NULL),(58,'Autopsy',1,'[Untrained, T10/20, Secret]','d20! + Healing skill + Wis mod vs. DC','10 min',NULL,'C, hands',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'1 corpse','You investigate a corpse and try to determine the cause of death.','S - You are able to determine the approximate cause o