INSERT INTO `skills` VALUES (1,'Acrobatics','Acrob',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Acrobatics is a skill that covers physical actions governed more by balance and agility than by brute strength. The more strength-based actions are covered by Athletics.'),(2,'Animal Empathy','AnEmp',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Animal Empathy is a skill that you use to interact with domesticated as well as wild animals. It can be used to improve their attitude towards you, get them to do as you want, or even turn wild animals into domesticated ones.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Druid and Ranger classes.'),(3,'Athletics','Athle',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Athletics is a skill that covers physical actions governed more by strength than by agility. The more agility-based actions are covered by Acrobatics.'),(4,'Crafting','Craft',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Crafting is a combination of all the skills used to create and repair stuff, from cutting gems to building ships. Realistically, there should be a separate skill for each craft, but they have been combined into a single skill for the sake of simplicity (and to make the skill more attractive for player characters).'),(5,'Healing','Heal',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Healing is a skill that covers most knowledge related to medicine, anatomy, pharmacology, toxicology, pathology, etc. Whether the actions related to this skill involve traditional medicine, acupuncture, massage, or something more exotic depends on the campaign.'),(6,'Knowledge','Know',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Knowledge is a combination of several areas of academic study and lore. Knowledge that is used for practical rather than academic purposes belongs to the Crafting, Profession, or even Survival skills. Realistically, there should be a separate skill for each type of knowledge, but they have been combined into a single skill for the sake of simplicity (and to make the skill more attractive for player characters).'),(7,'Linguistics','Lingu',1,3,NULL,NULL,'Linguistics is a measure of how many languages you speak, and it also represents a general academic knowledge of languages and alphabets. Realistically, there should be a separate skill for each language, but they have been combined into a single skill for the sake of simplicity (and to make the skill more attractive for player characters).\\nThe first time you specialize in a language, you learn its alphabet and its basics. The second time, you become nearly fluent. The third time, you learn to speak the language with little or no accent. This is one of very few skills where you can spend more than one skill point per specialization.'),(8,'Perception','Percp',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Perception is the skill you use to find hidden things, hear sneaking enemies, spot an ambush, etc.'),(9,'Perform','Perfm',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Perform is a combination of several types of artistic expression. Realistically, there should be a separate skill for each type of art, but they have been combined into a single skill for the sake of simplicity (and to make the skill more attractive for player characters).'),(10,'Profession','Prof',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Profession is a combination of several different occupational skills. Realistically, there should be a separate skill for each type of occupation, but they have been combined into a single skill for the sake of simplicity (and to make the skill more attractive for player characters). There are several similarities (and probably overlaps) between the Profession and Crafting skills, but generally speaking, Profession specialties are broader and much less focused on creating and repairing things.'),(11,'Psychology','Psych',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Psychology is a skill that can be used to actively influence other people in various ways. It can also be used more passively, to analyze the behavior of others.'),(12,'Riding','Ride',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Riding represents the ability to ride and take care of any type of mount, including those that are aerial or aquatic. A mount must be at least one size category larger than the rider, and it has to be either trained or willing to carry a rider. Some mounts are also trained for combat, although natural predators do not require such training.'),(13,'Composure','Compo',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Composure is a skill that improves your mental discipline, offering some protection against mental attacks, magical as well as mundane detections, et.al.'),(14,'Stealth','Steal',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stealth is a skill that you use to avoid detection, by hiding, sneaking, or just being inconspicuous.'),(15,'Survival','Surv',1,1,NULL,NULL,'Survival is a skill that covers most of the expertise necessary to survive in a wilderness setting, including how to find food, find water, avoid getting lost, etc.'),(16,'Thievery','Thiev',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thievery is a skill that covers most dexterity-based subterfuge actions, such as opening a lock, escaping manacles, picking a pocket, circumventing a trap, etc.'),(17,'Weapons - Natural','WpNat',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Natural is the skill used for all natural weapons, including hands, feet, claws, teeth, tails, etc.'),(18,'Weapons - Brawling','WpBrl',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Brawling is used when you are grappling or tackling your opponents.\\nNote that although natural weapons are often used when making grapple attacks, this skill is used in place of Weapons - Natural to calculate the bonuses while grappling.'),(19,'Weapons - Generic','WpGen',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Generic is a skill that gives you basic proficiency with most weapons, from axes and swords to crossbows and slings. The bonuses granted by this skill can be used for all weapons belonging to the generic group, and they can also be used in place of Weapons - Brawling skill modifiers and Weapons - Ray skill modifiers.'),(20,'Weapons - Exotic','WpExo',2,1,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Exotic is a skill that makes you more proficient in fighting with certain exotic weapons. It also makes you more capable when fighting with improvised weapons.'),(21,'Weapons - Axes','WpAxe',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Axes is a skill that turns you into an expert axe fighter.'),(22,'Weapons - Clubs','WpClb',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Clubs makes you better at attacking with clubs, maces, and other clubbing weapons.'),(23,'Weapons - Fencing','WpFnc',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Fencing is the skill used for all fencing weapons (usually blades that rely more on precise attacks than on brute force).'),(24,'Weapons - Flails','WpFll',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Flails is the skill you use when fighting with the flail type of weapons.'),(25,'Weapons - Heavy Blades','WpHvB',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Heavy Blades is the skill used for large swords and other similar weapons.'),(26,'Weapons - Light Blades','WpLtB',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Light Blades is the skill used for all small swords, daggers, knives, and other small blades.'),(27,'Weapons - Pole Arms','WpPlA',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Pole Arms makes you more proficient in fighting with pole arm weapons.'),(28,'Weapons - Shields','WpShd',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Shields is a skill that improves your ability to fight and defend yourself with a shield.'),(29,'Weapons - Spears','WpSpr',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Spears is the skill used for fighting with spears, lances, and other similar weapons.'),(30,'Weapons - Staves','WpStv',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Staves makes you more proficient in fighting with staves and other similar weapons.'),(31,'Weapons - Bows','WpBow',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Bows is the skill you use to fire any type of bow.'),(32,'Weapons - Crossbows','WpCrs',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Crossbows is the skill you use to load and fire crossbows.'),(33,'Weapons - Firearms','WpFir',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Firearms is the skill you use to load and fire gunpowder weapons.'),(34,'Weapons - Slings','WpSln',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Slings is the skill you use with sling-type weapons.'),(35,'Weapons - Small Thrown','WpSmT',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Small Thrown makes you more proficient in throwing daggers, shurikens, darts, and similar small weapons.'),(36,'Weapons - Area Attacks','WpAre',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Area Attacks is a skill that improves your attack proficiency with bursts, spreads, emanations and other attacks that cover a large physical area and normally target a victim\'s Reflex defense.'),(37,'Weapons - Body & Mind Attacks','WpBaM',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Body & Mind Attacks makes you more proficient in any attacks that target the victim\'s Fortitude and Will defenses.'),(38,'Weapons - Ray Attacks','WpRay',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Ray Attacks is the skill you use with any spell, device, or power that fires a ray (typically against DeC).'),(39,'Weapons - Siege','WpSie',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Weapons - Siege is the skill you use to load and fire siege weapons.'),(40,'Armor - Light','ArmLt',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Armor - Light is a skill that teaches you how to effectively wear and move in light armor.'),(41,'Armor - Medium','ArmMd',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Armor - Medium is a skill that teaches you how to effectively wear and move in armor of medium weight and rigidity.'),(42,'Armor - Heavy','ArmHv',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Armor - Heavy is a skill that teaches you how to effectively wear heavy and rigid suits of armor.'),(43,'Berserking','Bersk',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Berserking is a skill that lets you enter a blood frenzy, temporarily increasing your physical strength and resilience.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Barbarian class.'),(44,'Combat Instincts','CmbIn',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Combat Instincts is a skill that reflects your amount of combat experience and how quickly you respond in combat situations.'),(45,'Damage Reduction','DmRed',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Damage reduction is a skill that gradually gives you improved pain tolerance and resistance to physical damage.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Barbarian class.'),(46,'Danger Sense','DaSns',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Danger Sense is a combination of instinctive reflexes and a suspicious personality.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Barbarian and Rogue classes.'),(47,'Defensive Stance','DefSt',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Defensive Stance is a skill that can turn you into a veritable bastion of defense, increasing your strength, resilience, and defenses as long as you remain in the same spot.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Dwarven Defender prestige class.'),(48,'Enemy Specialization','EnSpc',3,1,NULL,NULL,'Enemy Specialization is a skill that teaches you the strengths and weaknesses of particular creature types.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Ranger class.'),(49,'Fighting Style - Akimbo','FSMul',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fighting Style - Akimbo teaches you how to wield multiple weapons and make multiple attacks simultaneously. The Akimbo Attack action shows the maximum number of simultaneous attacks you can perform and the base penalty on each attack. Note that in order to perform a \"double attack\", you also need to wield two weapons (or a double weapon), three weapons for a \"triple attack\", etc. For most humanoids, this means that anything beyond a \"double attack\" has to involve natural weapons. For example, a very skilled human wielding two daggers could perform up to a \"quintuple attack\" by using both daggers in combination with a double kick and a head-butt.'),(50,'Fighting Style - Mobility','FSMob',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fighting Style - Mobility is a skill that teaches different ways to stay mobile on a battlefield and to quickly switch between multiple opponents.'),(51,'Sniping','Snipe',10,NULL,'Skl(WpBow)>=5 AND Skl(VitAt)>=5','MIN(Skl(WpBow)-5,Skl(VitAt)-5)','Sniping is a skill that teaches you how to make stealthy and deadly ranged attacks. This skill is extremely difficult to learn and typically requires being taught by one who has already mastered it. It is practiced by elves and half-elves, but other cultures specializing in stealth and ranged weapons may also use it (and possibly with other weapons than bows).\\nInspired by the Midnight Elven Raider prestige class.'),(52,'Vital Attack','VitAt',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Vital Attack is the ability to strike the most vulnerable and sensitive spots on your enemies. Note that creatures that have no vital organs, such as most undead, constructs, and others, are resistant to critical hits and indirectly also to vital attacks.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Rogue class.'),(53,'Warfare','Warfr',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Warfare is a skill that teaches you strategy, army tactics, leadership, and science related to mass combat.'),(54,'Arcane - Abjuration','ArcAb',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Abjuration is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to protection, resistance, wards, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(55,'Arcane - Aeromancy','ArcAe',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Aeromancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to air, gas, wind, lightning, electricity, and sonic energy. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(56,'Arcane - Conjuration','ArcCo',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Conjuration is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to summoning, controlling, and dismissing extraplanar entities. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(57,'Arcane - Divination','ArcDi',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Divination is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to divination, detection, senses, prediction, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(58,'Arcane - Enchantment','ArcEn',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Enchantment is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to the mind and the emotions. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(59,'Arcane - Hydromancy','ArcHy',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Hydromancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to water, liquids, ice and cold, acid, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(60,'Arcane - Illumination','ArcIm',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Illumination is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to light, shadows, darkness, colors, radiant energy, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(61,'Arcane - Illusion','ArcIl',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Illusion is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to illusions and the senses. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(62,'Arcane - Kinetomancy','ArcKi',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Kinetomancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to telekinesis, force fields, levitation, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(63,'Arcane - Lithomancy','ArcLi',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Lithomancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to earth, stone, metal, solid matter, and some types of craft. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(64,'Arcane - Necromancy','ArcNe',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Necromancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to life, death, undeath, disease, necrotic energy, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(65,'Arcane - Ouranomancy','ArcOu',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Ouranomancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to time, space, other dimensions, teleportation, gravity, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(66,'Arcane - Pyromancy','ArcPy',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Pyromancy is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to fire, heat, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(67,'Arcane - Transmutation','ArcTr',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Arcane - Transmutation is a skill that lets you cast arcane spells related to changes and enhancements in size, shape, physical attributes, etc. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(68,'Divine - Animals','DivAn',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Animals is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to natural animals. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(69,'Divine - Blessing','DivBl',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Blessing is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to blessing the followers and allies of the church. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(70,'Divine - Charm','DivCh',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Charm is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to the mind and the emotions. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(71,'Divine - Death','DivDe',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Death is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to death, undeath, darkness, poison, disease, and necrotic energy. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(72,'Divine - Elements','DivEl',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Elements is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to the elements (air, earth, fire, and water). See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(73,'Divine - Insight','DivIn',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Insight is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to detection, divination, prediction, guidance, and scrying. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(74,'Divine - Life','DivLi',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Life is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to healing, light, life, and radiant energy. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(75,'Divine - Nature','DivNa',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Nature is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to nature and weather. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(76,'Divine - Plants','DivPl',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Plants is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to plants and plant-based materials. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(77,'Divine - Protection','DivPr',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Protection is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to protection, resistance, and warding. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(78,'Divine - Retribution','DivRe',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Retribution is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to cursing, attacking, and punishing infidels. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(79,'Divine - Summoning','DivSu',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine - Summoning is a skill that lets you cast divine spells related to summoning and dismissing extraplanar creatures as well as planar travel. See the magic rules for more details about spells and spell casting.'),(80,'Psi - Clairsentience','PsiCs',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Psi - Clairsentience is a skill that lets you manifest psionic powers related to divination, perception, scrying, and prediction. See the magic rules for more details about psionic powers and manifestation. Psions specializing in clairsentience are often referred to as seers.'),(81,'Psi - Metacreativity','PsiMc',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Psi - Metacreativity is a skill that lets you manifest psionic powers related to creation of matter and ectoplasm. They can even be used to create and temporarily bestow a semblance of life to constructs. See the magic rules for more details about psionic powers and manifestation. Psions specializing in metacreativity are often referred to as shapers.'),(82,'Psi - Psychokinesis','PsiPk',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Psi - Psychokinesis is a skill that lets you manifest psionic powers related to telekinesis, force fields, levitation, energy manipulation, etc. See the magic rules for more details about psionic powers and manifestation. Psions specializing in psychokinesis are often referred to as savants.'),(83,'Psi - Psychometabolism','PsiPm',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Psi - Psychometabolism is a skill that lets you manifest psionic powers related to shapeshifting, healing, physical enhancements, etc. See the magic rules for more details about psionic powers and manifestation. Psions specializing in psychometabolism are often referred to as egoists.'),(84,'Psi - Psychoportation','PsiPp',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Psi - Psychoportation is a skill that lets you manifest psionic powers related to time, space, teleportation, etc. See the magic rules for more details about psionic powers and manifestation. Psions specializing in psychoportation are often referred to as nomads.'),(85,'Psi - Telepathy','PsiTp',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Psi - Telepathy is a skill that lets you manifest psionic powers related to the mind, the senses, etc. See the magic rules for more details about psionic powers and manifestation. Psions specializing in telepathy are often referred to as telepaths.'),(86,'Bard Affinity','BAff',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bard Affinity lets you use music and singing to facilitate the casting of certain spells.'),(87,'Cleric Affinity - Air Domain','CAAir',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleric Affinity - Air Domain improves your casting of many divine spells, particularly those related to the element of air.'),(88,'Cleric Affinity - Animal Domain','CAAni',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleric Affinity - Animal Domain improves your casting of many divine spells, particularly those related to animals.'),(89,'Cleric Affinity - Cavern Domain','CACav',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleric Affinity - Cavern Domain improves your casting of many divine spells, particularly those related to caves and the Underdark.'),(90,'Cleric Affinity - Chaos Domain','CAChs',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleric Affinity - Chaos Domain improves your casting of many divine spells, particularly those related to the alignment of chaos and chaotic outsiders.'),(91,'Cleric Affinity - Charm Domain','CAChm',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleric Affinity - Charm Domain improves your casting of many divine spells, particularly those related to charm and seduction.'),(92,'Cleric Affinity - Craft Domain','CACrf',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleric Affinity - Craft Domain improves your casting of many divine spells, particularly t