adow Weave Affinity is a skill that lets you tap the Shadow Weave (instead of the regular Weave) when casting spells. In the Forgotten Realms world, the Shadow Weave is related to the goddess Shar, while the normal Weave is related to Mystra.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Shadow Weave feats.'),(161,'Adept Affinity','AAff',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Adept Affinity makes you more proficient in casting a selection of relatively basic spells.'),(162,'Animal Companion','AniCm',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Animal Companion is a skill that lets you attract one or more animals (creatures of the animal type) and turn them into dedicated friends and allies. It will even let you improve your companions to levels far above those of natural animals (see Rules of Culture for details). The CL sum of your animal companions must not exceed your (skill level - 1).\\nYou can handle your animal companions (see Animal Empathy) with verbal commands (no AP cost).\\nAny spell you cast on yourself can automatically affect your animal companions as well (1 sq range; no extra cost; effect ends if the companion moves more than 1 sq from master).\\nInspired by the 3.5E Druid and Ranger classes.'),(163,'Arcane Archery','AArch',10,NULL,'Skl(WpBow)>=6 AND Skl(ArcTr)>=1','MIN(Skl(WpBow)-6,Skl(ArcTr)-1)','Arcane Archery is a supernatural ability that lets you enchant arrows while firing them. This skill is extremely difficult to learn and typically requires being taught by one who has already mastered it. Only elves and half-elves have been known to master this skill, and they have never taught it to non-elves.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Arcane Archer prestige class.'),(164,'Arcane Trickery','ATrck',10,NULL,'Skl(Thiev)>=4 AND Skl(SplCr)>=1 AND (Skl(ArcKi)>=5 OR Skl(PsiPk)>=5) AND Skl(VitAt)>=3','MIN(Skl(Thiev)-4,MIN(Skl(SplCr)-1,MIN(Skl(VitAt)-3,MAX(Skl(ArcKi)-5,Skl(PsiPk)-5))))','Arcane Trickery is the ability to combine and enhance the Thievery skill with arcane magic.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Arcane Trickster prestige class.'),(165,'Bardic Knowledge','BdKno',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bardic Knowledge is a very generic knowledge skill.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Bard class.'),(166,'Bardic Music','BdMus',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bardic Music is a skill that lets you work magic with song and music.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Bard class.'),(167,'Divine Mount','DvMnt',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine Mount is a special skill that grants you the service of an exceptional extraplanar steed. As your skill level increases, you can either improve your mount (see Rules of Culture for details) or replace it with a more versatile one. Releasing a mount from your service and replacing it with a new one requires a one-day ritual but carries no other cost. If a mount dies, however, it will take thirty days before a new one can be called. The mount must be an animal or monstrous animal that can carry a rider, and the CL of your mount must not exceed your (skill level - 1).\\nEmpathic Link [Su]: You can communicate empathically with your mount to a range of 1 km (no AP cost).\\nAny spell you cast on yourself can automatically affect your mount as well (1 sq range; no extra cost; effect ends if the mount moves more than 1 sq from master).\\nWhen you are mounted, the mount can use your Fort, Ref, and Will defenses (if they are better).\\nInspired by the 3.5E Paladin class.'),(168,'Divine Providence','DvPro',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine Providence is a skill that represents how much protection your patron deity grants you. This skill is primarily taught by churches of good or evil deities, but a few neutral ones have also been known to teach it to their templars.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Paladin class.'),(169,'Divine Smiting','DvSmi',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Divine Smiting is a skill that helps you identify and punish the enemies of your deity. This skill is primarily taught by churches of good or evil deities, but a few neutral ones have also been known to teach it to their templars.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Paladin class.'),(170,'Enchant Item','EncIt',8,1,NULL,NULL,'Enchant Item is a combination of all the skills used for creating magic devices, animating constructs, imbuing objects with intelligence, transferring power from one item to another, etc. A magic item that has been partially damaged loses none of its magic and can still be repaired with the appropriate Crafting specialization.'),(171,'Familiar','Famil',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Familiar is a skill that lets you summon a special animal to serve as your familiar. As your skill level increases, you can either improve your familiar (see Rules of Culture for details) or replace it with a more versatile creature. Unless the DM specifically allows it, you can never have more than one familiar. If a familiar dies or is dismissed/replaced by you, it will take one year before a new one can be summoned.\\nThe familiar must be an animal or monstrous animal at least one size category smaller than you, and the CL of your familiar must not exceed your (skill level - 1). If the DM allows multiple familiars, the sum of their CL must not exceed your (skill level - 1).\\nEmpathic Link [Su]: You can communicate empathically with your familiar to a range of 1 km (no AP cost).\\nWhen the familiar is within 1 sq, you gain a +2 skill level bonus on Perception.\\nWhen the familiar is within 1 km, you gain a +2 skill level bonus on one of the familiar\'s racial skills (chosen when the familiar is summoned).\\nAny spell you cast on yourself can automatically affect your familiar as well (1 sq range; no extra cost; effect ends if the familiar moves more than 1 sq from master).\\nWhen the familiar is within 1 sq, it can use your Fort, Ref, and Will defenses (if they are better).\\nInspired by the 3.5E Sorcerer and Wizard classes.'),(172,'Ki - Defense','KiDef',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Defense is an almost supernatural ability to focus your inner strength and use it to defend against attacks.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(173,'Ki - Meditation','KiMed',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Meditation is the ability to focus your inner strength and gain a number of almost supernatural abilities.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(174,'Ki - Mobility','KiMob',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Mobility is the ability to focus your inner strength and use it to enhance your speed and mobility.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(175,'Ki - Offense','KiOff',8,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Offense is the ability to focus your inner strength and use it to enhance your natural weapon attacks.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(176,'Metamorphosis - Celestial','MmCel',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcCo)>=5 OR Skl(DivSu)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MAX(Skl(ArcCo)-5,Skl(DivSu)-5))','Metamorphosis - Celestial is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a celestial creature. This transformation can involve arcane rituals, bargains with celestial beings, awakening a dormant bloodline, et al.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Celestial bloodline and celestial template.'),(177,'Metamorphosis - Demonic','MmDem',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcCo)>=5 OR Skl(DivSu)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MAX(Skl(ArcCo)-5,Skl(DivSu)-5))','Metamorphosis - Demonic is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a demonic creature. This transformation can involve arcane rituals, bargains with demons, awakening a dormant bloodline, et al.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Demonic bloodline and fiendish template.'),(178,'Metamorphosis - Diabolic','MmDia',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcCo)>=5 OR Skl(DivSu)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MAX(Skl(ArcCo)-5,Skl(DivSu)-5))','Metamorphosis - Diabolic is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a diabolic creature. This transformation can involve arcane rituals, bargains with devils, awakening a dormant bloodline, et al.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Diabolic bloodline and fiendish template.'),(179,'Metamorphosis - Draconic','MmDra',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND Skl(ArcTr)>=5','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,Skl(ArcTr)-5)','Metamorphosis - Draconic is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a draconic creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Dragon Disciple prestige class, Draconic bloodline, and half-dragon template.'),(180,'Metamorphosis - Air Elemental','MmAEl',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcAe)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcEn)-5,Skl(DivLi)-5),MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcTr)-5,Skl(DivNa)-5),MAX(Skl(ArcAe)-5,Skl(DivEl)-5))))','Metamorphosis - Air Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(181,'Metamorphosis - Earth Elemental','MmEEl',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcLi)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcEn)-5,Skl(DivLi)-5),MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcTr)-5,Skl(DivNa)-5),MAX(Skl(ArcLi)-5,Skl(DivEl)-5))))','Metamorphosis - Earth Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(182,'Metamorphosis - Fire Elemental','MmFEl',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcPy)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcEn)-5,Skl(DivLi)-5),MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcTr)-5,Skl(DivNa)-5),MAX(Skl(ArcPy)-5,Skl(DivEl)-5))))','Metamorphosis - Fire Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(183,'Metamorphosis - Water Elemental','MmWEl',10,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcHy)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','MIN(Skl(SplCr)-5,MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcEn)-5,Skl(DivLi)-5),MIN(MAX(Skl(ArcTr)-5,Skl(DivNa)-5),MAX(Skl(ArcHy)-5,Skl(DivEl)-5))))','Metamorphosis - Water Elemental is not so much 