separate bolts, each of which has the full-size area of effect.'),(55,33,'Hold',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You render the animals or plant creatures immobile and helpless.'),(56,33,'Compulsion',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','You can actually control the animals or plant creatures with simple mental commands (compelled condition) as long as they remain within range.'),(57,34,'Suggestion',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','If you share a language with the target, you can make a separate attack check against Will to make a suggested course of action (simple enough to be described in a sentence or two) seem more reasonable. Note that this effect is separate and can be successful, even if the charm attempt fails.'),(58,36,'Hypnotism',NULL,NULL,'+0 PP','Instead of suffering the stunning/blinding/unconsciousness effect described, affected creatures become fascinated by the pattern and do nothing but stare at it for the specified duration (unless they are attacked).'),(59,36,'Mobility',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','With a redirect action, you can move the pattern 6 squares per round. If you use the hypnotism variation, affected creatures will try to follow the pattern. If the pattern leads creatures into obvious danger, you must succeed on a second check against their Will.'),(60,38,'Stone Tell',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You gain additional information from natural or worked stone in the area, including who or what has touched or walked on it, what is covered or concealed by it, etc.'),(61,39,'Animal Speech',NULL,'Divine - Animals','1 PP','The target becomes able to understand and communicate with all normal and monstrous animals. Note, however, that this does not automatically alter the attitude of an animal.'),(62,39,'Plant Speech',NULL,'Divine - Plants','5 PP','The target becomes able to understand and communicate with all normal and monstrous plants. Note, however, that this does not automatically alter the attitude of a plant.'),(63,40,'Planar Seal',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','All planar summoning and travel into or within the area must beat the spell\'s PL.'),(64,40,'Forbiddance','[MR, Radiant or Necrotic]',NULL,'+4 PP','Creatures that differ from the deity\'s alignment take damage when they try to enter the area. Make a +PL attack against Will (S - Those of opposed alignment take 12d6 HP of radiant or necrotic damage, and those of differing alignment take 6d6 HP; F - Half damage). The forbiddance can include a password that lets creatures enter freely, regardless of their alignment.'),(65,42,'Tornado',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','The wind strength reaches tornado level, and creatures in the area take 6d6 HP and 6d6 SP of blunt damage per round.'),(66,45,'Despair',NULL,NULL,'1 PP for -2\\n7 PP for -4','You cause great sadness, giving the targets a morale penalty on all action checks, weapon damage rolls, and defenses.'),(67,45,'Heroism',NULL,NULL,'1 PP or +2\\n7 PP for +4','You instill feelings of hope and heroism, giving the targets a morale bonus on all action checks, weapon damage rolls, and defenses.'),(68,45,'Mirth',NULL,NULL,'3 PP','The target laughs uncontrollably, falling prone and taking a -4 penalty on all action checks, weapon damage rolls, and defenses. Make a new attack roll each round against the target\'s Will (F - the effect ends against this target).\\nThis effect does not work against creatures of Int 2 or lower.'),(69,45,'Discord',NULL,NULL,'3 PP','The target becomes very irritated and aggressive. Each round there is a 50% chance that it spends all AP attacking the nearest conscious creature with its most effective attack. Make a new attack roll each round against the target\'s Will (F - the effect ends against this target).'),(70,45,'Death Wish',NULL,NULL,'11 PP','The target gets a suicidal urge and spends its actions trying to harm itself in the most efficient manner. This can include attacking itself, provoking opportunity attacks, jumping into a fire, etc. Make a new attack roll each round against the target\'s Will (F - the effect ends against this target).'),(71,45,'Dancing',NULL,NULL,'11 PP','The target gets an uncontrollable urge to dance and can perform no other actions. The dancing imposes a -4 penalty to DeC, -10 penalty to Ref defense, and negates any parry bonus to DeC. Make a new attack roll each round against the target\'s Will (F - the effect ends against this target).'),(72,46,'Quench',NULL,NULL,'5 PP','Extinguishes all fires in a shapeable area up to 64 cubes per skill level. In order to extinguish magical fires, your skill check must beat the fire\'s PL. Fire-based creatures in the area suffer 1d6 HP of damage per 2 skill levels.'),(73,49,'Charm',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You change the target\'s attitude to friendly. You will still need additional skill checks to convince the creature to do things it would not ordinarily do, and suicidal orders will not be obeyed. If you attack the target, you automatically break the spell.'),(74,49,'Hold',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','You render the target immobile and helpless.'),(75,49,'Compulsion',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','You can actually control the undead creatures (compelled condition) with simple mental commands as long as they remain within range.'),(76,52,'Weather',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP for normal\\n+10 PP for extreme','In addition to controlling the winds, you can also increase or decrease precipitation, fog, and temperature. Unless you pay the cost for extreme weather, you can only create weather conditions that are appropriate for the climate and season.'),(77,52,'Vengeance',NULL,'Divine - Retribution','+10 PP','You summon a fierce storm, including black clouds, lightning, and thunder. If you concentrate on the storm for a minimum number of rounds, you can trigger specific effects in the area; after 2 or more rounds, acid rain causing 1d6 HP of damage; 3 or more rounds, six bolts of lightning strike one square each (+PL attack against Ref; S - 10d6 HP of electricity damage; F - half damage); 4 or more rounds, hailstones dealing 5d6 HP of blunt damage. Even when you don\'t concentrate on the storm, it reduces visibility to 1 square, effectively deafens all creatures in the area, quadruples movement costs, and makes ranged attacks impossible.'),(78,52,'Cyclone',NULL,NULL,'+12 PP','As part of the wind alteration, you create a small cyclone that lasts for up to one round per skill level. The cyclone has a 2 sq diameter at the base, 6 sq diameter at the top, and is 6 sq tall. It can move 12 squares per round, and you can specify its path at the time of casting or control it each round by spending 6 AP. Creatures of Large size or smaller take 3d6 HP per round in contact with the cyclone. If a +10 attack beats the Ref of a victim of Medium size or smaller, it is bodily picked up by the cyclone and carried along, automatically taking 1d6 HP and 1d6 SP of damage per round.'),(79,52,'Waterspout',NULL,NULL,'+12 PP','You cause a waterspout to rise up from a body of water at least 2 squares wide and 4 squares deep. The spout has a 1 sq radius and is 16 sq tall, and you can move it 6 squares per round (but it must remain over water). Creatures and objects in contact with the spout suffer a +8 attack against Ref each round. A successful attack causes 4d6 SP of damage. Creatures and objects of medium size or smaller are sucked into the spout and take 2d6 SP per round for 1d3 rounds (after which they are expelled).'),(80,52,'Maelstrom',NULL,NULL,'+14 PP','You create a deadly vortex in a body of water. The vortex has a 12 square radius and is 12 squares deep, and the body of water must be at least this size. Any creature or craft of large size or smaller suffers a +10 attack against Ref each round. If the attack succeeds, the target is sucked into the vortex. Once sucked inside, a target is battered for 4d6 SP per round for 2d4 rounds (after which it is expelled).'),(81,56,'Feast',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','You bring forth a great feast suitable for up to one M-sized creature per skill level. In addition to the food and drink, you call forth tables, chairs, and services that remain for 1 hour. Those that partake of the feast\'s beverage are cured of natural diseases and nausea, become immune to poison for 12 h, and receive temporary HP equal to your skill level (also for up to 12 h). Those that partake of the food become immune to fear and receive a +1 morale bonus to attack rolls and Will defense for 12 h. At least 1 hour must be spent drinking and eating in order to receive the benefits.'),(82,61,'Cure Paralysis',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You remove the effects of any paralysis or stunned condition from the creature(s).'),(83,61,'Restoration',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP for lesser\\n+4 PP for medium\\n+8 PP for greater\\n+10 PP for life force','Lesser: You restore 1d4 points of ability damage to one ability score.\\nMedium: Restores all ability damage. Also restores ability drain to one ability score.\\nGreater: Restores all ability damage and ability drain.\\nLife force: Restores any levels and/or AP drained recently (up to 1 day per skill level).'),(84,61,'Cure Poison',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP for delay\\n+4 PP for neutralize','Delay: Suppresses the effects of any poison for 1 day, regardless of whether the target already has poison in its system or is exposed to poison during the day.\\nNeutralize: Instead of temporarily suppressing the effects of poison, it removes all poison from the target\'s system and also makes it immune to poison for 1 day.'),(85,61,'Cure Senses',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP for cure blindness\\n+4 PP for cure deafness','Cure blindness: You cure blindness, whether it is natural or magical. Lost eyes are not restored.\\nCure deafness: You cure deafness, whether it is natural or magical. Lost ears are not restored.'),(86,61,'Cure Disease',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Cures all diseases (and kills all parasites) that the target is suffering from. Certain magical diseases may require you to beat the DC of the disease with your spellcasting check.'),(87,61,'Cure Insanity',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Cures any insanity, natural or magical, that the target is suffering from.'),(88,63,'Mark',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The curse includes a highly visible mark of some sort. The mark has no special effects other than being difficult to hide.'),(89,63,'Silence',NULL,NULL,'+3 PP','The targets become unable to speak (or whistle, whisper, shout, cast verbal spells, utter command words, etc). Make a new attack roll each round against the target\'s Will (F - the effect ends against this target).'),(90,63,'Triggered',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The effects will not activate until the conditions specified by the caster have been fulfilled. The duration starts immediately, however.'),(91,64,'Free-Floating',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of causing an object to radiate darkness, you cause the air itself to do so. You can cause the darkness to move in any direction up to 20 squares per round.'),(92,64,'Shapeable',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The shape and direction of the darkness can be controlled each round. For example, you can turn it into a cone (like a bullseye lantern) or shape the darkness itself into a vaguely humanoid figure.'),(93,64,'Blacklight',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You are yourself not affected by the spell\'s area of darkness (in other words, you can see through the area as if the spell didn\'t exist).'),(94,65,'Shadow Shield','[Dark]','Arcane - Illumination','+4 PP','The shield becomes shadowy and grants the target concealment. The target also gains a +2 circumstance bonus to defenses against [Light] and [Radiant] effects.'),(95,68,'Potential Detection',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','With the 3rd level of information, you can also determine every creature\'s highest skill level in supernatural skills (but not which skill).'),(96,69,'Hazard Detection',NULL,NULL,'+1 PP','You detect natural hazards (quicksand, sinkholes, deadfalls, etc) and simple traps (pits, snares, etc).'),(97,69,'Animal Detection',NULL,'Divine - Animals','+1 PP','You detect one particular kind of animal. Each round, you can change the kind you detect.'),(98,69,'Plant Detection',NULL,'Divine - Plants','+1 PP','You detect one particular kind of plant. Each round, you can change the kind you detect.'),(99,70,'Divert Teleport','[Teleport]',NULL,'+10 PP','If a teleportation attempt out of the area fails to beat your spell\'s PL, you can choose to divert the teleport to a different destination within the teleport effect\'s range.'),(100,73,'Set Anchor',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You set a mental anchor at your current location. This anchor gives you a +10 bonus to all future attempts to locate, scry on, or teleport to this location.'),(101,73,'Find the Path',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP for Find the Path\\n+12 PP for Guidance','Find the Path: For as long as the duration lasts, you instinctively know the most direct physical route to the target.\\nGuidance: Same as above, but it also reveals traps and obstacles on the way (and any passwords required to bypass them, if any).'),(102,75,'Remove Curse',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','You can also make checks against certain instantaneous effects, such as curses, involuntary shapeshifting, petrification, charms, and some other enchantments.'),(103,75,'Disjunction',NULL,NULL,'+12 PP','You can render permanent magical items and constructs non-magical. Also, instead of checking against a random effect on each creature and object, you check against all effects in the area.'),(104,77,'Verbose',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','In addition to weal or woe, you receive a single-sentence advice. This variation requires a sacrifice of at least 25 sp worth of incense.'),(105,77,'Commune',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP (100 XP cost)','You commune with divine agents and can ask one yes/no question per three skill levels.'),(106,78,'Repulsion',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Summoned creatures are prevented from touching you (and from attacking with natural weapons), if the spellcasting check beats their PL.'),(107,78,'Shared Pain',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','As long as you and the target remain within close range, half of any HP damage taken by the target is transferred to you.'),(108,78,'Damage Resistance',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP for +5 DR\\n+10 PP for +10 DR\\n+14 PP for +15 DR','The aura provides a divine bonus to DR vs non-magical weapons.'),(109,78,'Magic Resistance',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','The aura has additional effects against opponents whose alignment is opposed to that of your deity\'s. First, it provides MR 15 against their supernatural attacks. Second, when such an opponent makes a successful melee attack against a warded creature, make a +PL attack against the attacker\'s Fort (S - The attacker is permanently blinded).'),(110,79,'Enlargement',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','The targets increase in size by one size category, with the appropriate adjustments.'),(111,82,'Cocoon',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The strands enclose the target in a full cocoon (with an exceptional success). The cocoon can be cut open from the outside; it has 20 HP and DR 8. A creature inside an ectoplasmic cocoon is completely enclosed and cannot be physically harmed unless the cocoon is destroyed. The target is held helpless - it can still breathe but becomes unable to see, speak, or take physical actions.'),(112,86,'Energy Shield',NULL,'Arcane - Aeromancy (Electricity or Sonic)\\nArcane - Hydromancy (Acid or Cold)\\nArcane - Pyromancy (Fire)\\nArcane - Necromancy or Divine - Death (Necrotic)\\nArcane - Illumination or Divine - Life (Radiant)','+4 PP','You wreathe the target in a shimmering energy field. You must have paid for at least one energy resistance or immunity to use this variation, and the energy field will have the same energy type(s) as chosen for the resistance. Any creature successfully striking the target with a melee weapon of 0 or 1 squares reach takes 1d6+5 HP of damage of the chosen energy type(s).'),(113,86,'Energy Absorption',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','For every 5 HP that the energy resistance protects against, the target regains 1 PP.'),(114,87,'Paralysis',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Additional attack roll of d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort\\nS - The target creature is also stunned for 1 round.\\nES - The target is also paralyzed for the rest of the encounter.'),(115,87,'Energy Drain',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP\\n+16 PP for true drain','A successful attack also causes 4 points of ability drain to both Con and Wis and inflicts a -4 penalty on all action checks.\\nTrue drain: Effects increase to 8 points of Con and Wis ability drain and -8 penalty on action checks.'),(116,89,'Jump',NULL,NULL,'+1 PP','The target also gains a +10 enhancement bonus to Jump checks.'),(117,89,'Spider Climb',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The target gains the ability to climb on vertical surfaces and even ceilings with a base speed of 4 (no Climb checks needed). Both hands and feet must be used while climbing.'),(118,89,'Immobility',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Whenever the target concentrates on anchoring itself (requiring full and continuous concentration), it gains a +20 enhancement bonus on defenses to avoid being physically or magically moved, and it also gains a natural DR of 10.'),(119,89,'Evasion',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP\\n+12 PP for greater evasion','The target gains the benefit of the evasion (or greater evasion) ability.'),(120,91,'Darkvision',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You grant the target creature darkvision with a range of 12 squares.'),(121,91,'See Invisible',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The target gains the ability to see invisible, magically concealed, and ethereal creatures (but not hidden or non-magically concealed ones) as translucent shapes.'),(122,91,'Scent',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The target gains the scent ability, making it easier to detect and track other creatures.'),(123,91,'Synesthete',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You can choose one sense to act as a replacement for another one. For example, you can choose to perceive sight or sound through your skin\'s sense of touch.'),(124,91,'Perception',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP for +5 bonus\\n+6 PP for +10 bonus\\n+10 PP for +20 bonus','The target gains an enhancement bonus to all Perception checks. Furthermore, passive checks can be made to automatically detect most secret doors, traps, etc.'),(125,91,'All-Around Vision',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The target gains all-around vision, protecting him against flanking.'),(126,91,'True Seeing',NULL,NULL,'+12 PP','The target gains the ability to see all things as they actually are, with a range of 24 sq. It can see through normal and magical darkness, see invisible and ethereal creatures and objects, recognize illusions, negate magical concealment effects, and see the true form of shapechanged creatures and objects.'),(127,94,'Mansion',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','You create a much larger extradimensional dwelling and an entrance to it. The entrance looks like a shimmering rectangle 1.2x2.4 m in size. Only those designated by you can enter the portal, and you can make it invisible when you are inside the dwelling. The dwelling is comfortable and magnificently decorated, has enough food and drink for a huge banquet for 12 people per skill level, and it has a maximum size of 25 cubes per skill level. If you also pay for the servant option, the spell includes servants for all inhabitants. Furniture and other items created by this spell turn into smoke if brought outside the mansion (even if cast with a permanent duration).'),(128,95,'Phantasmal Killer','[Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion','+6 PP','You enhance the fear effect with an illusion that is terrifying enough to kill the targets. Make a second attack against each affected target\'s Fort (same modifiers as the Will attack) to scare them to death (S - Targets suffer 6d6 SP of damage; ES - Targets die of fright; F - Targets suffer 3d6 SP).'),(129,96,'Preservation',NULL,'Divine - Nature','+0 PP','The fire causes no damage whatsoever to vegetation and plant creatures.'),(130,97,'Reactive Stride',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','During the spell\'s duration, and whenever you have a large enough fire within 6 squares, you can trigger a teleportation once per round as a free reaction to any trigger of your choice.'),(131,99,'Stench','[Poison]',NULL,'+2 PP','The fog is nauseating and requires a +PL attack against Fort (S - Target becomes sickened for the rest of the encounter; ES - Target becomes nauseated for the rest of the encounter).'),(132,99,'Solid Fog',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The fog is dense enough to slow movement and hinder attacks. Multiply all movement costs by 6, and reduce falling damage by 1d6 HP per square fallen through the fog. Melee attacks suffer a -2 penalty to both attack and damage. Ranged weapon attacks are stopped completely.'),(133,99,'Acid Fog','[Acid]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nDivine - Elements','+6 PP','The fog is highly acidic and causes 2d6 HP of acid damage each round to all creatures and objects inside.'),(134,99,'Cloudkill','[Poison]',NULL,'+6 PP','The fog is poisonous by touch (+PL against Fort each round; S - 1d4 points of Con damage).'),(135,99,'Mind Fog','[Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm','+6 PP','The fog clouds the mind (+PL against Will each round; S - -10 penalty on Will defense for the rest of the encounter (even if the target leaves the fog)).'),(136,99,'Incendiary Fog','[Fire]','Arcane - Pyromancy\\nDivine - Elements','+10 PP','The fog is shot through with white-hot embers and causes 3d6 HP of fire damage each round to all creatures and objects inside.'),(137,100,'Force Barrier',NULL,NULL,'7 PP','This variation creates a force field of the chosen shape. Unless otherwise specified, the field is immobile and invisible. The field is extremely durable, with a DR of 30 and 20 HP per PL, but it can be bypassed with teleportation effects or dispelled, and gaze attacks can pass through it.\\nThe force field can be created so that it intersects with solid, non-living matter, but it cannot be created within living creatures nor be used to injure them.\\nThe barred cage consists of 1-cm wide bands and 1-cm wide gaps. Attacks through such a cage are only possible if they can pass through gaps of that size.'),(138,100,'Telekinetic Field',NULL,NULL,'15 PP','Same as the force barrier variation, but if the creatures and objects enclosed in the force field weigh 2500 kg or less, you can concentrate to move the field and its contents up to 6 squares per round (in any direction but only within the chosen range). If you cease concentrating when the field is unsupported, it falls at a slow rate of 12 squares per round.'),(139,102,'Pushing Hand',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Once per round, the hand can make a bull rush attack (+15 vs. DeC) against the target.'),(140,102,'Grappling Hand',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Once per round, the hand can initiate a grapple (+22 vs. DeC) or make a grapple attack (+27 attack; no damage).'),(141,102,'Striking Fist',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Once per round, the hand can strike the opponent with a melee attack (+28 vs. DeC; 2d6 + 11 HP blunt damage; +20 attack vs. Fort to stun for 1 round).'),(142,102,'Crushing Hand',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','Once per round, the hand can initiate a grapple (+32 vs. DeC) or make a grapple attack (+37 attack; 3d6 + 12 HP blunt damage).'),(143,103,'Danger Sense',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP\\n+8 PP for improved','The target gains +6 enhancement bonus in the Danger Sense skill.\\nImproved danger sense: The target cannot be surprised or flat-footed, and the bonus in Danger Sense increases from +6 to +12.'),(144,108,'Silence',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You deaden sounds in the area of effect, providing a -10 circumstance penalty on listen checks. Sonic attacks are not affected, but creatures in the area receive a +4 circumstance bonus against language-dependent attacks. Action checks with a verbal component suffer a -4 circumstance penalty.'),(145,108,'Sound Sculpting',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You change a certain type of sound into a different sound. For example, you can change the sound of the wind into singing, or you can change all voices in the area into barking. If this affects someone\'s voice, action checks with a verbal component suffer a -4 penalty.'),(146,109,'Greater Glyph',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','The glyph makes a +10 attack and deals 12d6 HP of damage (instead of +5 and 6d6).'),(147,109,'Affliction Glyph','[Necrotic]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Death','+6 PP for pain glyph\\n+10 PP for weakness glyph\\n+12 PP for death glyph','Pain glyph: If a +10 attack against Fort succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst suffer wracking pains for 1 hour. This imposes a -4 penalty on all action checks.\\nWeakness glyph: If a +12 attack against Fort succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst suffer 3d6 points of Strength damage.\\nDeath glyph: If a +12 attack against Fort succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius die.'),(148,109,'Mind Glyph','[Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm','+6 PP for sleep glyph\\n+8 PP for fear glyph\\n+8 PP for persuasion glyph\\n+10 PP for stun glyph\\n+12 PP for insanity glyph','Sleep glyph ([Sleep]): If a +10 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst fall into a catatonic slumber for 3d6ร10 minutes.\\nFear glyph ([Fear]): If a +10 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst become panicked for 1 round per skill level.\\nPersuasion glyph ([Charm]): If a +10 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst become charmed by the caster for 1 hour per skill level.\\nStun glyph: If a +12 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius burst become stunned for 1d6 rounds.\\nInsanity glyph: If a +12 attack against Will succeeds, creatures within a 12 square radius become permanently insane.'),(149,110,'Revivify',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','If the target died due to HP damage during the previous two rounds, the healing still takes effect (potentially saving the target\'s life).'),(150,110,'Regeneration',NULL,NULL,'+14 PP','You restore missing body parts (limbs, eyes, ears, etc), destroyed organs, and crushed bones. This regeneration takes 2d10 rounds after completion of the spell.'),(151,116,'Blinding',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The glow makes a +PL attack against the target\'s Ref (S - The target is blinded for 1 round; ES - Target is blinded for the rest of the encounter).'),(152,117,'Improved Illusion',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The illusion can also include simple sounds (but not speech).'),(153,117,'Major Illusion',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The illusion can also include sound, smell, and temperature components. Speech with multiple voices (and other vocal sounds) is possible.'),(154,118,'Mask',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of disguising the targets, you cover their faces with shadowy masks. The mask conceals their appearance but does not impede vision. It also provides a +4 circumstance bonus to defenses against blinding attacks and gaze attacks.'),(155,118,'Full Illusion',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The illusion is not only visual, but also includes sound, smell, and touch.'),(156,119,'Mislead',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You make yourself invisible (see Invisibility spell) while creating a single illusory duplicate in your space. You can direct the duplicate to move anywhere within line of sight (with your own base speed and movement abilities). The duplicate is immune to all attacks.'),(157,119,'Projection',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','You create a single quasi-real duplicate of yourself within 40 squares. It looks, sounds, and smells like you but is intangible and immune to attacks. The duplicate mimics your actions (and speech) every round, unless you spend 5 AP to mentally direct it to act differently. Your MP can be spent either on yourself or on moving the duplicate (or a mix of both). You can choose to see and hear through the duplicate\'s senses, and you can switch your perception back and forth at no cost. You can cast your spells and use other supernatural powers through the projection, causing them to originate from (and even affect) the duplicate. If you are holding a melee weapon, the duplicate appears threatening enough to provide flanking bonuses.\\nIf the distance between you and the duplicate exceeds 40 squares, or if you lose line of effect, the duplicate disappears instantly, and the spell ends.'),(158,120,'Illusory Construction',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP per 2x2 sq wall\\n+4 PP for illusory construction','The wall variation lets you augment your illusion with a visual illusion of natural or constructed walls, floors, and/or ceilings. Such illusions can also be used to hide real doors, pits, and openings.\\nIllusory Building: You can also hide or change any buildings and other constructions in the area.'),(159,122,'Flensing',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','In addition to dealing damage, a successful attack also causes 1d6 points of ability damage to Con and Cha.'),(160,123,'Stun',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of confusing the target, you stun it. A stunned creature can take no actions.'),(161,123,'Feeblemind',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Instead of confusing the target, you reduce its Int and Cha to 1. It can still move and attack with weapons, but it cannot cast spells, communicate, or perform most skills.\\nThis variation is particularly potent against arcane casters; the attack gains a +2 bonus per Arcane Affinity skill that the target has at least 1 level in.'),(162,124,'True Invisibility',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','You make the target (and its equipment) invisible to normal sight as well as darkvision, in other words giving it total concealment. If the target makes an attack, the spell ends (just as for the basic spell).'),(163,124,'Invisibility Sphere',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Each target emanates an invisibility sphere of 2 square radius. All creatures within that volume at the time of casting also become invisible, and they remain invisible for as long as they stay within the emanation. Creatures within the emanation can see each other, but creatures entering it after the casting do not become invisible, nor can they see the invisible creatures. If any invisible creature makes an attack, the effect ends for each and every emanation affecting that creature.'),(164,124,'Greater Invisibility',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Same as true invisibility, but the invisibility is not terminated by attacks made by the subject(s).'),(165,125,'Greater Lore',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP\\n+14 PP for vision','You magically bring to mind legends about an important person, place, or object. The more information about the subject you start with and the better your spellcasting check, the more detailed the results of this spell. Normal success typically reveals the target\'s name, race or type, class, and alignment. Outstanding success also reveals approximate power and current location. Any greater level of success reveals actions taken and locations visited by the target during the previous 8 hours.\\nVision: Same as above, but in addition to the normal results, you may receive a vision about the person, place, or object. This can be a current view or a particularly important vision from its history.'),(166,126,'Water Walk',NULL,NULL,'+1 PP','By hovering 1 to 2 cm over the ground, you can move across any surface (including water, mud, snow, ice, and even lava) as if it were solid ground. You also become harder to track (-10 penalty). If the target is submerged in a liquid, this effect will carry it towards the surface at a rate of 12 sq per round.'),(167,126,'True Levitate',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The targeted creature can levitate up or down with a base speed of 4. It cannot move horizontally, unless it is able to push against a wall or ceiling (at half normal speed).'),(168,126,'True Flight',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The targeted creature can fly freely in any direction. You can choose either a base flying speed of 6 and good maneuverability or a base speed of 8 and average maneuverability.'),(169,127,'Free-Floating',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of causing an object to glow, you cause the air itself to glow. You can cause the light to move in any direction up to 20 squares per round.'),(170,127,'Shapeable',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The shape and direction of the glow can be controlled each round. For example, you can turn the light into a cone (like a bullseye lantern) or shape the glow itself into a vaguely humanoid figure.'),(171,127,'Daylight',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The brightness is equal to full daylight (bright light) within 8 squares, normal light within 16 squares, and dim light within 24 squares.'),(172,128,'Speak with Dead','[Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm','+4 PP','Instead of preserving the corpse, you try to read its memories. If you make an attack that beats the target\'s Will (that the creature had when alive), you can effectively \"ask\" the corpse one simple question per two skill levels. Note that this spell only accesses the knowledge and memories of the corpse, not its soul or personality. The duration of this effect is just one encounter, and each corpse can only be subjected to this spell variation once.'),(173,132,'Time Stop',NULL,NULL,'17 PP','This variation actually stops the flow of time for everyone except the target creatures, letting them immediately spend 5d10 AP without interference. The affected creatures can move, but they are unable to affect creatures and objects that are still frozen in time.'),(174,133,'Illusory Script',NULL,'Arcane - Illusion','+4 PP','You hide the actual writing behind an illusion of either unintelligible text or something else entirely. Only you and people designated by you at the time of casting can read the true text. If you spend an additional 2 PP, a successful dispelling of the illusion will also cause the real text to be erased.'),(175,133,'Suggestive Script',NULL,'Arcane - Enchantment','+4 PP','You embed a suggestion (e.g. close the book and leave, forget the book\'s existence, etc) in the text. Make a +PL attack against the reader\'s Will (S - target obeys the suggestion for 30 minutes).'),(176,134,'Stone Meld',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of melding with a plant, you meld with a mass of natural stone.'),(177,134,'Nature Stride','[Teleport]',NULL,'+6 PP\\n+8 PP for greater stride','After melding with nature, you can teleport to a similar plant or mass of stone within 400 squares (or 600 m). This action costs 5 AP and can be done once per round.\\nGreater stride: Same as above, but you can teleport to any similar plant or stone on the same plane. When you do this, however, the spell ends automatically.'),(178,135,'Stasis',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You enter a trance so deep that even magic cannot detect that you are alive. However, you remain fully aware of your surroundings, and you can dismiss the trance at any time (although this takes 4 rounds). Your metabolism is almost nonexistent, and one year of stasis equals a single day for the purpose of aging, hunger, thirst, and breathing.'),(179,135,'Regeneration',NULL,NULL,'+12 PP','You briefly increase your rate of metabolism, gaining regeneration (10 HP/SP per round) for 20 minutes.'),(180,136,'Mental Fortitude',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','In addition to the improved Will defense, the spell halves psychic damage and any other damage to health points and ability scores suffered from mind-affecting spells.'),(181,136,'Mental Fortress',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Any mind-affecting spell or effect attempted against the target has to beat your spell\'s PL. The same applies to all attempts to magically locate or detect the target.'),(182,137,'Surface Read',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','By reading the surface thoughts of the target creatures, you gain a +10 enhancement bonus on Psychology-based skill checks against them.'),(183,137,'Probe Memory',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','You can reach into a target\'s mind and examine its memories. Discovering a single piece of information takes a full round, and perusing the memory of an event takes half the time of the actual event. Each successful attack lets you probe one memory.'),(184,137,'Skill Leech',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You \"borrow\" a single skill (caster\'s choice) from the target. For the duration of the spell, you effectively have as many skill ranks in that skill as the target.'),(185,148,'Flame Blade',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The flame extends 1 m from your hand, increasing the fire damage to 1d10 HP and counting as a small-sized object (use Weapons - Natural or Weapons - Heavy Blades for bonuses).'),(186,149,'Anti-Detection',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP\\n+4 PP for improved','The spell also protects the target against any divination effect that detects auras. Any such attempt has to beat your spell\'s PL or reveal nothing.\\nImproved: The spell protects against all divination effects, not just aura detection.'),(187,149,'False Aura',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Instead of preventing the target\'s aura from being detected, you hide it behind a false aura. You can choose the specifics of the false aura, including alignment, magic, life force, etc.'),(188,150,'Detect Scrying','[Scry]',NULL,'+2 PP','You automatically detect any scrying against the target or within the area. If your spell\'s PL beats the spellcasting check of the scryer, you get a visual image of the scryer as well as his approximate direction and distance.'),(189,150,'Privacy',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','The target area is also protected against direct observers and eavesdroppers. Anyone watching from outside sees only a foggy mass, and no sounds can escape from the inside to the outside. Those inside can see and hear normally.'),(190,150,'False Vision',NULL,'Arcane - Illusion','+6 PP','You create a false image that will be seen (and heard) by any scryers unable to beat your spell\'s PL. You can concentrate to change the image at any time, but it otherwise remains static. If you combine this variation with the privacy variation, the same illusion can be presented to direct observers (instead of the fog).'),(191,150,'Backlash',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','Scryers who fail to beat the spell\'s PL also take 8d6 PP of damage.'),(192,151,'Memory Drain',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Instead of altering specific memories, you remove the benefits of recent experiences from the target creature. It effectively loses two levels.'),(193,151,'Delete Skill',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You can actually make the target forget a single skill, effectively reducing the level in that skill to 0. The only way to regain the skill is to relearn it or to use this spell again to undo the damage.'),(194,151,'Restoration',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You cure the target of any mental illness, including mind-affecting spells and powers. This can also restore memories and skills lost to this spell or other instantaneous effects. You can also choose to restore all ability damage to mental ability scores and any negative levels the target is suffering from.'),(195,154,'Fabricate',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You convert raw materials into a finished product. For example, you can turn trees into a bridge, hemp into a rope, wool into clothes, etc.'),(196,156,'Protection',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Targets also receive DR +5 vs non-magical weapons and a +3 resistance bonus on Fort, Ref, and Will defenses.'),(197,157,'Transmutation',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You also transmute the object to a cloth-like substance, and this will effectively suspend time for the object. For example, this application could be used on a burning torch or a bucket of water. If the cloth-like object is thrown against a solid surface, the spell ends, and the object reverts to normal.'),(198,160,'Repulsion',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','In addition to being protected against attacks, the target creature emanates a field that prevents hostile creatures from approaching. The field does not push creatures away, but it prevents affected attackers from moving closer to the target. The caster can set the radius of the emanation from 2 squares to 30 squares.'),(199,161,'Scrying Pool',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of personally receiving the information from the sensor, you show it on a display of some sort (pool of water, crystal ball, mirror, et al). This means you can show it to others.'),(200,161,'Mobile Sensor',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The sensor(s) can be moved at a rate of 6 squares per round. The sensor can pass through openings as small as 3 cm diameter. It cannot pass beyond the chosen range.'),(201,161,'Multiple Sensors',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You create up to 10 separate sensors within range.'),(202,161,'Smart Sensor',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You can give the sensor(s) simple commands, and it can alert you with a mental \"ping\". For example, you can use a mobile sensor to search for a certain object or individual, or you can use multiple sensors to set up a perimeter and watch for dangerous creatures.'),(203,162,'Lodge',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You create a small (2x2 squares) cottage or lodge inside the sphere of force. It can be made to look like a stone, timber, or even sod dwelling, but it always has the strength of a stone building. The lodge has a sturdy door (with a lock), two barred windows, a fireplace (the chimney is protected by a grate), 8 bunks, a table, 8 tools, and a writing desk.'),(204,164,'Simulacrum',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of choosing a certain creature type, you create a quasi-real duplicate of another creature within the spell\'s range. You must pay the full PP cost, based on the original\'s CL. The caster should make a Disguise check to determine how good the likeness is.'),(205,164,'Shadow Mount',NULL,NULL,'3 PP\\n+4 PP for levitating\\n+8 PP for flying','Instead of a \"normal\" creature, you conjure a horselike mount of Large size. It is black and gray, somewhat insubstantial, and completely soundless. It comes equipped with saddle, bit, and bridle, and it carries up to 100 kg plus 5 kg per skill level. It makes no attacks, but most normal animals shun it and refuse to attack it.\\nShadow mount (DeC 14; DR 4; HP 7 + skill level; Spd 3 x skill level)\\nLevitating mount: Same as above, but the creature can move across sand, mud, swamps, water, and other liquid or semiliquid surfaces without difficulty.\\nFlying mount: Same as above, but the mount can fly at base speed with average maneuverability.'),(206,164,'Shadow Hound',NULL,NULL,'7 PP','Instead of a \"normal\" creature, you conjure a shadow watchdog that guards you and attacks your enemies. It is invisible to everyone but yourself, and it can both detect and attack invisible and ethereal creatures. It barks when any intruder comes within 6 squares and attacks as directed by you.\\nShadow Watchdog (DeC 16; HP 20 + skill level; +10 attack - 2d6+3 HP piercing; invisible)'),(207,166,'Water Breathing',NULL,NULL,'1 PP','This variation alters the target(s) so that they can breathe both air and water.'),(208,166,'Plant Form',NULL,NULL,'+0 PP\\n+10 PP for oak body','You can turn the target(s) into plants of Large size (shrubs or trees). A creature in plant form has its normal HP, a natural DR of 4, +10 critical hit resistance, and is immobile (Dex and speed 0) but can still see, hear, and smell normally.\\nOak body: The target gains a natural DR of 5 and becomes immune to ability damage, blindness, deafness, disease, drowning, poison, stunning, and other similar effects. It also takes only 1/2 damage from cold but becomes vulnerable to fire. It gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Str but take a -2 enhancement penalty to Dex. The target does not (and actually can\'t) breathe, eat, or drink, but it can still speak.'),(209,166,'Gaseous Form',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You can turn the target(s) into gaseous form. In this form they have a base fly speed of 2 (perfect maneuverability).'),(210,166,'Stone Form',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP\\n+10 PP for stone body','You can turn the target(s) into solid stone statues. A creature in statue form has its normal HP, a natural DR of 8, +20 critical hit resistance, and is immobile (Dex and speed 0) but can still see, hear, and smell normally. If the creature normally consists of flesh, its mass triples.\\nStone body: Same as above, but the target can still move and act. However, its base speed is halved, and it suffers a natural encumbrance class of 8. It gains immunity to blindness, deafness, ability damage, disease, poison, and stunning. It takes 1/4 damage from cold and 1/2 damage from fire and electricity. It does not need to (and actually can\'t) breathe, drink, or eat. The creature gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Str but suffers a -4 penalty to Dex (to a minimum of 1). Finally, damage caused by its natural weapons increases by two steps.'),(211,166,'Form of Doom',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','You turn the target(s) into nightmarish versions of themselves, with writhing tentacles growing from their backs. The targets gain the frightful presence ability, a +5 natural DR bonus, +4 enhancement bonus to Str, and a +1 enhancement bonus to speed. Four of the tentacles are large enough to make melee attacks within normal reach, with a base damage of 2d8 HP.'),(212,166,'Iron Form',NULL,NULL,'+12 PP','Same as stone body variation, but the target\'s body turns into iron. It gains a natural DR of 10, enjoys a +6 enhancement bonus to Str, but suffers a -6 penalty to Dex and a natural encumbrance class of 10. A creature of iron weighs 8 times as much as one of flesh.'),(213,166,'Shadow Form','[Necrotic]',NULL,'+14 PP','You turn the target into an insubstantial shadow (+15 to Hide checks in dim light or darkness). It has its normal speed but can move across any surface, including walls and ceilings. It cannot attack physically or manipulate physical objects, but it can still cast spells and use mental powers. It gains a natural DR of 10, +20 critical hit resistance, and darkvision, and it gains immunity to ability damage, disease, drowning, and poison. It takes only 1/2 damage from acid, electricity, and fire.'),(214,169,'Ice Storm',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The storm deals 2d6 HP of blunt damage and 2d6 HP of cold damage (per round) to all creatures and objects in the area.'),(215,170,'Sympathetic Vibration',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','You bypass the DR of any targeted objects.'),(216,172,'Summon Mount',NULL,NULL,'1 PP','You summon a light riding horse or pony, including a bit and bridle and a riding saddle. It serves you willingly and well as a mount but will not serve in a combat capacity.'),(217,173,'Unseen Servant',NULL,NULL,'1 PP','A simple, nearly mindless type of air elemental that can act as a servant (fetch things, clean, mend, open doors, etc; it has Str 2 and Int 2).'),(218,177,'Scatterspray',NULL,NULL,'1 PP\\n9 PP for bombardment','You can cause a collection of small items to scatter violently, causing 2d6 HP of blunt damage in a burst of 2 square radius. You need to make an attack against the Ref of each target in the area.\\nBombardment: Instead of scattering objects, you hurl a number of objects at a single target within range. The number of objects is limited to one per two skill levels, their total mass limited to 5 kg per skill level, and they must all be within a spherical volume of 2 square radius (and within the spell\'s range). Weapons deal normal damage, while other objects deal damage based on weight and hardness.'),(219,177,'Knock',NULL,NULL,'3 PP','You remotely manipulate locks, bolts, levers, and knots and/or use brute force to open a door, a chest, box, manacles, et al. Use the spellcasting check against any DC that is keeping the object closed. Note that this check can aid or be aided by another character\'s Break Barrier or Open Lock action.'),(220,177,'Telekinetic Brawling',NULL,NULL,'7 PP','You use your telekinesis as a remote bull rush, disarm, grapple, or trip. Compare your attack against the appropriate target DC. These maneuvers are resolved normally but do not trigger attacks of opportunity.'),(221,178,'Deep Telepathy',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You can communicate fully, regardless of language barriers.'),(222,178,'Location','[Scry]',NULL,'+2 PP','As long as the target creature remains within range, you can sense its direction and distance.'),(223,178,'Status',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You can sense the target creature\'s current status (healthy, bloodied, dying, nauseated, panicked, stunned, diseased, insane, etc).'),(224,178,'Dream',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','If the target creature is sleeping, you can communicate telepathically with the creature without waking it. It will remember everything perfectly upon waking. If you make a successful attack against the target\'s Will, you can choose to give it a nightmare that prevents restful sleep and inflicts 2d10 SP and 2d10 PP of fatigue.'),(225,178,'Beckoning','[Scry]',NULL,'+4 PP','The target creature knows the approximate direction and distance to you for as long as the spell lasts.'),(226,178,'Charm',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You can cast a Charm Creature spell through the connection, but you have to spend the action time and PP for that spell as well. Use the range of the Telepathy spell.'),(227,179,'Time Hop',NULL,'Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Psychoportation','+4 PP\\n+8 PP for greater hop','You can also teleport the target forward in time up to 1 round per skill level.\\nGreater time hop: Same as above, but the maximum time is 1 hour per skill level.'),(228,179,'Trigger Object',NULL,'Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Protection','+8 PP','You store the teleport in a trigger object worth at least 150 gp (e.g. gem, rod, necklace, statuette). If the object is destroyed while speaking a command word (chosen at the time of casting), the teleport effect triggers. The teleport can have one of the following three effects, also chosen at the time of casting:\\n1. The creature breaking the object teleports to a pre-chosen destination\\n2. The creature breaking the object teleports to the caster\'s current location\\n3. The caster teleports to the location of the creature breaking the object.\\nIn all three cases, the destination has to be within the spell\'s range, or nothing happens.'),(229,183,'Ironguard',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','The target becomes \"immune\" to non-magical metal. Metal weapons pass harmlessly through him, and he can easily pass through metal walls, doors, and bars. If he makes attacks with a natural weapon against a creature with non-magical metal armor, the armor provides no DR. Note, however, that the target becomes unable to wear armor or wield weapons of non-magical metal.'),(230,185,'Fire Seeds','[Fire]',NULL,'+8 PP for bomb seeds\\n+10 PP for grenade seeds','Bomb seeds: Instead of creating nourishing berries, you turn the seeds into special bombs. If you are within 40 squares and speak a command word, each seed instantly bursts into flame, causing 1d8+skill level HP of fire damage and igniting combustibles in a burst of 1 square radius. Make a +10 attack against every affected creature\'s Ref; if the attack fails, the creature takes only half damage.\\nGrenade seeds: Instead of creating nourishing berries, you turn the seeds into special grenades. The base throwing range of each grenade is 4 squares and requires a normal ranged attack roll. A grenade that strikes a hard surface (including most creatures) explodes and causes 5d6 HP of fire damage to the target. The explosion also deals 10 HP of splash damage in a burst of 2 squares radius.'),(231,186,'Transmute Metal to Wood',NULL,NULL,'5 PP','This variation transmutes non-magical metal objects to wood.'),(232,186,'Rusting Grasp',NULL,NULL,'7 PP','This variation causes non-magical ferrous objects to become severely rusted, effectively destroying them.\\nThe spell causes 6d6+10 HP of damage against ferrous creatures.'),(233,187,'Soften',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You soften natural (unworked) earth and rock in the area. Wet earth becomes mud, dry earth becomes sand, and stone becomes soft clay. This is typically not sufficient to trap creatures, but the area becomes difficult terrain, and the spell can cause a small landslide.'),(234,187,'Spike Stones',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You turn a stone surface into a mass of hard and sharp spikes. Its appearance does not change, but it becomes difficult terrain and causes 1d8 HP of damage for every square that a creature moves on foot through the area. Furthermore, if a +10 attack roll succeeds against a creature injured by the spikes, its movement is halved for 24 h (as per caltrop wounds).'),(235,187,'Stone Shape',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','This variation lets you reshape a stone object into any shape you wish. The object must not weigh more than 10 kg per base PP cost. Fine details or moving parts will require a suitable Crafting check.'),(236,187,'Transmute Mud',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP for mud to stone\\n+4 PP for stone to mud','Mud to stone: Turns normal mud or quicksand into soft stone (sandstone, for example). Creatures in the mud suffer a +PL attack against Ref to avoid getting stuck.\\nStone to mud variation: Turns natural (unworked) stone into mud, to a maximum depth of two squares. Turning the ground into mud turns it into very difficult terrain. Turning a cliff wall or a cavern ceiling into mud will usually cause a mudslide.'),(237,188,'Ironwood',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You change the object into ironwood, a substance that is still wood but has the density, strength, resilience, and resistances of steel.'),(238,189,'Magic Mouth',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You record a spoken message and place the spell on an object or in an area and specify a trigger condition. When the condition is fulfilled, the message starts and continues for up to the chosen duration.'),(239,192,'Invisibility Purge',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The aura also temporarily disables any invisibility effect of a lower PL.'),(240,194,'Strength Drain',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','A successful attack also causes 2 points of ability damage to Str.'),(241,194,'Vampiric',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','You gain half the necrotic damage dealt as temporary HP and SP. If the damage kills a target creature, you also gain a +2 morale bonus on all action checks for the rest of the encounter.'),(242,199,'Deafening',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','A successful attack also deafens the target for the rest of the encounter.'),(243,199,'Stunning',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','A successful attack also stuns the target for 1 round.'),(244,200,'Silver Needles',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','The silver particles become needles that deal an additional 3d6 HP of continuous piercing damage per round. Against creatures sensitive to silver the damage increases to 3d10 HP.'),(245,31,'Knockdown',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','A successful attack also knocks the target prone.'),(246,28,'Freeze',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','A successful attack halves the target\'s base speed for 1 round.'),(247,196,'Freeze',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','A successful attack halves the target\'s base speed for 1 round.'),(248,169,'Sleet Storm',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The storm also douses natural fires and makes the ground extremely slippery.'),(249,183,'Thornskin',NULL,'Divine - Plants','+2 PP','The target\'s skin grows thorns that deal d6 HP of piercing damage to anyone the target is grappling with (once per round), is engulfed by, or is struck by with natural weapons (per successful attack).');
