INSERT INTO `spells` VALUES (1,'Affliction','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Nature\\nDivine - Retribution','(Tch: d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + other mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','0 PP','Rch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Special (+0)','1 living creature (+0)\\n2 living creatures (+2)\\n3-4 living creatures (+4)\\n5-8 living creatures (+6)\\n9-16 living creatures (+8)','You afflict the targets with deafness, blindness, poison, and/or a debilitating disease (see variations).','Disease option: Caster can choose one of the following diseases: Blinding sickness, Cackle fever, Filth fever, Mindfire, Red ache, Shakes, and Slimy doom. The disease strikes immediately, with no incubation period.\\nPoison option [Poison]: You inflict the target with a horrible poison (see Affliction Poison).','S - The target suffers the chosen effects for 1 round.\\nES - The target suffers the chosen effects for the rest of the encounter.\\nCS - The effect becomes permanent (does not apply to poison variation).\\nF - The target avoids the effect.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(2,'Air Walk','[Su, MR, AoO, Air]','Divine - Elements',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','7 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)\\nL creatures count as 2, H as 4, G as 8, and C as 16','The targets can tread on air as if it was solid ground. They can walk up or down at a maximum angle of 45 degrees.\\nA mount of animal intelligence has to be trained before it can walk on air successfully.','Wind walk option: The targets can also turn into gaseous form and back at will (5 r transformation time). When gaseous, a target can choose a base speed of 2 (perfect maneuverability) or 60 (poor maneuverability).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3,'Analyze Dweomer','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination and Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Clairsentience (+2 PP cost)','(d20! + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will)','1 h (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (500+ sp gem)','1 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)\\nConcentration (+4)','Objects or creatures (+0)','You discern all active spells and magical properties of an object or creature. If you choose the \"concentration\" duration, you can redirect the spell and analyze multiple targets (one per round).\\nFor magical items, you learn of all functions, how to activate them, and how many PP it has. For active spells, you learn of the skill, the spell, and the power level.',NULL,'S - You discern all active spells and magical properties of the target.\\nF - You fail to analyze the target.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(4,'Animal Shapes','[Su, MR, AoO]','Wild Shape',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','11 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)','1 willing creat. (+0)\\n2 willing creat. (+2)\\n3-4 willing creat. (+4)\\n5-8 willing creat. (+6)\\n9-16 willing creat. (+8)','You change the shape of all targets into the same kind of animal. This is a grade II shapechange.\\nEach target can terminate the effect on itself at will.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'Animate Objects','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Life\\nPsi - Psychokinesis',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 small object (+0)\\n2 small objects (+2)\\n3-4 small objects (+5)\\n5-8 small objects (+10)\\n9-16 small objects (+18)\\nM objects count as 2, L as 4, H as 8, and G as 16','The basic spell allows you to give simple commands to inanimate and unattended objects (but within their inherent limitations). For example, a rope can be commanded to \"coil\", \"knot\" itself, \"loop\", \"uncoil\", \"entangle\" (a creature in the same square), etc. An unlocked chest can be commanded to \"open\" or \"close\".','Full mobility option: The objects gain full mobility and attack ability (see the creature chapter).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(6,'Animate Plants','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Plants',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)\\nLong (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Plants in spherical spread; 8 sq radius (+0)','The basic spell animates all normal plants in the area of effect, creating difficult terrain and causing the plants to entangle all creatures that enter the area.','Spike growth option: Instead of animating the plants in the area, you turn them into a mass of hard and sharp spikes. Their appearance does not change, but they cause 1d4 HP of damage for every square that a creature moves on foot through the area. Furthermore, if a +10 attack roll succeeds against a creature injured by the spikes, its movement is halved for 24 h (as per caltrop wounds).\\nFull mobility option: You give full mobility and attack ability to a maximum of eight large plants in the area. A huge plant counts as two large, a gargantuan plant as four large, and a colossal plant as eight large. See animated objects in the creature chapter for details.\\nLiveoak option: You transform any Huge tree in the area into a treant-like creature (see the creature chapter) that defends you and obeys your spoken commands.\\nChangestaff option: Same as the liveoak option, but this instead transforms any wooden staff (or small tree).\\nShambler option: You transform some of the undergrowth into 1d4+2 shambling mounds that defend you and obey your spoken commands.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,'Antilife Shell','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Protection',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','5 PP for anti-plant','0 (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 2 PP/h)','Spherical emanation; 2 sq radius (+0)','The basic spell creates an invisible and mobile barrier that keeps out plant creatures and animated plants.\\nAlthough affected creatures are unable to reach into the protected area, they can still make ranged attacks and cast spells past the barrier.\\nForcing the barrier against an affected creature disrupts the field.','Anti-vermin option: The barrier also keeps out vermin (small mammals, insects, arachnids, etc).\\nAnti-animal option: Like anti-vermin, but the barrier also keeps out animals, monstrous animals, and vermin.\\nAnti-life option: Like anti-animal, but the barrier also keeps out aberrations, dragons, humanoids, and monstrous humanoids (but not outsiders, elementals, constructs, and undead).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(8,'Antimagic','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Ouranomancy and Abjuration\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Psychokinesis and Telepathy',NULL,'7+TPC AP\\nReaction (mandatory check with +10 DC)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for +1 resistance\\n+3 PP per additional +1','Personal (+0)\\nTch (+3)\\nClose (+6; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)\\nSpherical emanation; 2 sq radius (+0), 4 sq rad (+4), 6 sq rad (+8)','The basic spell grants a resistance bonus to defenses against spells and other supernatural effects.','Specific MR option: You grant the targets magic resistance equal to your skill level against all spells belonging to a single arcane, divine, or psi skill.\\nGeneric MR option: You grant the targets generic magic resistance equal to your skill level.\\nBacklash option: Anyone who casts a spell or uses a power that can be affected by the Antimagic power suffers a backlash that inflicts a loss of 2 PP.\\nSpell turning option: You add spell turning to the protection. Casters who cast rays and targeted spells (but not area effects) against the resistance and fail will themselves become a target.\\nSpell leeching option: Same as spell turning option, but instead of turning a spell against its caster, you absorb some of the spell\'s power. If you are the target of a ray or targeted spell, and the spell fails, you gain half of the spell\'s (total PP cost + PP boost) as temporary PP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(9,'Antipathy/Sympathy','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','1 h','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (gem worth 100+ gp)','15 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','Location or object; Up to 8 cubes per level','With the Antipathy effect you cause an object or location to repel creatures of a specific race or alignment.\\nWith the Sympathy effect you cause an object or location to attract creatures of a specific race or alignment.',NULL,'S - The spell works as intended.\\nAntipathy: Affected creatures are unable to enter the area or approach within 12 sq of the object (LoS).\\nSympathy: Affected creatures feel an overpowering urge to stay in the area or approach and touch the object (if within 12 sq and LoS).\\nF - The spell fails to attract or repel the target.\\nAntipathy: Intended creatures feel uncomfortable (shaken) within the area of effect.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(10,'Arcane Mark','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Illusion','(d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC)','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+1 PP for invisible mark','Tch (+0)','Permanent (+0)','One personal mark','You mark any object or surface with your personal rune or mark (up to six separate characters). The mark can be no larger than 30x30 cm. On a living creature, the mark disappears after roughly one month.\\nBy paying the additional cost, you can make the mark invisible (but still visible to anyone able to detect magic or invisibility).','Invisible option: The mark is invisible, but can be seen by anyone able to detect magic or invisibility.\\nLocation option (req Arcane - Divination): As long as you are in the same plane, you can sense the approximate direction and distance to the mark.\\nSecret chest option (req Arcane - Conjuration and Ouranomancy; [Dimension]): You mark a special chest (constructed of expensive materials and worth at least 500 gp) that you can repeatedly hide on the Ethereal Plane and summon to your present location at will (5 AP cost). Regardless of the chest\'s actual size, it can contain 30 litres per skill level.\\nSummoning option (req Arcane - Conjuration; [Teleport]): If the mark is placed on an object weighing no more than 5 kg, you can summon it to your current location at any time (5 AP cost). If the object is held or carried by another creature, you have to make a spellcasting check against that creature\'s Will.',NULL,NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(11,'Arcane Ward','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Divination',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+2)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (tiny bell)','1 PP\\n+4 PP keeps out normal animals\\n+4 PP trigger on ethereal/incorporeal','Close (+0; PoE)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','Spherical emanation; 4 sq radius (+0), 8 sq radius (+4)','You create a ward that triggers a mental or audible alarm every time a creature of tiny or larger size enters without saying the password.\\nMental alarm: If you are within 1 km, you hear a mental \"ping\". It wakes you up from normal sleep but does not interrupt your concentration.\\nAudible alarm: A bell-like sound is heard for 1 round within the warded area and up to 12 squares outside.','Animal option: Normal animals will not willingly enter the area.\\nEthereal option: The alarm will also trigger on incorporeal and extradimensional creatures.\\nProtection option [Illusion]: When the ward triggers, a number of protective effects take place. The area fills with dense fog (as in Fog Cloud spell), all doors become magically held (as in Hold Object spell), stairways are filled with strong entangling webs, up to ten doors can be hidden behind illusory walls, and the fog can be made nauseating in two separate positions. All of these effects have a duration of one day.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(12,'Astral Construct','[Su, AoO, Dimension]','Psi - Metacreativity',NULL,'1 r (+0)\\n7+TPC AP (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','2 PP per CL','Close (+0; PoE)\\nMedium (+3; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Astral construct(s) (+0)','You use ectoplasm to create one or more astral constructs of the chosen total CL. They appear at any spot you choose within range and can act immediately. They automatically protect you and attack your opponents, but you can direct them to perform other actions.\\nWhen the spell ends or the creatures die, they dissipate without a trace.','Shambler option: Instead of an ectoplasmic creature, you create a pseudo-alive ectoplasmic mist. It has a size of 3x3 squares and is 2 squares in height, and it has a speed of 1. The mist is very thick and reduces visibility to one square. Furthermore, the mist is corrosive, and enveloped creatures take 5 HP of acid damage per round.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,'Atonement','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Blessing',NULL,'1 h','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','9 PP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 living creature (+0)','You remove the burden of acts and misdeeds that have angered the target\'s deity. The target must be truly repentant.\\nIf the acts were committed unwittingly or unwillingly, there is no additional cost. If the acts were deliberate, however, the caster must sacrifice a part of his soul (500 XP). It is also recommended that the subject performs some sort of quest to prove his dedication and remorse.\\nAtonement can be used for the following more specific purposes:\\n- Reverse magical alignment change (no XP cost).\\n- Restore class benefits (may involve XP cost).\\n- Change of alignment (no XP cost).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,'Attack of the Beast','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Animals\\nPsi - Psychometabolism',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for bite attack\\n1 PP for claw attacks\\n+4 PP per damage dice increase (up to four steps)','Personal (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)','The basic spell transforms either your mouth into a fanged maw or your hands into sharp claws. If you are medium-sized, a transformed bite causes 1d8 P HP of damage, and a transformed claw deals 1d4 S HP of damage.\\nYou can spend additional PP to increase the damage dice, 3 PP per step.','Extendable option (only for claws): You can extend your claws greatly, increasing your reach by 1 square and making the claws count as one size larger.\\nPain strike option: Your natural weapons also cause 1d6 SP of damage with each successful attack.\\nGraft weapon option (req Psi - Psychometabolism; only for claws): Instead of turning your hands into beastly claws, you graft one or two one-handed weapons onto your hand or hands. A grafted weapon gains a +1 circumstance bonus to attack, parry, and damage, and it cannot be disarmed. However, a hand with a grafted weapon cannot be used as a regular hand (with the penalties this entails).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(15,'Awaken Intelligence','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Divine - Animals or Plants','d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC\\nand then d20! + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will (or DC 20 for a tree)','1 day','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','9 PP, 250 XP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 animal or tree (+0)','You awaken a tree or animal to humanlike sentience. The awakened subject becomes friendly towards you but has no special obligations or compulsions to help you. It automatically learns to speak your native language.\\nAn awakened animal receives 3d6 Intelligence, +1d3 Charisma, and +2 racial levels.\\nAn awakened tree becomes an \"animated object\" of the same size but also receives Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores of 3d6.',NULL,'S - You awaken the animal or tree and grant it intelligence.\\nF - The spell fails.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(16,'Banishment','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Conjuration\\nDivine - Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation','(Rch: d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20! + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (see below)','7 PP','Rch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You try to banish an extraplanar creature back to its home plane.\\nNote that some creatures may wish to return and will therefore be willing targets.',NULL,'S - The extraplanar creature is sent back to its home plane.\\nF - You fail to banish the creature.','For every focus hated or feared by the target: +2','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(17,'Bestow Power','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Divine - Charm and Life\\nPsi - Telepathy',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','2 PP per 1 bestowed PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You channel your mental energy into the target creature(s), using it to cure their mental fatigue. The base cost is 2 PP per 1 bestowed PP (same amount for each target).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(18,'Binding','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment','(Rch: d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','1 min (+0)\\n1 r (+4)\\n7+TPC AP (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (gems worth 500+ sp per target\'s TL; only for creatures and for duration longer than an encounter)','9 PP','Rch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\n1 year (D; +6)\\nPermanent (D; +8)','1 creature or object (+0)','This spell creates a magical restraint to bind and/or hide the target creature or object.\\nYou can specify any number of triggering conditions that can end the spell prematurely and release the target. If the DM deems the conditions reasonable, they provide a bonus to the attack check.\\nThe following binding types can be chosen:\\n- Chaining (req Arcane - Transmutation): The target is immobilized and confined in magical chains. The chains generate an Antipathy effect that affects all creatures other than the caster.\\n- Slumber: The target becomes comatose and does not age nor need to eat, drink, or breathe for the duration.\\n- Bound Slumber (req Arcane - Transmutation): A combination of Chaining and Slumber.\\n- Imprisonment (req Arcane - Ouranomancy): Same as Slumber, but the target is also imprisoned far beneath the surface of the earth.\\n- Hedged Prison (req Arcane - Ouranomancy): The target is transported to a confined area (e.g. a labyrinth) from which it cannot escape.\\n- Metamorphosis (req Arcane - Transmutation): The target\'s body (but not head) assumes a gaseous form, and the target is bound within a magical container. The target remains aware and can still speak, but it is unable to escape, attack, cast spells, and use other skills and abilities. It does not age nor require food, drink, and air for the duration. Breaking the container ends the spell.\\n- Minimus Containment: The target is shrunk to a size of 2 to 3 cm and bound within a magical container. It does not age nor require food, drink, and air for the duration. Breaking the container ends the spell.','Sequester option (req Arcane - Illusion): The target is also rendered invisible, and attempts to scry on or magically locate the target have to beat your spellcasting check.\\nTrigger gem option: For this option, the material component has to be a single gem (instead of several). The spell is stored inside the gem and does not take effect until the intended target touches or picks up the gem.','S - The target is helpless for 1 round while fighting off the spell.\\nES - You successfully bind the target.\\nF - You fail to bind the target.','Each reasonable termination trigger: +2 (maximum +6)\\nTarget\'s name known: +2\\nTarget\'s background history known: +2\\nUsing a statuette of the target as focus: +2\\nSlumber binding: -1\\nBound Slumber binding: -2\\nImprisonment binding: -2\\nHedged Prison binding: -3\\nMetamorphosis binding: -4\\nMinimus Containment binding: -4\\nTrigger gem: +10','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(19,'Blade Barrier','[Su, MR, AoO, Force]','Arcane - Abjuration and Kinetomancy\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Psychokinesis','d20! + 5 vs. DeC (for force weapon)\\nd20! + 10 vs. Ref (for the Wall of Blades variation)','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+2 PP per +1 attack or parry (up to +5)\\n+1 PP per +1 damage (up to +10)\\n+2 PP for additional d8 HP radiant damage [Radiant]','Medium (+0; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','One force shield (+0)\\nOne force weapon (+2)','With the single shield \"area\", you create a shield of pure force. It provides you with a +2 parry bonus to DeC, and it also works against ethereal and incorporeal attacks.\\nWith the single weapon \"area\", you create a weapon of pure force and direct it against one opponent within range. The weapon automatically makes one attack per round (starting on the round it is created), successful hits dealing 2d8 S HP or B SP of damage. The weapon can be redirected to a new opponent by spending 5 AP.\\nBy spending more PP, you can increase the damage caused by the force weapon(s).','Radiant weapon option [Radiant]: Infuses the weapon(s) with radiant energy, doubling damage against undead.\\nAnti-force weapon option: If the weapon strikes a [Force] effect of lower PL, that effect is dispelled.','Force weapon:\\nS - The target takes the specified amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - The weapon misses.\\nWall of Blades variation:\\nS - The target takes 1d6 per 2 skill levels HP of slashing damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - The target takes half damage.\\nCF - The target avoids all damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(20,'Bless Water','[Su, AoO, Radiant/Necrotic]','Divine - Blessing',NULL,'1 min','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (25 sp of powdered silver)','1 PP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','Flask of water (+0)','Imbues a flask of water with radiant or necrotic energy, turning it into holy or unholy water.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(21,'Blight','[Su, MR, AoO, Water]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nDivine - Elements','Ranged: d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort\\nRch: d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 4d6 SP\\n+1 PP per add. 1d6 SP','Rch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)\\nLong (+9; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 plant (+0)\\n1 living creature (+2)\\n2 living creatures (+4)\\n3-4 living creatures (+6)\\n5-8 living creatures (+8)\\n9-16 living creatures (+10)\\nLiving creatures in spherical spread; 12 sq rad (+6), 18 sq rad (+10)','This spell evaporates moisture from the targets, causing the indicated SP damage. Plants, water elementals, and other creatures sensitive to dehydration take d8s of damage instead of d6s.',NULL,'S - The target suffers the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - The target suffers half damage.\\nCF - The target takes no damage.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(22,'Blink','[Su, AoO, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Personal (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)','You (+0)','You start to rapidly and randomly switch between the Material Plane and the Ethereal Plane. This occurs several times per round, giving you a 50% chance to completely avoid any attack or magical effect (except those that extend into the Ethereal Plane). You also suffer only half damage from ongoing effects in the area you occupy (unless they extend into both planes). You yourself get some premonition of each switch, but every action you perform still has a 20% chance of activating on the unintended plane. You gain the same offensive advantages when attacking as if you were invisible (+2 attack bonus, and defender can only use passive DeC).\\nYou can pass through solid walls and objects, as long as they are no thicker than 1 square.\\nYou enjoy the same bonuses and effects on both the Material and the Ethereal Planes.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(23,'Body Affinity','[Su, MR, AoO]','Psi - Psychometabolism and Telepathy\\nCleric Affinity - Family Domain\\nCleric Affinity - Suffering Domain','(Rch: d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Rch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\nSpherical emanation, 4 sq radius (+8)','As long as you and the target remain within close range, you take only half HP and SP damage from any attack. The same amount of damage is taken by each of the targets.','Shared pain option: This version does not reduce the damage you take. However, affected creatures take the same amount and type of physical damage (HP as well as SP) that you do for as long as the spell lasts. For example, if you take 10 HP of damage, all affected creatures also take the same damage.\\nAbility affinity option: In addition to HP and SP, affected creatures also suffer the same ability damage to physical ability scores (Str, Con, and Dex) as you do.\\nHealing option: In addition to suffering the same damage, affected creatures enjoy the same healing of HP and SP as you. If this is combined with the ability affinity option, healing of ability damage will also affect all targets.\\nFate link option: Instead of creating a one-way affinity from yourself to the targets, you create a mutual affinity between you and all the affected targets. Whenever one of the targets suffers some damage, all other targets take the same damage.','S - The target\'s body enters an affinity feedback loop with your body.\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(24,'Body Crisis','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Psi - Telepathy','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)\\nLong (+6; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)','1 living person (+0)\\n1 living creature (+4)\\n2 living creatures (+6)\\n3-4 living creatures (+8)','The basic spell causes horrible agony in the mind of the target (who is effectively sickened for the spell\'s duration).','Breath option: This option disrupts the breathing cycle of the targets, causing 1d6 SP of damage per round.\\nCardiac option: This option interrupts the heart rhythm as well as the breathing of the targets. Damage increases to 2d6 SP and 2d6 HP per round.','S - The target is successfully affected.\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(25,'Bolt of Acid','[Su, MR, AoO, Acid]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nPsi - Psychometabolism\\nCleric Affinity - Earth Domain','d20! + Dex mod + weapon skill + MAM + other mods vs. DeC or Ref','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 2d6 HP\\n+1 PP per additional 1d6 HP','0 or Close (+0; LoE)\\nMedium (+3; LoE)\\nLong (+6; L