rolled for as long as you concentrate.\\nF - The target is unaffected.','Actions that go against target\'s nature: -2\\nSuicidal actions: -5','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(44,'Control Earth','[Su, AoO, Earth]','Arcane - Lithomancy\\nDivine - Elements',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','11 PP','Long (+0; PoE)','Instantaneous (+0)','10000 squares (S; +0)','The basic spell slowly moves earth (dirt, clay, loam, or sand, but not rock) from one place to another. You can change elevation in any spot by up to 2 squares up or down, collapsing embankments, creating hills, shifting dunes, etc. The change is too slow and wavelike to seriously affect creatures in the area.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(45,'Control Emotions','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm\\nPsi - Telepathy\\nBardic Music','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for calm\\n1 PP for rage','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You try to alter the target\'s emotions in some way.\\nThe calm effect calms agitated or excited creatures. Affected creatures can defend themselves but not take violent actions or do anything destructive. Attacks made or damage dealt against an affected creature automatically terminates the spell. The spell also suppresses any bonuses and penalties based on morale and fear.\\nThe rage effect instills the targets with berserker rage, giving a +2 morale bonus to Str and Con, +1 morale bonus on Will defense, and a -2 penalty on DeC.','Sadness option: You cause great sadness, giving the targets a -2 morale penalty on all action checks, weapon damage rolls, and defenses.\\nDespair option: Same as sadness, but with a -4 penalty (instead of -2).\\nHope option: You instill hope, giving the targets a +2 morale bonus on all action checks, weapon damage rolls, and defenses.\\nHeroism option: Same as hope, but with a +4 bonus (instead of +2).\\nMirth option: The target laughs uncontrollably, falling prone and rendered unable to take actions. This effect does not work against creatures of Int 2 or lower.\\nDiscord option: The target becomes very irritated and aggressive. Each round there is a 50% chance that it attacks the nearest conscious creature with its most effective attack.\\nDeath wish option: The target gets a suicidal urge and spends its actions trying to harm itself in the most efficient manner. This can include attacking itself, provoking opportunity attacks, jumping into a fire, etc.\\nDancing option: The target gets an uncontrollable urge to dance and can perform no other actions. The dancing imposes a -4 penalty to DeC, -10 penalty to Ref defense, and negates any parry bonus to DeC.','S - You successfully affect the emotions of the target.\\nES - The effect\'s duration increases by one step for free.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.','You or your allies are attacking the targets: -5 for calm emotions','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(46,'Control Fire','[Su, AoO, Fire]','Arcane - Pyromancy\\nDivine - Elements\\nPsi - Psychokinesis',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for control (sz F, +2 PP per increased size)\\n3 PP for pyrotechnics\\n3 PP for smoke cloud','Medium (+0; LoS)\\nLong (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 fire source (+0)','The basic spell lets you control an existing fire of up to the specified size. You can increase or decrease the size by one step or you can move the fire up to 6 squares.\\nThe pyrotechnics effect consumes a nonmagical fire source (up to a 4x4x4 squares volume) by turning it into a momentary pyrotechnics display. Creatures within 24 squares (and line of sight) of the display suffer a +PL attack against Ref (S - Blinded for 1 r; ES - Blinded for rest of encounter).\\nThe smoke cloud effect consumes a nonmagical fire source (up to a 4x4x4 squares volume) by turning it into a cloud of thick smoke that billows out 4 squares in all directions. The cloud renders all vision ineffective, and creatures that need to breathe risk suffer a +PL attack against Fort (S - -4 penalty to Str and Dex).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(47,'Control Light','[Su, AoO, Light]','Arcane - Illumination\\nPsi - Psychokinesis',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 light source (+0)\\n2 light sources (+2)\\n3-4 light sources (+4)','This spell lets you increase or decrease the power of the target light sources. The intensity can be reduced to nothing or increased by one step (from dim to normal, normal to bright, etc). In addition, the radius of a light source can be reduced by up to 100% or increased by up to 100%. The intensity and size can be altered continuously, for as long as the spell lasts.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(48,'Control Temperature','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Lithomancy\\nDivine - Elements\\nPsi - Psychokinesis','d20! + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will (against attended object)','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +4)','Stone and metal in spherical spread; 3 sq radius (+0)','The basic spell gradually heats or chills stone and metal objects. The maximum amount of affected material is 10 kg per skill level, and a creature must wear metal armor or carry metal and stone objects weighing at least one-fifth of its own weight to suffer the effects listed below.\\nRound 1: Cold/Warm, No damage\\nRound 2: Icy/Hot, 1d6 HP of cold/fire\\nRound 3+: Freezing/Searing, 2d6 HP of cold/fire',NULL,'S - You successfully heat or chill the targeted objects.\\nF - You fail to affect the objects.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(49,'Control Undead','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Death','d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Special (+0)','1 undead (+0)\\n2 undead (+2)\\n3-4 undead (+4)\\n5-8 undead (+6)\\n9-16 undead (+8)','The basic spell makes you and your companions effectively invisible to the targeted undead, causing them to ignore you completely (as long as you don\'t touch or attack them).','Charm option: You change the target\'s attitude to friendly. You will still need additional skill checks to convince the creature to do things it would not ordinarily do, and suicidal orders will not be obeyed. If you attack the target, you automatically break the spell.\\nHold option: You render the target immobile and helpless.\\nCompulsion option: You can actually control the undead creatures (compelled condition) with simple mental commands as long as they remain within range.','S - The target ignores you for the rest of the encounter. For the other variations, the duration is 1 round.\\nES - The effect lasts for the rest of the encounter (all variations).\\nCS - The effect\'s duration increases to one day.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.','You or your allies are attacking the targets: -5 circ (only charm variation)','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(50,'Control Vegetation','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Plants\\nCleric Affinity - Plant Domain',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Long (+0; PoE)','Instantaneous (+0)','Special (see below)','This spell can have one of the following effects:\\nOvergrowth: You cause normal vegetation to become extra thick and overgrown (see heavy undergrowth in Environment chapter). Multiply all movement costs in the area by 4. The area can be a 20 square radius circle, a 30 square radius semicircle, or a 40 square radius quarter-circle.\\nPrune growth: You cause normal vegetation to shrink to one-third its normal size, becoming less tangled and bushy. The vegetation appears to have been carefully pruned and trimmed. The area can be a 20 square radius circle, a 30 square radius semicircle, or a 40 square radius quarter-circle.\\nGreenshield: You cause an area of abundant foliage to shape itself into 6 sq diameter hemispherical \"chamber\". Creatures inside have full concealment towards the outside, and good concealment the other way. The area looks relatively natural and can only be detected with a DC 15 Spot check.\\nEnrichment: You increase the potential growth and productivity of normal vegetation by one-third for one year. The area is a circle of 1 km radius.\\nStunt growth: You reduce the potential growth and productivity of normal vegetation by one-third for one year. The area is a circle of 1 km radius.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(51,'Control Water','[Su, AoO, Water]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nDivine - Elements\\nCleric Affinity - Ocean Domain',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','9 PP','Long (+0; PoE)','1 h (D; +0)','Circular surface of water; 20 sq rad (+0), 30 sq rad (+4), 40 sq rad (+8)\\n+4 for shapeable','You raise or lower a surface of water by up to 0.5 m per skill level. At the start of the effect, you can choose to change the level uniformly or as a wave propagating in any direction, traversing the entire area in a single round. Boats at the edge of the altered surface will slide down to the lower level.\\nAlternatively, you can redirect the area\'s natural flow of water for the spell\'s duration. You can change currents or make rivers flow uphill, for example.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(52,'Control Weather','[Su, AoO, Air, Water]','Arcane - Aeromancy and Hydromancy\\nDivine - Elements and Nature',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for winds','Medium (+0; PoE)\\nLong (+3; PoE)','Concentration (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Cylindrical volume; up to 8 x level sq rad, 8 sq high (+0); 3 km rad, 3 km high (+4); 6 km rad, 3 km high (+8)','You alter the winds and/or weather in the local area. The wind effects are noticed as soon as the casting is completed, but other weather effects take approximately 10 minutes to manifest.\\nFor wind, you can alter its direction and strength, and you can optionally create a calm eye around you of up to 8 square radius. Other than a normal wind blowing in a single direction, you can create a downdraft from the center outward, an updraft from the edges towards the center, or a clockwise or counterclockwise rotation. For every skill level, you can increase or decrease the wind speed by 3 m/s.','Weather option: In addition to controlling the winds, you can also increase or decrease precipitation, fog, and temperature. However, you can only create weather conditions that are appropriate for the climate and season.\\nExtreme weather option: Same as weather option, but you can also create weather conditions that are not typical or appropriate for the climate and season.\\nVengeance option (req Divine - Retribution): You summon a fierce storm, including black clouds, lightning, and thunder. If you concentrate on the storm for a minimum number of rounds, you can trigger specific effects in the area; after 2 or more rounds, acid rain causing 1d6 HP of damage; 3 or more rounds, six bolts of lightning strike one square each (+20 attack against Ref; S - 10d6 HP of electricity damage; F - half damage); 4 or more rounds, hailstones dealing 5d6 HP of blunt damage. Even when you don\'t concentrate on the storm, it reduces visibility to 1 square, effectively deafens all creatures in the area, quadruples movement costs, and makes ranged attacks impossible.\\nCyclone option: As part of the wind alteration, you create a small cyclone that lasts for up to one round per skill level. The cyclone has a 2 sq diameter at the base, 6 sq diameter at the top, and is 6 sq tall. It can move 12 squares per round, and you can specify its path at the time of casting or control it each round by spending 6 AP. Creatures of Large size or smaller take 3d6 HP per round in contact with the cyclone. If a +10 attack beats the Ref of a victim of Medium size or smaller, it is bodily picked up by the cyclone and carried along, automatically taking 1d6 HP and 1d6 SP of damage per round.\\nWaterspout option: You cause a waterspout to rise up from a body of water at least 2 squares wide and 4 squares deep. The spout has a 1 sq radius and is 16 sq tall, and you can move it 6 squares per round (but it must remain over water). Creatures and objects in contact with the spout suffer a +8 attack against Ref each round. A successful attack causes 4d6 SP of damage. Creatures and objects of medium size or smaller are sucked into the spout and take 2d6 SP per round for 1d3 rounds (after which they are expelled).\\nMaelstrom option: You create a deadly vortex in a body of water. The vortex has a 12 square radius and is 12 squares deep, and the body of water must be at least this size. Any creature or craft of large size or smaller suffers a +10 attack against Ref each round. If the attack succeeds, the target is sucked into the vortex. Once sucked inside, a target is battered for 4d6 SP per round for 2d4 rounds (after which it is expelled).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(53,'Courage','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Divine - Charm',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for +4 bonus\\n+4 PP for immunity','Close (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You instill courage in the target creatures, giving them a morale bonus (or immunity) against fear effects. Fear effects that are active at the time of casting are suppressed for the spell\'s duration.','Immunity option: The target creatures become completely immune 