dallion, etc.','Unlimited option: The destination can be any location in the same plane.\\nExtraplanar option: The destination can be any location on any plane.\\nTwo-way option: The portal is two-way and clearly visible at both the origin and destination locations.\\nKeyed option: The portal is keyed to a trigger of some sort. Here are some example triggers: active when exposed to sunlight, active at the autumn equinox, active for one minute after password is spoken, active only for creatures carrying a certain medallion, etc.','S - You create a portal to the correct destination.\\nF - You create a portal, but you miss the destination by 1d4x10%.\\nOF - You fail to open the portal.','Very familiar destination: +0\\nStudied destination carefully: -2\\nSeen destination casually: -4\\nViewed destination once: -6',NULL,NULL),(56,'Create Sustenance','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Life and Summoning',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+2)\\n1 r (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for water or purification\\n+4 PP for food','Close (+0; PoE)','Instantaneous (+0)','Sustenance (see below)','The basic spell creates up to 10 l of water per skill level. Alternatively, it can be used to purify spoiled, rotten, or poisoned food and drink, making it suitable for eating and drinking. The latter use is limited to an amount suitable for 10 M-sized creatures per skill level (daily intake).\\nFood: In addition to the water, you create simple but nourishing fare for up to 3 M-sized creatures per skill level (daily intake). The food stays fresh for approximately 24 hours.','Food option: In addition to the water, you create simple but nourishing fare for up to 3 M-sized creatures per skill level (daily intake). The food stays fresh for approximately 24 hours.\\nFeast option: You bring forth a great feast suitable for up to one M-sized creature per skill level. In addition to the food and drink, you call forth tables, chairs, and services that remain for 1 hour. Those that partake of the