), 50 sq (+2), 100 sq (+4), 200 sq (+6)','The basic spell detects natural poisons and diseases, whether they are part of a creature, an object, or an area.\\nFast detection: A single scan gives all the information (see below).','Hazard detect option: You detect natural hazards (quicksand, sinkholes, deadfalls, etc) and simple traps (pits, snares, etc).\\nAnimal detect option (req Divine - Animals): You detect one particular kind of animal. Each round, you can change the kind you detect.\\nPlant detect option (req Divine - Plants): You detect one particular kind of plant. Each round, you can change the kind you detect.\\nFast detection option: A single scan gives all the information (see below).','1st round - You detect the presence or absence of poison, disease, hazard, or the chosen animal or plant.\\n2nd round - You detect the number of poisons, diseases, hazards, or specimens of the chosen animal or plant.\\n3rd round - You detect the location of each aura. For poisons and diseases, you also detect its type and strength (and this provides a +4 circumstance bonus for Healing checks to treat it), for hazards, its type, and for animals and plants, its status (healthy, diseased, bloodied, or dying).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(70,'Detect Teleportation','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination and Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Clairsentience and Psychoportation',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+2 PP for portal detect\\n+1 PP for fast detection','0 (+0)','Concentration (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Conical emanation; 12 sq (+0), 24 sq (+1)','You detect teleportation effects into or out of the area. You also detect any such effect that took place during the previous minute.\\nPortal detection: In addition to instantaneous teleportation effects, you also detect magical portals, gates, teleportation circles, and extradimensional access points.\\nFast detection: A single scan gives all the information (see below).','Portal detection option: In addition to instantaneous teleportation effects, you also detect magical portals, gates, teleportation circles, and extradimensional access points.\\nFast detection option: A single scan gives all the information (see below).\\nDivert teleport option [Teleport]: If a teleportation attempt out of the area fails to beat your spell\'s PL, you can choose to divert the teleport to a different destination within the teleport effect\'s range.','1st round - You detect the presence or absence of teleportation effects, portals, et al.\\n2nd round - You detect the number of teleportation effects in the area.\\n3rd round - For teleportation effects, you can make a Spellcraft check to detect the approximate direction and distance of the teleport. For portals, you detect the special properties (triggering conditions, limitations, one- or two-way, etc) of each portal. You can make a Spellcraft check to get a rough indication of the direction and distance to a portal\'s destination.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(71,'Detect Thoughts','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination and Enchantment\\nPsi - Clairsentience and Telepathy','d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+1 PP for fast detection','0 (+0)','Concentration (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Conical emanation; 6 sq (+0), 9 sq (+2)','You detect thoughts and consciousness.\\nFast detection: A single success gives all the information of a triple success (see below).','Fast detection option: A single success gives all the information of a triple success (see below).','1st round - You detect the presence or absence of thinking creatures (Int 1 or higher).\\n2nd round - You detect the number and approximate intelligence of thinking creatures.\\n3rd round and S - If your attack beats a creature\'s Will, you pick up its surface thoughts.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(72,'Dimensional Lock','[Su, MR, AoO]','A