er round, the hand can initiate a grapple (+32 vs. DeC) or make a grapple attack (+37 attack; 2d6 + 12 HP blunt damage).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,'Foresight','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination\\nDivine - Insight\\nPsi - Clairsentience',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP per offensive +1\\n5 PP per defensive +1\\n11 PP per reroll','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','1 r (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +10; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+2)\\n2 creatures (+4)\\n3-4 creatures (+6)\\n5-8 creatures (+8)\\n9-16 creatures (+10)','This spell gives the target a rudimentary sixth sense or precognitive ability. This precognition means that you gain an insight bonus to attack rolls (offensive choice) and/or to DeC and Ref defenses (defensive choice). The reroll option means that one check (typically one that you fail or one that an enemy succeeds with) can be rerolled; note that any single check may only be rerolled once.','Danger sense option: The target gains 6 bonus skill levels in the Danger Sense skill.\\nImproved danger sense option: The target cannot be surprised or flat-footed, and the bonus skill levels in Danger Sense increase from 6 to 12.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,'Freedom','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Psychometabolism and Psychoportation\\nKi - Study of Water',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+12 PP for greater freedom','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (existing effects only; +0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +10; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+2)\\n2 creatures (+4)\\n3-4 creatures (+6)\\n5-8 creatures (+8)\\n9-16 creatures (+10)','You make the target resistant to mundane or magical effects that restrict and slow. The target can move with full speed and freedom through water, mud, undergrowth, webs, and similar obstacles. It also gains a +10 enhancement bonus on any defense against grappling and entangling attacks, spells that slow movement or cause paralysis, and similar effects.\\nExisting and active effects that slow or entangle are also terminated, if the effect\'s PL is beaten.\\nGreater freedom: The target gains immunity (rather than a +10 bonus) against slowing and restricting effects. The immunity also extends to binding spells, petrification, stunning, and similar effects.','Greater freedom option: The target gains immunity (rather than a +10 bonus) against slowing and restricting effects. The immunity also extends to binding spells, petrification, stunning, and similar effects.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(105,'Fusion','[Su, MR, AoO]','Psi - Psychometabolism',NULL,'1 r (+0)\\n7+TPC AP (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','15 PP','Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)','You and one willing creature (+0)','You physically join your body with that of another willing creature. This creature must be of the same size category and creature type as yourself. At the time of casting, you decide whether you or the other creature has control of your fused body. You also decide which equipment is worn and carried by the fused body (all other equipment is temporarily absorbed into the body).\\nThe fused body looks like a mix of you and the other creature. It has the sum of both creatures\' health points (HP, FP, and PP; current as well as maximum). Its ability scores, speed, attack forms, skill ranks, and levels will be the best from each creature.\\nWhen the spell ends (or the body dies), the fused being separates, leaving the two bodies in adjacent squares. Damage to health points and ability scores are divided equally between the two bodies.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(106,'Geas','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Lang, Charm]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+8 PP for greater geas','Close (+0; LoS)','Up to 1 week (D; +0)','1 creature (+0)','You place a magical command on the target creature, typically to carry out some service or refrain from some action. If the command is suicidal or nearly so, or if the creature\'s TL exceeds your skill level, the spell fails.\\nIf the target is prevented from carrying out the command or tries to avoid carrying it out, it takes 2 points of persistent ability damage per day to each ability score (to a minimum of 1). This damage disappears 24 hours after the creature resumes its task.\\nGreater geas: In addition to the ability damage for disobeying the geas, the creature also takes 3d6 HP and 3d6 SP of damage per day and is constantly sickened.','Greater geas option: In addition to the ability damage for disobeying the geas, the creature also takes 3d6 HP and 3d6 SP of damage per day and is constantly sickened.','S - The target creature is placed under a magical command.\\nF - The target resists your geas.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(107,'Genesis','[Su, AoO, Dimension]','Arcane - Conjuration, Ouranomancy, and Transmutation\\nDivine - Elements and Summoning\\nPsi - Metacreativity and Psychoportation',NULL,'1 week (33%; +0)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\n1000 XP','17 PP','Medium (+0; LoE)','Instantaneous (+0)','Demiplane (+0)','This powerful spell creates a demiplane of finite size. If you cast the spell on one of the inner planes, you create a demiplane within the Ethereal Plane, and if you use it on an outer plane, the demiplane will take shape within the Astral Plane.\\nWhen the spell is completed, the plane is very small (1 m diameter), but it starts to grow spontaneously, increasing 0.3 m in radius per day for 180 days. After that the rate of growth decreases to 0.3 m per week (approximately 15 m per year).\\nYou determine the plane\'s environment and characteristics as you cast the spell. For an ethereal demiplane this includes atmosphere, water, temperature, terrain features, etc, but it does not include precious materials nor buildings and other constructions. An astral demiplane is typically more dreamlike and spiritual in nature, and your decisions determine primarily how the plane is perceived by visitors.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(108,'Ghost Sound','[Su, AoO, Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion\\nPsi - Psychokinesis\\nBardic Music','d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Illusory sound within a 3 sq radius sphere (+0)\\nIllusory sound in a 1 sq radius emanation centered on creature (+0)','You create the illusion of a sound, roughly limited in volume to four talking humans per skill level. For example, you can create the sound of talking, singing, shouting, walking, marching, running, roaring, squeaking, etc. Some variation in volume and basic character can be programmed at the time of casting.','Silence option: You deaden sounds in the area of effect, providing a -10 penalty on listen checks. Sonic attacks are not affected, but creatures in the area receive a +4 bonus against language-dependent attacks. Action checks with a verbal component suffer a -4 penalty.\\nSound sculpting option: You change a certain type of sound into a different sound. For example, you can change the sound of the wind into singing, or you can change all voices in the area into barking. If this affects someone\'s voice, action checks with a verbal component suffer a -4 penalty.','S - Target does not realize that the sound is an illusion.\\nF - Target realizes that the sound is an illusion.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(109,'Glyph of Warding','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration\\nDivine - Protection and Retribution',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (5 gp of diamond dust per PL)','3 PP\\n+2 PP for concealment','Tch (+0)','Triggered (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +8)','1 glyph (+0)','You trace a clearly visible glyph on an object or surface. When a creature not designated by you at the time of casting interacts with the object (e.g. touches, reads, opens, walks over, etc), the glyph triggers. Optionally, you can designate a password that lets any creature interact with the trapped object without triggering the trap.\\nHiding or being invisible does not fool a glyph, but it will not be triggered by creatures on another plane. Also note that a glyph cannot be used offensively, by throwing a trapped object at an opponent, for instance.\\nIf the duration is permanent, the glyph can be triggered repeatedly (but requires 1 hour to recharge).\\nAcid glyph (req Arcane - Hydromancy or Divine - Elements; [Acid]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of acid damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.\\nCold glyph (req Arcane - Hydromancy or Divine - Elements; [Cold]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of cold damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.\\nFire glyph (req Arcane - Pyromancy or Divine - Elements; [Fire]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of fire damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.\\nForce glyph (req Arcane - Kinetomancy or Divine - Elements; [Force]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of blunt damage in a 2 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes full damage.\\nLightning glyph (req Arcane - Aeromancy or Divine - Elements; [Electric]): +5 attack against Ref (S - 6d6 HP of electricity damage in a 1 sq radius; F - half damage). The trapped object takes no damage.\\nParalysis glyph (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm): +5 attack against Ref (S - the target is enclosed in a shimmering stasis field for up to 10 days (or until released by you)). A captured target is not aware, does not age, and needs no air, food, or drink, but it can still be i