tack bonus per AP',NULL),(118,'Illusory Disguise','[Su, AoO, Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion','(d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will)','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+4 PP for variation','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+2)\\n2-4 creatures (+6)\\n5-16 creatures (+10)\\n17-64 creatures (+14)\\nL creatures count as 2, H as 4, G as 8, and C as 16','You disguise the target with a relatively basic visual illusion. Apparent height can be altered by +/-30 cm, weight by +/-50%, but features and equipment can be given any appearance. Body type cannot be changed.\\nThe spell provides a +10 circumstance bonus to Disguise attempts, but the attack shown above also has to beat the Will of any creature interacting with the illusion.\\nIf used on multiple targets, and unless you pay extra for \"variation\", every target has to be disguised as the same race.','Mask option: Instead of disguising the targets, you cover their faces with shadowy masks. The mask conceals their appearance but does not impede vision. It also provides a +4 circumstance bonus to defenses against blinding attacks and gaze attacks.\\nFull illusion option: The illusion is not only visual, but also includes sound, smell, and touch.\\nVariation option: Each target creature can be disguised as a different race.',NULL,NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(119,'Illusory Double','[Su, AoO, Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion\\nCleric Affinity - Trickery Domain',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Personal (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)','You (+0)','You create one or more illusory duplicates of yourself (with visual and sound components).\\nThe basic spell creates 1d4+1 figments that mimic your every action and move around you but stay within one square. Any creature not immune to illusions will be unable to distinguish between you and the duplicates. When you are subjected to a targeted attack, roll randomly to see if you or one of the figments is the actual target. A figment has the same DeC as the original (but without the benefit of parry bonuses and magical effects), and it is automatically destroyed by any successful attack (but not by area attacks). An opponent can close his eyes to avoid being fooled by the figments, but will instead suffer the appropriate blindness penalties.','Mislead option: You make yourself invisible (see Invisibility spell) while creating a single illusory duplicate in your space. You can direct the duplicate to move anywhere within line of sight (with your own base speed and movement abilities). The duplicate is immune to all attacks.\\nProjection option: You create a single quasi-real duplicate of yourself within 40 squares. It looks, sounds, and smells like you but is intangible and immune to attacks. The duplicate mimics your actions (and speech) every round, unless you spend 5 AP to mentally direct it to act differently. You can choose to see and hear through the duplicate\'s senses, and you can switch your perception back and forth at no cost. You can cast your spells and use other supernatural powers through the projection, causing them to originate from (and even affect) the duplicate. If the distance between you and the duplicate exceeds 40 squares, or if you lose line of effect, the duplicate disappears instantly, and the spell ends.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(120,'Illusory Terrain','[Su, AoO, Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Medium (+0; PoE)\\nLong (+3; PoE)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4)','200 x level cubes (S; +0)','The basic spell makes any natural terrain look, sound, smell, and feel like some other natural terrain. It cannot be used to hide or change creatures, equipment, and constructions.','Wall option: By spending additional PP you can create a visual illusion of natural or constructed walls, floors, and/or ceilings. Such illusions can also be used to hide real doors, pits, and openings.\\nIllusory construction option: You can also hide or change buildings and other constructions in the area.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(121,'Illusory Trap','[Su, AoO, Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (50 sp of iron pyrite)','1 PP','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4)','Object (+0)','This spell creates a visual illusion of a trap on an object or small area (up to one square). Any form of inspection, mundane or magical, will automatically reveal the \"trap\". The inspector has to beat the spell\'s PL in order to recognize it as a false trap.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(122,'Inflict Wounds','[Su, MR, AoO, Necrotic]','Divine - Death','Ranged: d20! + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will\\nTch: d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 2d8 HP\\n+2 PP per additional 1d8 HP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 living creature (+0)\\n2 living creatures (+2)\\n3-4 living creatures (+4)\\n5-8 living creatures (+6)\\n9-16 living creatures (+8)','You channel necrotic energy into the target creature(s), using it to create open wounds.','Flensing option: In addition to dealing damage, a successful attack also causes 1d6 points of ability damage to Con and Cha.','S - You inflict wounds on the target.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - The target takes only half damage.\\nCF - The target takes no damage.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(123,'Insanity','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nPsi - Telepathy','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Special (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You confuse the target, rendering it unable to make rational decisions. At the beginning of each affected creature\'s turn, roll a d10 to determine what it does (1 - attack caster, 2 - act normally, 3-5 - babble incoherently, 6-7 - flee from caster, 8-10 - attack nearest creature).\\nConfused creatures can still defend themselves normally, and if attacked, they automatically try to attack their attacker(s) the next turn.','Stun option: Instead of confusing the target, you stun it. A stunned creature can take no actions.\\nFeeblemind option: Instead of confusing the target, you reduce its Int and Cha to 1. It can still move and attack with weapons, but it cannot cast spells, communicate, or perform most skills.','S - The target suffers the chosen effect for 1 round.\\nES - The effect lasts until the end of the encounter.\\nCS - The effect\'s duration increases to one day.\\nF - The target is dazed for 1 round.\\nOF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(124,'Invisibility','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Illusion\\nPsi - Psychometabolism (target you only and no invisibility sphere variation)',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for concealment\\n+2 PP for good concealment','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)\\n17-32 creatures (+10)\\n33-64 creatures (+12)\\nL creatures count as 2, H as 4, G as 8, and C as 16','The basic spell lets the target blend in with the environment, giving it either concealment or good concealment. The spell ends if the target attacks any other creature by weapon or spell. This also includes natural weapon attacks, brawling attacks, and any area effect that includes a foe, but attacking or handling unattended objects does not terminate the concealment, nor do indirect attacks (such as summoned creatures).','True invisibility option: You make the target (and its equipment) invisible to normal sight as well as darkvision. A creature made invisible becomes visible if it attacks any other creature by weapon or spell. This also includes natural weapon attacks, brawling attacks, and any area effect that includes a foe, but unattended objects can be attacked or handled without terminating the invisibility.\\nInvisibility sphere option: Each target emanates an invisibility sphere of 2 square radius. All creatures within that volume at the time of casting also become invisible, and they remain invisible for as long as they stay within the emanation. Creatures within the emanation can see each other, but creatures entering it after the casting do not become invisible, nor can they see the invisible creatures. If any invisible creature makes an attack, the effect ends for that emanation.\\nGreater invisibility option: The invisibility is not terminated by attacks made by the subject(s).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(125,'Legend Lore','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination\\nPsi - Clairsentience and Telepathy\\nCleric Affinity - Knowledge Domain','Spellcasting check vs. DC (as per Knowledge skill)','1 day (-2)\\n1 h (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (2 gp of incense per PL)','1 PP','Personal (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','You (+0)','You gain a +4 enhancement bonus to a single Knowledge skill check.','Greater lore option: You magically bring to mind legends about an important person, place, or object. The more information about the subject you start with and the better your spellcasting check, the more detailed the results of this spell. Normal success typically reveals the target\'s name, race or type, class, and alignment. Outstanding success also reveals approximate power and current location. Any greater level of success reveals actions taken and locations visited by the target during the previous 8 hours.\\nVision option: Same as greater lore but in addition to the normal results, you may receive a vision about the person, place, or object. This can be a current view or a particularly important vision from its history.','S - You bring to mind legends about the subject.\\nF - The spell fails.','Subject of the casting is at hand: +4\\nDetailed information about subject available: +0\\nOnly rumors about subject available: -4',NULL,NULL),(126,'Levitate','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Kinetomancy\\nPsi - Psychokinesis (target you only)\\nKi - Study of Air',NULL,'7+TPC AP\\nReaction (mandatory check with +10 DC)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature/object (+0)\\n2 creatures/objects (+2)\\n3-4 creatures/objects (+4)\\n5-8 creatures/objects (+6)\\n9-16 creatures/objects (+8)\\nL creatures count as 2, H as 4, G as 8, and C as 16','The basic spell causes the targeted creatures and objects to fall slowly (12 squares per round). This means that they take no falling damage, and the damage they cause upon landing is based only on weight (not on distance).','Water walk option: By hovering 1 to 2 cm over the ground, you can move across any surface (including water, mud, snow, ice, and even lava) as if it were solid ground. You also become harder to track (-10 penalty).\\nFull levitate option: The targeted creature can levitate up or down with a base speed of 4. It cannot move horizontally, unless it is able to push against a wall or ceiling (at half normal speed).\\nTrue flight option: The targeted creature can fly freely in any direction. You can choose either a base flying speed of 6 and good maneuverability or a base speed of 8 and average maneuverability.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(127,'Light','[Su, AoO, Light]','Arcane - Illumination\\nDivine - Life\\nPsi - Psychokinesis',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (+4)','1 object (+0)\\n2-4 objects (+4)','Causes an object of up to medium size to glow and radiate light equivalent to a torch (normal light within 4 squares and dim light within 8 squares). This light does not generate heat or smoke, and the object can be covered to dim or block the light.','Free-floating option: Instead of causing an object to glow, you cause the air itself to glow. You can cause the light to move in any direction up to 20 squares per round.\\nShapeable option: The shape and direction of the glow can be controlled each round. For example, you can turn the light into a cone (like a bullseye lantern) or shape the glow itself into a vaguely humanoid figure.\\nDaylight option: The brightness is equal to full daylight (bright light) within 8 squares, normal light within 16 squares, and dim light within 24 squares.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(128,'Manipulate Corpse','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Death\\nPsi - Psychometabolism and Telepathy (interrogation variation only)','(d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will)','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Tch (+0)','1 week (+0)\\n1 year (+4)','1 corpse (+0)','The basic spell prevents a relatively fresh corpse (or the parts of a corpse) from decaying for the spell\'s duration. It also prevents the soul from departing the body for the same time.','Interrogation option (req Arcane - Enchantment or Divine - Charm; [Mind]): If you make an attack that beats the target\'s Will (that the creature had when alive), you can read the corpse\'s memories. You can effectively \"ask\" the corpse one simple question per two skill levels. Note that this spell only accesses the knowledge and memories of the corpse, not its soul or personality.',NULL,NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(129,'Manipulate Gravity','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Nature',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','13 PP','Medium (+0; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','(4 x skill level) cubes (S; +0)','The basic spell reverses gravity in the area of effect. All unattached objects and creatures immediately fall upward (unless they can levitate or fly). If they strike the ceiling, they take falling damage based on the distance they \"fell\". If falling objects reach the top of the area without striking a ceiling, they stop and float at that point (without taking damage).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(130,'Manipulate Matter','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nPsi - Metacreativity',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP\\n+2 PP for stasis','Close (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 object (+0)\\n(up to a mass of 20 kg per skill level)','You either weaken or strengthen the material of the target object. When weakening an object, you can reduce its DR by up to 5 points (to a minimum of 0); each point also reduces HP by 1 HP per cm of thickness (to a minimum of 1 HP/cm). When strengthening an object, you can increase its DR by up to 5 points; each point also increases HP by 1 HP per cm of thickness.\\nBy paying for \"stasis\", the target object is also protected against the effects of time.','Stasis option: The target object is also protected against the effects of time.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(131,'Manipulate Senses','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Psi - Telepathy','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP for one sense\\n+2 PP per additional sense','Medium (+0; LoS)\\nLong (+3; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You falsify one or more of the target\'s senses. You can\'t create a sensation from nothing nor completely hide a sensation, but you can make the targets believe they see, hear, smell, taste, or touch something different from what is really there. For example, you can make a human appear to be a dwarf, make water taste like wine, etc. The spell lets you alter the size (for vision and touch) or strength (for sound, smell, and taste) from a minimum of 50% to a maximum of 200% of the original sensation.\\nFor multiple targets, all affected targets will experience the same altered sense(s).',NULL,'S - The senses of the target are successfully affected.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(132,'Manipulate Time','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)\\nCleric Affinity - Time Domain','(d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort)','7+TPC AP\\nReaction (mandatory check with +10 DC)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for +2 AP haste (+5 PP per additional +2 AP)\\n3 PP for -2 AP slow (+5 PP per additional -2 AP)','Personal (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','This spell causes time to flow faster or slower for the target creatures.\\nThe haste version gives the targets an enhancement bonus to their AP (and half that enhancement bonus to base speed). The bonus AP can be used as normal AP, for attack bonuses, defensive bonuses, or for additional actions (but not until the start of the target\'s next turn).\\nThe slow version gives the targets an enhancement penalty to their AP.',NULL,'S - The target suffers or enjoys the chosen effect (from the start of its next turn).\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(133,'Manipulate Writing','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination and Transmutation',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)\\n(Permanent for illusory script and suggestive script)','1-2 pages of text (+0)\\n3-8 pages of text (+2)\\n1 book (+4)','The basic spell can be used to either identify or erase written text, whether it is mundane or magical. This can include glyphs, symbols, sigils, and other text-based traps.\\nMundane text is automatically affected, but your spellcasting check must beat the PL of magical text.','Illusory script option (req Arcane - Illusion): You hide the actual writing behind an illusion of either unintelligible text or something else entirely. Only you and people designated by you at the time of casting can read the true text. If you spend an additional 2 PP, a successful dispelling of the illusion will also cause the real text to be erased.\\nSuggestion option (req Arcane - Enchantment): You embed a suggestion (e.g. close the book and leave, forget the book\'s existence, etc) in the text. Make a +PL attack against the reader\'s Will (S - target obeys the suggestion for 30 minutes).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(134,'Meld with Nature','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Nature',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for plant meld','Personal or Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)','You (+0)\\n+(1 to 4) creatures (+4)','The basic spell lets you meld yourself (and optionally 1 to 4 other willing creatures) into a living plant. The plant has to be large enough to contain your body in all three dimensions. Your body remains just below the surface of the plant, letting you hear sounds and sense vibrations from the outside, but rendering your other senses effectively useless. Furthermore, you do not need to (and are unable to) breathe while melded. You remain fully conscious and can even cast non-verbal spells on yourself.\\nAny damage that beats the plant\'s DR will cause the same damage to you, and if the plant is damaged so as to become smaller than you, you are automatically expelled from it. Any transmutation of the plant is also likely to expel you.\\nWhen the spell ends, you exit the plant in the same spot where you entered it.','Stone meld option: Instead of melding with a plant, you meld with a mass of natural stone.\\nNature stride option [Teleport]: After melding with nature, you can teleport to a similar plant or mass of stone within 400 squares (or 600 m). This action costs 5 AP and can be done once per round.\\nGreater stride option [Teleport]: Same as nature stride, but you can teleport to any similar plant or stone on the same plane. When you do this, however, the spell ends automatically.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(135,'Metabolic Trance','[Su, AoO]','Psi - Psychometabolism',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Personal (+0)','Instantaneous/spcl (+0)','You (+0)','The basic spell provides you with sustenance (food and water) for one day.','Stasis option: You enter a trance so deep that even magic cannot detect that you are alive. However, you remain fully aware of your surroundings, and you can dismiss the trance at any time (although this takes 4 rounds). Your metabolism is almost nonexistent, and one year of stasis equals a single day for the purpose of aging, hunger, thirst, and breathing.\\nRegeneration option: You briefly increase your rate of metabolism, gaining regeneration (10 HP/SP per round) for 20 minutes.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(136,'Mind Blank','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Abjuration and Enchantment\\nPsi - Telepathy\\nCleric Affinity - Mentalism Domain',NULL,'7+TPC AP\\nReaction (mandatory check with +10 DC)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for +1\\n+2 PP per additional +1','Personal or Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+2)\\n2 creatures (+4)\\n3-4 creatures (+6)\\n5-8 creatures (+8)\\n9-16 creatures (+10)','By emptying and/or shielding your mind, you gain the indicated resistance bonus to Will defense.','Fortification option: In addition to the improved Will defense, the spell halves any damage to health points and ability scores suffered from mind-affecting spells.\\nImmunity option: Any mind-affecting spell or effect attempted against the target has to beat your spell\'s PL. The same applies to all attempts to magically locate or detect the target.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,'Mind Reading','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Telepathy]','Arcane - Divination and Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm and Insight\\nPsi - Telepathy','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','The basic spell lets you know the target\'s current emotions and also its attitude towards you.','Surface read option: By reading the surface thoughts of the target creatures, you gain a +10 enhancement bonus on Psychology-based skill checks against them.\\nProbe memory option: You can reach into a target\'s mind and examine its memories. Discovering a single piece of information takes a full round, and perusing the memory of an event takes half the time of the actual event. Each successful attack lets you probe one memory.\\nSkill leech option: You \"borrow\" a single skill (caster\'s choice) from the target. For the duration of the spell, you effectively have as many skill ranks in that skill as the target.','S - You successfully read the target\'s mind.\\nF - Target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(138,'Mind Seed','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Psi - Telepathy','d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC\\nand then d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\n3000 XP','15 PP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (spcl; +0)','1 person (+0)','You place a seed containing your full psyche into the subconscious mind of the target. The seed germinates over a period of one week, during which the target gradually takes on your mannerisms and eventually personality and alignment.\\nAfter a full week, the seed has effectively become a lesser mental duplicate of you (as you were at the time of casting but eight levels lower). At this time, the seed will start to fight the target\'s mind for control of the body. Use the rules for possession to determine the exact results. If the occupier becomes expelled, this means that the mind seed is defeated and dies.\\nNote that even when the mind seed is in control, you have no mental connection to or control over it. It has your personality, but it is a separate and fully independent creature.',NULL,'S - The target is successfully seeded.\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(139,'Necrotic Mantle','[Su, MR, AoO, Necrotic]','Arcane - Necromancy','d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','The affected targets do not regain HP, SP, PP, or ability damage for the duration of the spell. This applies to natural healing as well as magical.',NULL,'S - The target cannot regain HP, SP, PP, or ability damage.\\nF - The target cannot regain HP, SP, PP, or ability damage for 1 round.\\nOF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(140,'Petrification','[Su, MR, AoO, Earth]','Arcane - Lithomancy and Transmutation\\nPsi - Metacreativity and Psychometabolism','d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','7 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +4)\\nInstantaneous (+8)','1 creature/statue (+0)','Flesh to stone: Effectively petrifies the target creature (and all of its equipment). A creature transformed to stone becomes inert and non-living but does not really die; when the duration expires or the target is turned back to flesh in some other way, the creature is fully restored to its former state.\\nStone to flesh: Restores a petrified creature to normal. This can also be used to turn a man-sized mass of stone into inert (but edible) flesh.',NULL,'S - The target is paralyzed for 1 round.\\nES - The target is turned to stone or vice versa for the spell\'s duration.\\nF - The target is slowed (-2 AP and -2 speed) for 1 round.\\nOF - The target is unaffected.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(141,'Phase Door','[Su, AoO, Dimension]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Psychoportation',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','9 PP for up to 2 sq depth\\n+3 PP per additional sq\\n+4 PP for private door','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 x 1.5 sq opening','You temporarily \"phase out\" solid wood, plaster, or stone to create a passage. It does not work on metal walls, constructs, or living materials. Creatures still in the passage when the spell ends are shunted towards the nearest exit.\\nIf you pay the extra cost for a \"private door\", the passage is only visible and accessible to you and creatures designated by you. Certain detection powers can reveal the passage but do not provide access to it.','Private option: The passage is only visible and accessible to you and creatures designated by you. Certain detection powers can reveal the passage but do not provide access to it.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(142,'Planar Binding','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Conjuration\\nDivine - Summoning','d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will (if target is unwilling)','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','11 PP\\n30 XP per creature TL','Close (+0; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 extraplanar creat. (+0)','You call an extraplanar creature (either a specific individual or a type of creature) into your presence and try to bind it inside a magical circle. If the creature is unwilling, your attack must beat the target\'s Will. If the creature\'s TL exceeds your skill level, it can decide freely whether to answer your call or not, and it cannot be forcibly contained within the circle.\\nIf successfully contained, the creature is unable to leave, reach outside, or make attacks outside the circle. If the magical circle is broken or disturbed somehow, the creature is instantly released and is free to attack the caster or return to its home plane. Note, however, that the creature itself is unable to directly or indirectly disturb the circle.\\nOnce called, you can try to coerce or bargain with the creature to provide you with information, to fight for you, or to perform a service. The creature can be contained for a maximum of 1 day per skill level. Note that a divine caster who serves the same deity as a called extraplanar creature will be much more likely to elicit a helpful response or at least a fair bargain.\\nWhen the service and any subsequent transaction have been completed, the creature is released and returned to its own plane.',NULL,'S - You call and bind the extraplanar creature.\\nF - You successfully call the creature but fail to contain it.\\nCS - The summoned creature helps you willingly.\\nOF - The target creature fails to appear.','Spellcraft synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(143,'Planar Projection','[Su, MR, AoO, Dimension, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (gem worth 100+ gp)','15 PP for Astral Plane\\n+4 PP for Outer Plane\\n+4 PP for specific loc.','Personal (+0)\\nTch (+2)','Permanent (D; +0)','You or 1 willing creature (+0)\\n2 willing creatures (+2)\\n3-4 willing creatures (+4)\\n5-8 willing creatures (+6)\\n9-16 willing creatures (+8)','You project your soul (and those of the other targets) into the Astral Plane. Once there, the soul will typically create an astral body around itself.\\nYour point of arrival is essentially random.\\nYour physical bodies are helpless and in suspended animation while you are projecting.\\nAn incorporeal silvery cord connects your soul with your physical body, and if this cord should be broken, you die (astrally as well as physically).\\nEach participant can return to his body at will (and terminate the spell for him).\\nPaying for \"Outer Plane\" lets you project the souls all the way into an Outer Plane.\\nIf you pay for \"specific location\", you can specify a desired point of arrival in the destination plane.','Outer Plane option: You project the souls all the way into an Outer Plane.\\nSpecific location option: You can specify a desired point of arrival in the destination plane.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(144,'Planar Travel','[Su, MR, AoO, Dimension, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (tuning fork)','9 PP for Ethereal\\n+2 PP for Shadowfell, Feywild, or Elemental Plane\\n+4 PP for alternate Prime\\n+4 PP precision location','Personal (+0)\\nTch (+2)','Instantaneous (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','You or 1 willing creature (+0)\\n2 willing creatures (+2)\\n3-4 willing creatures (+4)\\n5-8 willing creatures (+6)\\n9-16 willing creatures (+8)','You travel physically to a different plane or dimension. If you travel between the Prime Material, Ethereal, Shadowfell, or Feywild planes (those that overlap the Prime Material), you appear in a location that matches your starting location. If you travel to a non-overlapping plane, you appear 5d% km from your desired location.\\nThe illusory and quasi-real nature of Shadowfell and Feywild lets you travel ten times as fast as normal (relative to the Prime Material). These planes can therefore be used to speed travel to a Prime Material destination.\\nFocus: Each plane requires a tuning fork of a specific material and tuned to a specific frequency.\\nBy paying for \"precision location\", you appear much closer (5d% m) to your desired destination.','Precision location option: You appear much closer (5d% m) to your desired destination.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(145,'Power Word','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment','d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','15 AP\\n10 AP (mandatory check with +6 DC)','V (+0)','13 PP for blindness\\n15 PP for stun\\n17 PP for death','Close (+0; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 creature (+0)','You utter a single word of power that assaults the mind of your target. The target does not actually have to hear the word in order to be affected.\\nThe blindness option causes permanent blindness.\\nThe stun option stuns the target for the rest of the encounter.\\nThe death option simply wills the target to death.',NULL,'S - The target is affected for 1 round (death effect causes paralysis).\\nES - You successfully affect the target for the specified duration.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(146,'Prismatic Attack','[Su, MR, AoO, Light]','Arcane - Illumination','d20! + Dex mod + Area Attack skill + MAM + other mods vs. Ref','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','13 PP','0 (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','Conical burst; 12 sq (+0)','You shoot a spray of vividly colored beams of light from your hand. One or two beams (roll d8) will strike each creature in the area, causing the effects described below.\\n1 - Red: 40 (or 20) HP of fire damage\\n2 - Orange: 60 (or 30) HP of acid damage\\n3 - Yellow: 100 (or 50) HP of electricity damage\\n4 - Green: Poison causing 3d6 (or 1d6) Con damage\\n5 - Blue: Petrification (or -5 AP penalty) for rest of encounter\\n6 - Indigo: Insanity (or 1d6 Wis damage)\\n7 - Violet: Sent to another plane (or no effect)\\n8: Struck by two random beams',NULL,'S - The target is blinded for 1 round an