 pushed along, unless they drop the items (or they are strong or heavy enough to resist).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,'Resize Animal','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Animals','d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for shrink\\n5 PP for growth\\n3 PP for giant vermin','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 animal (+0)\\n2 animals (+2)\\n3-4 animals (+4)\\n5-8 animals (+6)\\n9-16 animals (+8)\\nL animals count as 2, H as 4, G as 8, and C as 16','You decrease or increase the size of the target animals by one step. See the size alteration table for effects on Strength, Constitution, Dexterity, and natural DR.\\nWith the giant vermin variety, you turn normal insects, centipedes, spiders, or scorpions into their giant version (M-sized). You can increase their size further, up to colossal size, by spending 4 extra PP per size category.','Protection option: Targets also receive DR +10 vs non-magical weapons and a +3 resistance bonus on Fort, Ref, and Will defenses.','S - You can change the target\'s size.\\nF - The target resists.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(157,'Resize Object','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 object (+0)','This spell lets you shrink one nonmagical object, reducing its size to 1/16th in each dimension and reducing its volume and mass to 1/4000th. This is equivalent to a reduction in size of four categories.','Transmutation option: You also transmute the object to a cloth-like substance, and this will effectively suspend time for the object. For example, this application could be used on a burning torch or a bucket of water. If the cloth-like object is thrown against a solid surface, the spell ends, and the object 