nM (1000 gp of diamonds)\\nF (divine focus)','13 PP\\n+4 PP for greater resurrection','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 corpse (+0)','You restore life to a creature that has been dead for a maximum of one day per skill level. The creature\'s soul must be free and willing to return. Creatures that have been turned into undead, killed by necrotic damage, or died of old age incur a penalty on the spellcasting check (see Resurrection in Core Mechanics). Apply a further penalty of -10, if the spell is not cast on the plane where death occurred.\\nBeing resurrected is quite a traumatic experience and typically involves some memory loss (see the generic resurrection rules for exact amount of XP lost).\\nThe resurrection spell heals the target\'s body of any fatal injuries (as well as non-magical poison and disease), but the creature still wakes up severely weakened (set current HP, SP, and PP equal to the creature\'s TL). Missing body parts are not restored. Any ability damaged to 0 is restored to 1.\\nGreater resurrection: You can restore life to a creature that has been dead for up to 10 years per skill level. You also halve the check penalty for targets turned undead, killed by necrotic damage, or killed on another plane. All you need is some portion of the creature\'s body. The creature wakes up with full HP, SP, and PP, but still loses XP.','Greater resurrection option: You can restore life to a creature that has been dead for up to 10 years per skill level. You also halve the DC increase for targets turned undead, killed by necrotic damage, or killed on another plane. All you need is some portion of the creature\'s body. The creature wakes up with full HP, SP, and PP, but still loses XP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,'Sanctuary','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Abjuration and Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm and Protection\\nPsi - Telepathy',NULL,'7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Personal or Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+4)','This spell protects the target creature against hostile attacks by mentally repelling attackers. Compare (10 + the spell\'s PL) against the Will of anyone attempting a direct attack (including ranged attacks and targeted spells but not including area attacks). If the spell wins, that attacker cannot make direct attacks against the protected creature for the duration of the spell.\\nIf the protected creature performs a hostile action against anyone, the spell ends.','Repulsion option: In addition to being protected against attacks, the target creature emanates a field that prevents hostile creatures from approaching. The field does not push creatures away, but it prevents affected attackers from moving closer to the target. The caster can set the radius of the emanation from 2 squares to 30 squares.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(161,'Scrying','[Su, AoO, Scry]','Arcane - Divination\\nDivine - Insight\\nPsi - Clairsentience','d20! + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. DC or Will (when scrying on a sentient creature)','1 h (+0)\\n10 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP\\n+2 PP for hearing\\n+4 PP for magical senses','Long (+0)\\nUnlimited (+3)\\nExtraplanar (+6)','Concentration (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','Magical sensor(s) (+0)','You create a floating invisible magical sensor (SZ Fine; 1 HP; DeC 18; Stealth +16) that sends you visual information from its vicinity (24 squares in all directions). The starting point must be within range and either known to you or within line of sight. You can also try to scry on an individual, but then you have to beat his Will defense.\\nYou can use inherent visual enhancements (such as low-light vision and darkvision) through the sensor.\\nIf you pay the extra cost for \"hearing\", the sensor will also pick up sounds as if you were there.\\nBy paying the cost for \"magical senses\", you can also use magically enhanced senses and detection spells through the sensor.','Scrying pool option: Instead of personally receiving the information from the sensor, you show it on a display of some sort (pool of water, crystal ball, mirror, et al). This means you can show it to others.\\nHearing option: The sensor will also pick up sounds as if you were there.\\nMagical senses option: In addition to your inherent enhancements, you can also use magical enhancements and detection spells through the sensor.\\nMobile option: The sensor can be moved at a rate of 6 squares per round. The sensor can pass through openings as small as 3 cm diameter. It cannot pass beyond the chosen range.\\nMultiple sensors option: You create up to 10 separate sensors within range.\\nSmart sensor option: You can give the sensor simple commands, and it can alert you with a mental \"ping\". For example, you can use a mobile sensor to search for a certain object or individual, or you can use multiple sensors to set up a perimeter and watch for dangerous creatures.','S - You successfully create the sensor in the desired location.\\nF - You fail to locate the target (and the sensor is not created). Further tries by you to scry on the same target during the next 24 hours automatically fail.','If you try to scry on an individual, use the following modifiers:\\nNo knowledge: -10\\nSecond-hand knowledge: -5\\nFirst-hand knowledge: +0\\nLikeness or picture of subject: +2\\nPossession or garment: +4\\nBody part, hair, nail, etc.: +10\\nFamiliar: +5','+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(162,'Secure Shelter','[Su, AoO, Force]','Arcane - Conjuration and Kinetomancy',NULL,'1 min (+0)\\n1 r (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+2 PP for servant','Close (+0; PoE)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Sphere; 4 sq rad (+0)','The basic spell creates an immobile sphere of force (typically half above ground and half below). The sphere maintains a comfortable temperature (20 degrees C) and protects against the elements (rain, dust, sandstorms et al) but does not keep out creatures, weapons, or magical effects. A temperature below -20 C or above 40 C or a hurricane force wind (40 m/s or more) will overload the sphere and destroy it instantly.\\nThe sphere is transparent from within but can be made opaque (any chosen color) from the outside.\\nThe caster can illuminate the interior dimly at will.\\nServant: The spell includes a simple, mindless force that can act as a servant (fetch things, clean, mend, move furniture, open doors, etc).','Lodge option: You create a small (2x2 squares) cottage or lodge inside the sphere of force. It can be made to look like a stone, timber, or even sod dwelling, but it always has the strength of a stone building. The lodge has a sturdy door (with a lock), two barred windows, a fireplace (the chimney is protected by a grate), 8 bunks, a table, 8 tools, and a writing desk.\\nServant option: The spell includes a simple, mindless force that can act as a servant (fetch things, clean, mend, move furniture, open doors, etc).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(163,'Sense Link','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Telepathy]','Divine - Animals and Insight (target animal only)\\nPsi - Telepathy','(d20! + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will)','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for one sense\\n+4 PP per add. sense','Medium (+0; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)','You link one of your own senses with that of the target; you either sense what the target is sensing or vice versa. You can use your own senses normally, regardless of whether they are linked to someone else or not. Once the link has been established, distance to the target is no longer important.\\nYou enjoy the benefits as well as penalties of the linked senses. For example, if linked to a creature with darkvision, sight received through the link enjoys the benefits of darkvision, and a gaze attack can take effect through a sight link.',NULL,'S - You successfully link your senses with those of the target.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(164,'Shadow Creature','[Su, AoO, Dark]','Arcane - Illumination and Illusion\\nCleric Affinity - Darkness Domain\\nShadowdancing','d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+2 PP per creature CL\\n+4 PP for greater shadows\\n+8 PP for shades','Close (+0; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Shadow creature(s) (+0)','The basic spell uses shadowstuff to create one or more quasi-real creatures that obey your commands. The creatures have only 20% as many HP, SP, and PP as real creatures of that type. Their natural DR is also just 20% of a regular creature. Opponents that recognize the shadow creatures\' quasi-real nature (typically because your attack fails to beat their Will) suffer less damage from their attacks. Such opponents take only 20% damage from attacks that cause HP, SP, or PP damage, while other attacks have only a 20% chance of working at all. Objects and mindless creatures automatically disbelieve the shadow creatures.\\nGreater shadows: The shadow creatures are 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades: The shadow creatures are 80% real instead of 20%.','Simulacrum option: Instead of choosing a certain creature type, you create a quasi-real duplicate of another creature within the spell\'s range. You must pay the full PP cost, based on the original\'s CL. The caster should make a Disguise check to determine how good the likeness is.\\nGreater shadows option: The shadow creatures are 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades option: The shadow creatures are 80% real instead of 20%.\\nMount option: Instead of a \"normal\" creature, you conjure a horselike mount of Large size. It is black and gray, somewhat insubstantial, and completely soundless. It comes equipped with saddle, bit, and bridle, and it carries up to 10 kg per skill level. It makes no attacks, but most normal animals shun it and refuse to attack it.\\nShadow mount (DeC 14; DR 4; HP 7 + skill level; Spd 3 x skill level)\\nLevitating mount option: Same as mount option, but the creature can move across sand, mud, swamps, water, and other liquid or semiliquid surfaces without difficulty.\\nWatchdog option: Instead of a \"normal\" creature, you conjure a shadow watchdog that guards you and attacks your enemies. It is invisible to everyone but yourself, and it can both detect and attack invisible and ethereal creatures. It barks when any intruder comes within 6 squares and attacks as directed by you.\\nShadow Watchdog (DeC 16; HP 20 + skill level; +10 attack - 2d6+3 HP piercing; invisible)\\nFlying mount option: Same as mount option, but the mount can fly at base speed with average maneuverability.','S - The shadow creatures have full effect against the target.\\nF - The shadow creatures have only their limited effect against the target.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(165,'Shadow Evocation','[Su, MR, AoO, Dark]','Arcane - Illumination and Illusion\\nShadowdancing','d20! + Int mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Will','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','x PP (as per duplicated spell)\\n+4 PP for greater shadow\\n+8 PP for shades','As per duplicated spell','As per duplicated spell','As per duplicated spell','The basic spell uses shadowstuff to duplicate a spell of a different type. The duplicated spell looks and works normally against creatures who believe it is real, but opponents who recognize the spell\'s quasi-real nature (typically because your attack fails to beat their Will) suffer less damage from it. Such opponents take only 20% damage from effects that cause HP, SP, or PP damage, while other effects have only a 20% chance of working at all. Objects and mindless creatures automatically disbelieve the spell.\\nSpells that can be duplicated include Bolt of Acid, Bolt of Death, Bolt of Fire, Bolt of Ice, Bolt of Lightning, Bolt of Radiance, Bolt of Sound, Create Object, Create Wall, Create Web, Fog Cloud, Ice Storm, and Wall of Energy.\\nNote that many duplicated spells will require a second attack roll (as per the duplicated spell).\\nGreater shadows: The spell is 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades: The spell is 80% real instead of 20%.','Greater shadows option: The spell is 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades option: The spell is 80% real instead of 20%.','S - The target suffers full effect from the illusion.\\nF - The target suffers only the reduced effect.',NULL,'+1 attack bonus per AP',NULL),(166,'Shapechange','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nPsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)\\nWild Shape','((d20! + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill + MAM + others mods vs. DeC)\\nand then d20! + Con mod + Body & Mind skill + MAM + other mods vs. Fort)','7+TPC AP','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for grade I\\n+2 PP for grade II\\n+8 PP for grade III\\n+10 PP for grade IV\\n+4 PP for multiple uses\\n+4 PP for mental change','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+4)\\n2 creatures (+6)\\n3-4 creatures (+8)\\n5-8 creatures (+10)\\n9-16 creatures (+12)\\nUnwilling target(s) (+2)\\nNon-mag. object(s) (+2)\\nL targets count as 2, H as 4, G as 8, and C as 16','You alter the appearance and/or physical form of the target or targets.\\nGrade I: You can perform a single grade I shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade II: You can perform a single grade II shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade III: You can perform a single grade III shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade IV: You can perform a single grade IV shapechange of the target(s).\\nMultiple uses: The target(s) can perform multiple shapechanges. Each change requires just 2 AP.\\nMental change: If you are making a grade II or III shapechange and succeed on a (d20! + Body & Mind skill + MAM + Wis mod vs. Will) check, the target\'s mental ability scores, alignment, and personality will also change.','Grade I option: You can perform a single grade I shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade II option: You can perform a single grade II shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade III option: You can perform a single grade III shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade IV option: You can perform a single grade IV shapechange of the target(s).\\nPlant form option: You can turn the target(s) into plants of Large size (shrubs or trees). A creature in plant form has its normal HP, a natural DR of 4, +10 critical hit resistance, and is immobile (Dex and speed 0) but can still see, hear, and smell normally.\\nGaseous form option: You can turn the target(s) into gaseous form.\\nStatue form option: You can turn the target(s) into solid stone statues. A creature in statue form has its normal HP, a natural DR of 8, +20 critical hit resistance, and is immobile (Dex and speed 0) but can still see, hear, and smell normally. If the creature normally consists of flesh, its mass triples.\\nMultiple uses options: The target(s) can perform multiple shapechanges. Each change requires just 2 AP.\\nMental change option: If you are making a grade II or III shapechange and succeed on a (d20 + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + Wis mod vs. Will) check, the target\'s mental ability scores, alignment, and personality will also change.\\nOak body option: The target gains a natural DR of 5 and becomes immune to ability damage, blindness, deafness, disease, drowning, poison, stunning, and other similar effects. It also takes only 1/2 damage from cold but becomes vulnerable to fire. It gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Str but take a -2 enhancement penalty to Dex. The target does not (and actually can\'t) breathe, eat, or drink, but it can still speak.\\nStone body option: Same as statue form option, but the target can still move and act. However, its base speed is halved, and it suffers a natural encumbrance class of 8. It